(92, 4, 1, 'What is role play often used for?', 'Only for entertainment in big theaters.', 'To trick people.', 'To hide your true feelings.', 'As a way to practice real-life situations or explore ideas in a safe environment.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 17:45:46'),
(93, 4, 1, 'Which of these is a key difference between acting and role play?', 'Acting is usually for performance, while role play is often for learning or practice.', 'Acting involves no emotions, while role play does.', 'Acting needs no script, while role play always does.', 'Acting is easy, while role play is hard.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 17:45:46'),
(94, 4, 1, 'What does it mean to \"differentiate\" between acting and role play?', 'To choose which one you like more.', 'To understand and explain how they are different.', 'To understand and explain how they are similar.', 'To practice both at the same time.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 17:45:46'),
(95, 4, 1, 'What is the main goal when you are practicing skills through role play?', 'To improve how you handle situations or express yourself in real life.', 'To avoid learning anything new.', 'To just have fun without a purpose.', 'To become famous.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 17:45:46'),
(96, 4, 1, 'What is a traditional apprenticeship system?', 'A system where a young person learns a trade or craft by working closely with a skilled master for a period of time.', 'A modern school for learning computer skills.', 'A way to learn by only reading books.', 'A system where everyone learns the same job.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 17:45:46'),
(97, 4, 1, 'What is the significance of the traditional apprenticeship system?', 'It helps people forget old skills.', 'It is a very slow way to learn.', 'It plays a crucial role in passing down traditional skills, knowledge, and values across generations.', 'It only helps rich people.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 17:45:46'),
(98, 4, 1, 'Which of these is a type of trade often learned through traditional apprenticeship?', 'Space exploration', 'Medicine (as a doctor)', 'Software programming', 'Blacksmithing or weaving.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 17:45:46'),
(99, 4, 1, 'What does \"skill acquisition\" mean in the context of apprenticeship?', 'Forgetting how to do things.', 'Learning and gaining new abilities or proficiencies.', 'Only learning how to read.', 'Only learning how to play games.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 17:45:46'),
(100, 4, 1, 'What does \"value acquisition\" refer to in the apprenticeship system?', 'Learning important life lessons like discipline, respect, and perseverance.', 'Buying valuable items.', 'Learning about money.', 'Finding new places to live.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 17:45:46'),
(101, 4, 2, 'Imagine an artist creates a painting using bright, warm colors and smiling faces. How might this express cultural identity or emotions?', 'It shows the artist is angry.', 'It tells a story about food.', 'It might express joy, celebration, or a happy cultural event.', 'It means the artist used only one color.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(102, 4, 2, 'You have a piece of clay and want to tell a story about a brave animal. How would you use this material to create your art?', 'By writing words on the clay.', 'By only coloring the clay.', 'By making the clay disappear.', 'By shaping the clay into the form of the brave animal and its surroundings.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(103, 4, 2, 'Consider a painting and a sculpture. How might you compare these two art forms?', 'By only looking at their sizes.', 'By thinking about what materials they use and how they show ideas (2D vs. 3D).', 'By only looking at their colors.', 'By seeing which one is older.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(104, 4, 2, 'You are given different types of paper: rough, smooth, and crinkled. How might you use these materials to show different textures in a collage that tells a story about nature?', 'By using the rough paper for tree bark, smooth for water, and crinkled for leaves to show variety.', 'By making them all look the same.', 'By only using the smooth paper.', 'By throwing away the crinkled paper.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(105, 4, 2, 'A mask is created for a traditional festival. How does this piece of art express cultural identity?', 'It shows what someone wants for a gift.', 'It often incorporates symbols, colors, and designs important to that culture\'s beliefs or history.', 'It is only used to hide faces.', 'It is only for playing games.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(106, 4, 2, 'If you want to draw a tree with leaves moving in the wind, which drawing technique would be most important to develop?', 'Only careful observation of the tree\'s shape.', 'Focusing only on adding many colors.', 'Capturing movement to show how the leaves are blowing.', 'Drawing the tree very small.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(107, 4, 2, 'You are given a bowl of fruit to draw. Which type of drawing are you doing, and what aspect of the world are you trying to express?', 'Nature drawing, showing mountains.', 'Still Life drawing, expressing the arrangement and details of everyday objects.', 'Life drawing, showing people.', 'Landscape drawing, showing a view.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(108, 4, 2, 'When drawing a person, you notice shadows on their face. Applying shading technique helps you to:', 'Make the drawing look flat.', 'Make the drawing seem less realistic.', 'Show the direction of light and make the drawing look more three-dimensional.', 'Only use dark colors.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(109, 4, 2, 'A drawing of a vibrant forest with many plants and animals represents which type of drawing, and what aspect of the world does it express?', 'Nature drawing, showing the beauty and details of the natural environment.', 'Still Life drawing, showing objects.', 'Life drawing, showing people.', 'Abstract drawing, showing ideas.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(110, 4, 2, 'A drawing activity asks you to show the emotions of a happy child playing. Which basic drawing technique would be most useful to develop in this activity?', 'Drawing only straight lines.', 'Observation of how happy people look and move, to help capture their expression and movement.', 'Focusing only on the background.', 'Drawing with your eyes closed.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(111, 4, 2, 'You want to make a birthday card for your best friend. What material would be best to use for adding shiny decoration?', 'Plain white paper.', 'A dull pencil.', 'Glitter or shiny stickers.', 'A broken stick.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(112, 4, 2, 'When making a card for your grandmother, you decide to draw a picture of her favorite flowers. How does this apply creativity to personalize the card?', 'It means you copied someone else\'s drawing.', 'It shows you didn\'t think much about the card.', 'It makes the card seem boring.', 'It shows you used your imagination to make the card special and meaningful for her.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(113, 4, 2, 'You are making a card with a pop-up design, but the pop-up isn\'t working right. How would problem-solving skills help you fix this?', 'You would give up and throw the card away.', 'You would try different folding methods or cutting techniques to make the pop-up work correctly.', 'You would ask someone else to finish it for you.', 'You would just glue the pop-up flat.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(114, 4, 2, 'Why is a handmade card often considered to have more emotional significance than a store-bought card?', 'Because it is cheaper.', 'Because it is faster to make.', 'Because the person who made it put in time, effort, and personal thought.', 'Because it is always perfectly straight.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(115, 4, 2, 'You want to make a card that conveys a feeling of comfort to someone who is sad. What colors and images would you choose to apply emotional intelligence in your card design?', 'Bright, loud colors and sharp images.', 'Soft, calming colors and gentle images like a warm blanket or a quiet place.', 'Dark colors and scary images.', 'Only black and white.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 18:23:11'),
(116, 4, 2, 'You have several paper strips laid out vertically. To start plain weaving, what should you do with a new horizontal strip?', 'Glue it on top without interlacing.', 'Cut it into tiny pieces.', 'Pass it over one vertical strip, then under the next, and continue this pattern.', 'Just stack it next to the vertical strips.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(117, 4, 2, 'When comparing plain weaving and twill weaving, what is a key difference you might observe in the pattern?', 'Plain weaving has no pattern, while twill always has circles.', 'Plain weaving has a simple over-and-under pattern, while twill creates diagonal lines.', 'They both create exactly the same pattern.', 'Twill weaving uses only one color.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(118, 4, 2, 'You are trying to create a pattern where the weft strip goes over two warp strips and under one, then repeats. Which weaving technique are you demonstrating?', 'Plain weaving', 'Mat weaving', 'Knitting', 'Twill weaving.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(119, 4, 2, 'If your paper strips keep slipping out of place while weaving, what problem-solving skill would you apply?', 'Give up and throw away the paper.', 'Ask someone else to finish it for you.', 'Think about ways to secure the strips, maybe by taping the ends or using clips.', 'Make the strips even thinner.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(120, 4, 2, 'You notice that a mat woven using thin, flimsy paper looks different from one woven with thick, stiff paper. How would you analyze this difference?', 'The color of the paper makes it different.', 'The thickness and stiffness of the material affect the texture and stability of the woven piece.', 'One paper is stronger than the other.', 'The shape of the paper is different.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(121, 4, 2, 'Imagine you want to create a mosaic of a sunny day. What materials and colors would you use to convey this message effectively?', 'Dark, dull colored stones.', 'Large, unbroken pieces of grey tile.', 'Small, bright yellow, orange, and blue pieces of glass or tile.', 'Only black and white stones.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(122, 4, 2, 'A mosaic shows a group of people working together to build a house. How does this mosaic convey a message or story?', 'It shows how tall the house is.', 'It means the house is very old.', 'It is just a random picture.', 'It visually tells a story about teamwork and community effort.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(123, 4, 2, 'When creating a mosaic, you realize some pieces are too big for a detailed area. How would you problem-solve this?', 'Use the big pieces anyway, making the detail look messy.', 'Give up on the detailed area.', 'Break or cut the larger pieces into smaller, more appropriate sizes.', 'Ask someone else to do it.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(124, 4, 2, 'An artist uses rough, unpolished stones for one part of a mosaic and smooth, shiny glass for another. How does this choice of materials affect the message or story conveyed?', 'It adds texture and contrast, helping to emphasize different parts of the story or feelings.', 'It makes the mosaic boring.', 'It shows the artist did not plan well.', 'It means the artist ran out of one material.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(125, 4, 2, 'You see a mosaic that uses a lot of swirling lines and bright, clashing colors. How might you analyze the message or feeling it intends to convey?', 'It intends to convey peace and quiet.', 'It might convey a feeling of energy, movement, or even chaos.', 'It intends to convey sadness.', 'It intends to convey boredom.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(126, 4, 2, 'An artist carves a wooden sculpture of a wise elder from their community. How does this artwork express social commentary?', 'It shows that wood is easy to carve.', 'It means the artist is very old.', 'It might comment on the importance of respecting elders in society.', 'It is just a pretty picture.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(127, 4, 2, 'You have a plain calabash and want to decorate it with patterns that tell a story about your family\'s history. How would you explore artistic techniques to do this?', 'By only painting one solid color.', 'By gluing plastic toys onto it.', 'By breaking the calabash.', 'By using traditional patterns or symbols that represent your family\'s heritage and painting them onto the calabash.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(128, 4, 2, 'Some traditional calabash designs use intricate burnt patterns. How does this technique add meaning to the art?', 'It makes the calabash smell smoky.', 'The controlled burning creates permanent, detailed designs that often carry cultural symbols or stories.', 'It makes the designs disappear.', 'It makes the calabash soft.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(129, 4, 2, 'If you are painting a message about peace onto a piece of wood, what choice of colors and images would you apply to convey this message effectively?', 'Soft, calming colors (like blue, white, green) and images like doves or open hands.', 'Bright, clashing colors and angry faces.', 'Dark, gloomy colors and sad images.', 'Only one color that makes people feel confused.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(130, 4, 2, 'A wood carving shows a scene of people working together in a village. How does this artwork reflect its purpose as an artistic expression and social commentary?', 'It only shows trees.', 'It portrays an ideal of community cooperation, offering a positive comment on social values.', 'It is only about the artist\'s personal feelings.', 'It shows people fighting.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(131, 4, 2, 'Traditional Nigerian houses often have thick mud walls and small windows. How does this design reflect adaptation to the local climate?', 'It makes the houses cold inside.', 'It makes the houses darker inside.', 'It helps keep the interiors cool in hot weather and warm in cold weather.', 'It uses up a lot of materials.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(132, 4, 2, 'Many traditional compounds have a central courtyard. How does this design element contribute to family life and social interaction?', 'It keeps families separated.', 'It is only used for storing water.', 'It makes the compound look smaller.', 'It provides a shared open space for family activities, gatherings, and cooling off.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(133, 4, 2, 'Some traditional Nigerian buildings have special symbols carved into their walls or doors. How does this analyze their cultural significance?', 'They are just random drawings.', 'These symbols often represent family history, beliefs, or protection.', 'They are only for decoration.', 'They tell you the building\'s age.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(134, 4, 2, 'Consider a traditional Nigerian building made of local materials like mud, wood, and thatch. How does using these materials contribute to the building\'s sustainability and connection to the environment?', 'It uses resources found nearby and minimizes environmental impact.', 'It means the building will fall down quickly.', 'It makes the building look modern.', 'It means the building is very expensive.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(135, 4, 2, 'If you wanted to learn about a Nigerian community\'s ancient way of life just by looking at their traditional houses, what would you observe?', 'Only the color of the paint.', 'The materials, layout, and decorative elements might tell you about their family structures, beliefs, and climate adaptations.', 'Only the size of the windows.', 'How many doors the house has.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(136, 4, 2, 'A musician writes a song about the importance of family and helping your neighbors. How does this song promote Nigerian values?', 'It promotes only individual success.', 'It teaches children to ignore their elders.', 'It shares and reinforces positive community and family values that are important in Nigeria.', 'It is just a story with no real meaning.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(137, 4, 2, 'You hear a song that uses drums and flutes that sound like traditional Nigerian instruments. How does this musical choice reflect Nigerian identity?', 'It means the song is very old.', 'It makes the song sound like music from another country.', 'It is just a random choice of instruments.', 'It uses sounds and instruments that are part of Nigeria\'s musical heritage.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(138, 4, 2, 'Music can often make people feel happy, sad, or motivated. How does this analyze how music can influence emotions?', 'Music has no power over how people feel.', 'Different rhythms, melodies, and lyrics can evoke various emotional responses in listeners.', 'Music only makes people feel one emotion.', 'Music is only for dancing.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(139, 4, 2, 'Consider a song that tells the story of Nigeria\'s journey to independence. How does this song promote Nigerian identity and social change?', 'It educates and inspires people about their national history and the struggle for freedom.', 'It helps people forget history.', 'It encourages people to complain.', 'It only focuses on one person.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(140, 4, 2, 'A song blends traditional Nigerian drumming with modern pop beats. How does this demonstrate creativity in composing music that blends traditional and contemporary sounds?', 'It makes the song sound confusing.', 'It creates a new, unique sound that honors the past while embracing the present.', 'It shows a lack of understanding of traditional music.', 'It means the song is not Nigerian.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(141, 4, 2, 'A character in a play finds a lost wallet and returns it to its owner, even though they could have kept the money. How does this action demonstrate the value of honesty?', 'It shows the character is not smart.', 'It shows the character is afraid of the owner.', 'It exemplifies telling the truth and doing the right thing, even when it\'s difficult.', 'It means the character doesn\'t like money.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(142, 4, 2, 'In a play, a group of students work together to clean up their school, even though it\'s a big job. How does this scene demonstrate a positive attitude towards work?', 'It shows they are lazy.', 'It means they don\'t like playing.', 'It shows they are only working for a reward.', 'It shows their willingness to cooperate and put in effort for a shared goal.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(143, 4, 2, 'You are participating in creating a short play. If your character is supposed to show integrity, how would their actions or words be?', 'They would say one thing and do another.', 'They would act according to strong moral principles, even when no one is watching.', 'They would always hide the truth.', 'They would constantly change their mind.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(144, 4, 2, 'A play ends with a character who lied facing bad consequences. How does this analyze how drama can be used to teach life lessons?', 'It uses a storyline to demonstrate the negative outcomes of dishonesty, teaching a moral lesson.', 'It shows that lying is fun.', 'It means the play is boring.', 'It encourages people to lie.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(145, 4, 2, 'If a play shows characters who always finish their tasks with care and pride, how does this influence the audience\'s understanding of a good attitude to work?', 'It makes the audience want to be lazy.', 'It models and reinforces the value of diligence and pride in one\'s efforts.', 'It means the audience will never work again.', 'It makes the audience feel sleepy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(146, 4, 2, 'Imagine you want to play a song exactly as the composer intended. How does music notation help you achieve this?', 'It helps you guess how it should sound.', 'It tells you how loud to play.', 'It provides a written guide for pitch, rhythm, and timing, allowing accurate reproduction.', 'It tells you the name of the song.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(147, 4, 2, 'You are given a musical pattern that goes \"Clap, snap, clap, snap.\" How does understanding rhythm help you perform this correctly?', 'It tells you to sing very loudly.', 'It tells you which instruments to use.', 'It makes you forget the pattern.', 'It helps you keep a steady beat and repeat the sequence of sounds and silences accurately.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(148, 4, 2, 'If a composer uses a lot of short, quick notes and silences in their music. How does this choice of notation create a specific feeling?', 'It makes the music sound slow and calm.', 'It can create a feeling of excitement, speed, or nervousness.', 'It makes the music sound sad.', 'It has no effect on the feeling.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(149, 4, 2, 'You are learning a new song. The sheet music shows a half note and then two quarter notes. How does applying your knowledge of notation help you play this rhythm?', 'You play the half note longer than the two quarter notes.', 'You play all notes at the same length.', 'You ignore the different types of notes.', 'You only play the first note.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(150, 4, 2, 'A song has a very fast rhythm. How does understanding this rhythm influence the type of dance movements you might do to the music?', 'You would do slow, flowing movements.', 'You would likely do quick, energetic movements.', 'You would stand still.', 'You would do no movements.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30');
INSERT INTO `exam_questions` (`question_id`, `subject_id`, `type`, `question`, `option1`, `option2`, `option3`, `option4`, `option5`, `feedback1`, `feedback2`, `feedback3`, `feedback4`, `feedback5`, `answer`, `marks`, `createdate`) VALUES
(151, 4, 2, 'A dancer repeats a rising arm movement several times in a performance. How does this apply a dance motif?', 'It shows the dancer is tired.', 'It means the dancer has forgotten other movements.', 'It helps emphasize an idea like growth or hope throughout the dance.', 'It is just a random arm movement.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(152, 4, 2, 'A dancer performs a very high jump with perfect balance. How does this demonstrate a basic dance technique?', 'It shows they are lucky.', 'It means they are not following the music.', 'It is only possible with magic.', 'It showcases control and skill in executing a difficult movement.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(153, 4, 2, 'Imagine a dance uses sharp, quick, and powerful movements as its motif. How does this express emotions?', 'It expresses sadness and quiet.', 'It might express anger, excitement, or a strong, forceful feeling.', 'It expresses calm and peace.', 'It expresses sleepiness.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(154, 4, 2, 'A traditional Nigerian dance uses specific footwork passed down through generations. How does applying these techniques contribute to cultural expression?', 'It preserves and showcases the unique cultural heritage and history of the dance.', 'It makes the dance look modern.', 'It means the dancers are not creative.', 'It only makes the dance look complicated.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(155, 4, 2, 'If a dancer uses flowing, gentle movements as a motif, how would you analyze how it contributes to the dance\'s overall mood?', 'It creates a fast, energetic mood.', 'It creates a calm, peaceful, or gentle mood.', 'It creates an angry, chaotic mood.', 'It creates a confusing mood.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(156, 4, 2, 'Imagine you are in a play and you have to show that your character is very scared. How would you apply acting techniques to do this?', 'By laughing loudly.', 'By standing still and showing no emotion.', 'By using trembling voice, wide eyes, and shaky body movements.', 'By talking about something else.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(157, 4, 2, 'Your teacher asks you to role play a situation where you resolve an argument with a friend. How does this activity help you in real life?', 'It helps you avoid talking to friends.', 'It teaches you how to argue better.', 'It means you will never argue again.', 'It allows you to practice communication and problem-solving skills for real conflicts.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(158, 4, 2, 'An actor studies a script very carefully to understand their character\'s feelings and motivations. How does this technique contribute to a believable performance?', 'It makes the character seem fake.', 'It helps the actor truly embody the character\'s personality and express emotions realistically.', 'It makes the actor forget their lines.', 'It makes the play shorter.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(159, 4, 2, 'If you are using role play to understand what it\'s like to be a teacher, what kind of scenarios would you engage in to effectively explore this role?', 'Scenarios where you practice explaining a lesson, answering questions, or managing a classroom.', 'Scenarios where you only play with toys.', 'Scenarios where you pretend to be a student.', 'Scenarios where you just sit quietly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(160, 4, 2, 'A group of students decide to act out a historical event for their class presentation. How does this differ from just reading about the event?', 'It makes the event less interesting.', 'It makes the event seem less real.', 'It means they don\'t have to learn the facts.', 'Acting allows them to physically portray the characters and emotions, making the history more vivid and understandable.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(161, 4, 2, 'An apprentice spends years observing and helping their master in a workshop. How does this method of learning contribute to acquiring a skill?', 'It makes learning very fast.', 'It means the apprentice doesn\'t have to work.', 'It allows for hands-on practice and direct guidance, leading to deep understanding of the craft.', 'It makes the apprentice bored.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(162, 4, 2, 'An apprentice is always on time and works hard, even when the master is not watching. How does this demonstrate a value acquired through apprenticeship?', 'Laziness', 'Discipline and integrity', 'Dishonesty', 'Impatience.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(163, 4, 2, 'If an apprentice makes a mistake, the master patiently explains how to correct it. How does this approach influence the apprentice\'s learning process?', 'It discourages the apprentice from trying again.', 'It makes the apprentice afraid to learn.', 'It provides constructive feedback, helping the apprentice understand and learn from errors.', 'It means the master is not strict enough.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(164, 4, 2, 'The apprenticeship system often involves respect for the master. How does this value contribute to the learning environment?', 'It encourages the apprentice to listen, learn, and follow instructions carefully.', 'It makes the master feel powerful.', 'It stops the apprentice from asking questions.', 'It makes learning difficult.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
(165, 4, 2, 'You observe a traditional weaver teaching their apprentice how to prepare the threads for weaving, a very detailed process. How does this transfer of skill ensure the survival of the craft?', 'It means the craft will die out.', 'It ensures the apprentice learns the foundational knowledge directly from the experienced master.', 'It makes the craft less popular.', 'It means new machines are not needed.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-06-29 21:22:30'),
