(242, 3, 2, 'Imagine your friend tells you a secret and asks you not to tell anyone. If you keep the secret, how does this reflect loyalty?', 'It shows you are good at keeping secrets.', 'It shows you don\'t like talking.', 'It demonstrates faithfulness and trustworthiness to your friend.', 'It means you are afraid to tell.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(243, 3, 2, 'A story is told about a soldier who bravely protects their country even when it\'s dangerous. How does this story analyze an example of loyalty?', 'It shows that the soldier is very strong.', 'It highlights how the soldier gave up when things were hard.', 'It demonstrates profound national loyalty and dedication to their country.', 'It means the soldier wants a reward.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(244, 3, 2, 'Your school has a rule that everyone must follow to keep the school safe. If you always follow this rule, how does this reflect loyalty to your school?', 'It shows you are scared of rules.', 'It demonstrates commitment to the well-being and rules of your school community.', 'It means you don\'t like trying new things.', 'It is only because someone is watching.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(245, 3, 2, 'A child promises to help their parent with chores, but then goes to play instead. How does this scenario analyze an example of disloyalty?', 'It shows the child is good at playing.', 'It means the child forgot.', 'It shows a failure to keep a promise and support someone they should be loyal to.', 'It teaches the child to be independent.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(246, 3, 2, 'You and your classmates have a project, and everyone agrees to do their part. If you do your part well, how does this reflect loyalty to your group?', 'It means you want to be the best.', 'It shows you are dependable and committed to the success of your team.', 'It means you don\'t trust others.', 'It makes the project harder.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(247, 3, 2, 'Imagine your class needs to choose a leader for a group project. If you apply the knowledge of leadership types, why might a democratic leader be a good choice?', 'They would make all decisions quickly without asking.', 'They would let everyone do whatever they want.', 'They would listen to everyone\'s ideas and help the group decide together.', 'They would only listen to their best friend.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(248, 3, 2, 'A good leader sees that some group members are not participating. How might they demonstrate good leadership characteristics to solve this problem?', 'They would ignore the problem.', 'They would tell those members to leave the group.', 'They would do all the work themselves.', 'They would encourage everyone to share ideas and make sure all voices are heard.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(249, 3, 2, 'Your class decides to organize a clean-up day. What kind of leadership style would be most appropriate for getting everyone to participate?', 'An autocratic leader who just orders everyone around.', 'A democratic leader who explains the importance and involves everyone in planning.', 'A leader who does nothing.', 'A leader who only cleans up by themselves.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(250, 3, 2, 'A school principal makes a new rule without asking any students or teachers. How does this leadership style affect the students\' feelings about the rule?', 'They would feel very happy about the rule.', 'They would feel like they were part of the decision.', 'They might feel that their opinions don\'t matter, leading to less support for the rule.', 'They would understand the rule better.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(251, 3, 2, 'You are trying to solve a group problem: how to share toys fairly. Applying knowledge of leadership types, how could a leader help solve this using a fair approach?', 'The leader takes all the toys.', 'The leader helps the group create rules for sharing that everyone agrees on.', 'The leader hides some of the toys.', 'The leader decides who gets all the toys.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(252, 3, 2, 'The text describes a market that became disorganized due to leadership focused on \"immediate gains and favoring friends.\" How does this analyze the impact of bad leadership?', 'It shows that friends are always good for a business.', 'It means the market was too big to manage.', 'It demonstrates how selfish and unfair leadership leads to chaos and suffering for the community.', 'It made the market more lively.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(253, 3, 2, 'When a community organizes a meeting to discuss problems like market chaos and rising crime, what key aspect of addressing poor leadership are they demonstrating?', 'Ignoring the problems.', 'Taking collective action and engaging in problem-solving.', 'Waiting for things to get worse.', 'Blaming others without action.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(254, 3, 2, 'The text states that leaders who listened to their people\'s needs and made fair decisions made a positive difference. How does this apply to the characteristics of good leadership?', 'Good leaders only tell people what to do.', 'Good leaders are always silent.', 'Good leaders never change anything.', 'Good leaders involve and consider the community\'s voice and welfare in their decisions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(255, 3, 2, 'If a leader tries to \"undermine\" positive community efforts by spreading rumors and creating divisions, how does this analyze the challenges communities face when striving for change?', 'It demonstrates how resistance and sabotage from ineffective leaders can disrupt positive initiatives.', 'It shows that leaders always help.', 'It means the community was not strong.', 'It helps everyone understand each other better.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(256, 3, 2, 'The community in the text decided on \"new rules for the market\" and to \"address workers\' grievances.\" How does this show them solving problems related to bad leadership?', 'They created new problems.', 'They took practical steps to restore order and address unfair conditions caused by poor leadership.', 'They waited for someone else to solve problems.', 'They only talked without doing anything.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(257, 3, 2, 'Imagine your school principal is like the Executive arm of government. What is one thing your principal might do that is similar to the Executive\'s role?', 'Make new rules for the school.', 'Decide if a school rule was broken.', 'Ensure school rules are followed by students and teachers.', 'Argue about school rules.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(258, 3, 2, 'Your school has a student council that helps make rules for students. Which arm of government is the student council most similar to?', 'Executive arm', 'Judiciary arm', 'Community arm', 'Legislative arm.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(259, 3, 2, 'When there is a disagreement in your classroom about a rule, and your teacher helps decide what is fair, which arm of government is your teacher acting like?', 'Executive arm', 'Judiciary arm', 'Legislative arm', 'School arm.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(260, 3, 2, 'The Legislative arm makes a law, and the Executive arm has to approve it. This is an example of \"checks and balances.\" How does this help ensure fairness?', 'It speeds up the law-making process.', 'It makes one arm more powerful than the others.', 'It prevents any single arm from having too much power and abusing it.', 'It makes the government bigger.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(261, 3, 2, 'If the Executive arm (like a school principal) tries to make a rule that the Legislative arm (like the student council) thinks is unfair, what might happen due to checks and balances?', 'The Executive arm would just do what it wants.', 'The Legislative arm might challenge the rule, leading to discussion and possible changes.', 'The rule would automatically become a law.', 'No one would care about the rule.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(262, 3, 2, 'Imagine a pressure group wants to stop littering in your community. How might they influence change?', 'By creating more litter.', 'By ignoring the problem.', 'By organizing clean-up drives and asking local leaders for more bins and awareness campaigns.', 'By moving to another community.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(263, 3, 2, 'A pressure group campaigns for better healthcare for everyone. What challenge might they face?', 'Everyone will agree with them immediately.', 'They might find it easy to get money.', 'No one will care about healthcare.', 'They might face resistance from people who don\'t agree or from leaders who don\'t want to change.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(264, 3, 2, 'You see a group of parents advocating for a safer playground in your neighborhood. How are they acting like a pressure group?', 'They are just playing on the playground.', 'They are trying to influence the local government to make a positive change for children\'s safety.', 'They are trying to build the playground themselves.', 'They are causing trouble.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(265, 3, 2, 'A pressure group organizes a public awareness campaign about climate change. How does this activity influence change?', 'It makes people aware of the problem and encourages them to support actions to protect the environment.', 'It stops people from caring about the environment.', 'It makes people more confused.', 'It only helps scientists.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(266, 3, 2, 'What makes it a challenge for a small pressure group to bring about a big change?', 'They always have a lot of money.', 'They might not have enough people or resources to make their voice heard by powerful decision-makers.', 'They never have good ideas.', 'It is always easy for them.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(267, 3, 2, 'Imagine your class has a big project due next week. If everyone works hard and cooperates, how will this lead to success for the project?', 'The project will be finished quickly, but not well.', 'The project will fail because too many people worked.', 'The project will likely be of high quality and completed on time.', 'Only one person will get a good grade.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(268, 3, 2, 'A student consistently finishes their homework carefully and on time, even when it\'s challenging. How does this demonstrate hard work?', 'It shows they are lucky.', 'It means their homework is always easy.', 'It shows they don\'t like to play.', 'It highlights their dedication and effort in completing tasks.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(269, 3, 2, 'You observe two students: one always tries their best, even if they fail at first, and the other gives up quickly. How do these behaviors illustrate the difference between hard work and laziness?', 'The first student is just smarter.', 'The first shows perseverance (hard work), the second shows a lack of effort (laziness).', 'They are both showing hard work.', 'They are both showing laziness.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(270, 3, 2, 'If you want to discourage laziness in your group during a task, what is an effective way to discourage it?', 'Clearly explain the importance of each person\'s contribution and the negative impact of not trying.', 'Do all the work yourself.', 'Tell people it doesn\'t matter if they don\'t work.', 'Ignore those who are not working.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(271, 3, 2, 'A young athlete practices every day, even when they are tired. How does this reflect how hard work leads to rewards and success in sports?', 'They will become tired and give up.', 'Their consistent effort often leads to improved skills and better performance in competitions.', 'They will only get injured.', 'They will become famous without practice.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(272, 3, 2, 'Imagine a situation where all the girls in a classroom are told they cannot play soccer, only the boys can. How does this identify an example of social injustice?', 'It\'s just a school rule.', 'It means girls don\'t like soccer.', 'It is unfair because it treats people differently based on their gender without a fair reason.', 'It helps everyone play better.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(273, 3, 2, 'A group of children decides to only share their toys with a few friends and exclude others. How does this demonstrate unfairness?', 'It shows they are good friends.', 'It helps them play better.', 'It means they have too many toys.', 'It excludes some children from enjoying the toys based on favoritism, which is not just.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(274, 3, 2, 'If you see someone being bullied because they are different, how could you address this unfair situation?', 'Join the bullies.', 'Speak up for the person being bullied and tell a trusted adult.', 'Ignore it and walk away.', 'Laugh at the person being bullied.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(275, 3, 2, 'Consider a community where only people from certain families get good jobs, even if others are more qualified. How does this analyze the consequences of ignoring social injustices?', 'It could lead to anger, division, and a lack of progress in the community.', 'It would make everyone feel happy.', 'It would make the community richer.', 'It means everyone gets fair chances.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(276, 3, 2, 'A story is told where a kind person helps someone who is hungry and has nothing. How does this story demonstrate a way to address an unfair situation?', 'It shows that the hungry person is lazy.', 'It exemplifies compassion and taking action to help someone in need, addressing inequality.', 'It means the kind person is very rich.', 'It only helps one person.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(277, 3, 2, 'Imagine your school needs a clean-up day. How could you apply the value of hard work to contribute to this?', 'By watching others clean.', 'By complaining about the task.', 'By actively picking up litter and helping organize the clean-up efforts.', 'By leaving early.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23');
INSERT INTO `exam_questions` (`question_id`, `subject_id`, `type`, `question`, `option1`, `option2`, `option3`, `option4`, `option5`, `feedback1`, `feedback2`, `feedback3`, `feedback4`, `feedback5`, `answer`, `marks`, `createdate`) VALUES
(278, 3, 2, 'You see a new student who seems lost and alone. How can you apply the value of justice/fairness to help them?', 'Ignore them.', 'Make fun of them.', 'Tell them to find their own way.', 'Introduce yourself, invite them to play, and make sure they feel welcome and included.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(279, 3, 2, 'A community leader always seeks advice from different groups before making decisions. How does this reflect good leadership contributing to society?', 'It shows they are weak.', 'It ensures decisions are fair and consider the needs of all community members.', 'It makes decisions slower.', 'It means they don\'t know what to do.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(280, 3, 2, 'If your local park is damaged, how might applying the value of hard work help create a better society?', 'By organizing a group to fix the damage, showing initiative and dedication.', 'By complaining about the damage.', 'By waiting for someone else to fix it.', 'By making the damage worse.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(281, 3, 2, 'A young person volunteers to help teach younger children to read after school. How does this action contribute to a better society?', 'It helps only that one young person.', 'It promotes education and helps improve the lives of others in the community.', 'It means the young person has too much free time.', 'It teaches children to read slowly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:02:23'),
(282, 3, 3, 'Your class is discussing loyalty. Which statement best evaluates why loyalty is crucial for teamwork in any setting (like a sports team or a school group)?', 'Loyalty makes teams slower.', 'Loyalty means always agreeing with the leader without thinking.', 'Loyalty builds trust and commitment, which are essential for a team to work together and succeed.', 'Loyalty is only for individuals, not teams.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(283, 3, 3, 'If you were asked to create an activity that helps students understand national loyalty, what would be the most effective activity?', 'A game where everyone competes against each other.', 'A project where students research and present on national heroes or symbols.', 'An activity where students only learn about other countries.', 'A game that teaches individual skills only.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(284, 3, 3, 'Reflect on the importance of loyalty. If you were to design a short play for your class to teach younger students about loyalty, what kind of story or characters would be most effective?', 'A story where characters frequently betray each other.', 'A story about characters who always keep their promises and support their friends, even when it\'s difficult.', 'A story about characters who only care about themselves.', 'A story with no clear message about loyalty.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(285, 3, 3, 'Your class is discussing what makes a good leader. Which statement best evaluates why listening to others is a crucial characteristic for a leader?', 'Listening makes a leader slow.', 'Listening only makes a leader confused.', 'Listening helps a leader understand different perspectives and make fair decisions that benefit the whole group.', 'Leaders don\'t need to listen, they just need to talk.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(286, 3, 3, 'If you were asked to create a new type of leadership for a school club, what core characteristic would you emphasize to ensure everyone feels included?', 'Only the leader makes all the decisions.', 'The leader only listens to popular students.', 'The leader makes sure every single person\'s idea is heard and considered.', 'The leader always does everything themselves.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(287, 3, 3, 'Reflect on choosing appropriate leadership styles. If you had to design a role-play scenario to teach younger children about being a good leader during a fire drill, what leadership style would be most appropriate to demonstrate?', 'A leader who asks for everyone\'s opinion on what to do.', 'A leader who is calm and clearly directs everyone to safety without debate.', 'A leader who waits for someone else to take charge.', 'A leader who lets children decide where to go.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(288, 3, 3, 'The text concludes that \"good leadership required more than just authority; it involved listening, fairness, and dedication to solving problems.\" Which statement best evaluates why listening is crucial for good leadership?', 'Listening makes a leader popular.', 'Listening makes decisions slower.', 'Listening ensures a leader hears all ideas, leading to better decisions for the whole community.', 'Listening is only for followers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(289, 3, 3, 'If you were asked to create a motto for a young leader inspired by the lessons in this text, what would it emphasize about leadership and community?', 'Lead alone, succeed faster.', 'Only power matters.', 'Blame others for problems.', 'Serve with honesty, unite for progress.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(290, 3, 3, 'Reflect on the idea that \"perseverance and teamwork could lead to positive change.\" If you had to design a plan to improve a small area in your own community, what core value from the text would be most essential to ensure success despite difficulties?', 'Courage and commitment in working with others to overcome obstacles.', 'Giving up when things are hard.', 'Working only by yourself.', 'Acting without empathy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(291, 3, 3, 'Your class is discussing why we need different arms of government. Which statement best evaluates why having separate arms of government helps ensure fairness and justice?', 'It makes the government complicated.', 'It\'s only for big countries.', 'It ensures that power is divided, so no one part of the government can control everything and be unfair.', 'It makes laws slowly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(292, 3, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple game for younger children to understand the roles of the three arms of government, what would be the most effective way to represent their separate duties?', 'A game where one child does all the jobs.', 'A game where everyone runs around randomly.', 'A game with no rules.', 'A game where different children have specific roles for making, enforcing, and judging rules.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(293, 3, 3, 'Think about applying your understanding of checks and balances in a practical scenario. If your class wanted to make a new rule for recess, and you wanted to ensure it was fair, what process would you design inspired by the arms of government?', 'One person decides the rule alone.', 'Everyone votes on the rule, but no one checks if it\'s fair.', 'The teacher decides the rule, and students just follow.', 'The students propose the rule, the teacher approves it, and a \"fairness committee\" reviews any disagreements.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(294, 3, 3, 'Your class is discussing how pressure groups bring about change. Which statement best evaluates why peaceful protests are often an effective method for pressure groups?', 'Peaceful protests are boring.', 'They always make people angry.', 'They only work if there are very few people.', 'They draw public attention to an issue and show leaders that many people care, without causing harm.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(295, 3, 3, 'If you were asked to create a new pressure group for your school to promote kindness, what would be your main purpose?', 'To only talk about kindness without doing anything.', 'To stop people from being kind.', 'To influence students and teachers to be kinder to each other.', 'To make kindness a secret club.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(296, 3, 3, 'Reflect on the challenges pressure groups might face. If you were to design a strategy for a pressure group to overcome being ignored by leaders, what practical step would be most effective?', 'Give up and stop trying.', 'Make sure they are silent so leaders don\'t notice them.', 'Gain more support from the community and contact leaders repeatedly with clear, organized demands.', 'Only complain to friends.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(297, 3, 3, 'Your class is reflecting on how hard work leads to rewards and success. Which statement best evaluates why personal effort is more important than just hoping for luck?', 'Luck is all you need for success.', 'Hard work is too difficult.', 'Effort often directly leads to improvement and achievements that are earned, not just given.', 'Rewards just happen naturally.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(298, 3, 3, 'If you were asked to create a school campaign to encourage hard work, what slogan would you emphasize to motivate students?', 'Relax, it\'s easy!', 'Work smart, not hard.', 'Luck is all you need.', 'Effort today, success tomorrow!', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(299, 3, 3, 'Think about distinguishing between hard work and laziness. If you had to design a peer recognition system for your class to highlight positive work habits, what type of behavior would you ask students to specifically look for and praise?', 'Students who finish tasks very quickly without caring about quality.', 'Students who only work when the teacher is watching.', 'Students who complain about their work.', 'Students who show persistence on challenging tasks and help others when needed.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(300, 3, 3, 'Your class is discussing fairness. Which statement best evaluates why fairness matters in society?', 'Fairness makes everything boring.', 'Fairness only helps the strong.', 'Fairness means everyone is exactly the same.', 'Fairness builds a more peaceful and just society where everyone has a chance to succeed.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(301, 3, 3, 'If you were asked to create a new school rule to address an unfair situation (e.g., some students always get to play first), what rule would you propose?', 'A rule that says only the fastest students can play first.', 'A rule that says only teachers can decide who plays.', 'A rule that removes the game entirely.', 'A rule that rotates turns so everyone gets an equal chance to play.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(302, 3, 3, 'Reflect on the consequences of ignoring social injustices. If you had to design a poster to encourage people to speak up against unfairness, what message would be most impactful?', 'It\'s not your problem.', 'Silence helps injustice grow.', 'Someone else will fix it.', 'Don\'t get involved.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(303, 3, 3, 'Your class is reflecting on key values like loyalty, leadership, hard work, and justice. Which statement best evaluates why these values, no matter how small your actions, can make a difference?', 'Only big actions by famous people matter.', 'Values are only for personal use.', 'It\'s too hard to make a difference.', 'Small actions add up and can inspire others, leading to bigger positive changes in the community.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(304, 3, 3, 'If you were asked to create a personal plan for contributing to a better society, what would be the most important first step?', 'To ignore everyone else\'s problems.', 'To only wish for a better society.', 'To do one small act of kindness for a neighbor or friend.', 'To wait until you are an adult to do anything.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(305, 3, 3, 'Think about how your actions can make a difference. If you had to design a school project to show how applying values contributes to a better society, what would be its main message?', 'That values are not important for society.', 'That individual actions have no impact.', 'That every person has the power to make a positive change in their community through their actions.', 'That only talking about values helps.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:04:44'),
(306, 6, 1, 'What was one of the main reasons the British came to Nigeria a long time ago?', 'To learn how to farm from the local people.', 'To help build new schools for everyone.', 'To trade for goods like palm oil and minerals.', 'To explore new types of animals.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:18:22'),
(307, 6, 1, 'Which of these describes how British rule changed Nigerian society?', 'Everyone started speaking only British languages.', 'The people began to rule themselves even more.', 'Traditional ways of life became much stronger.', 'New systems of government and education were introduced.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:18:22'),
(308, 6, 1, 'What does \"occupation\" mean when we talk about one country taking over another?', 'When one country takes control of another country, often by force.', 'A type of job someone has.', 'A peaceful visit between two countries.', 'When people from different countries decide to share land.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:18:22'),
(309, 6, 1, 'Why was British rule considered a \"big impact\" on Nigeria?', 'Because it brought new types of food.', 'Because it introduced new sports and games.', 'Because it affected how people lived, governed themselves, and traded.', 'Because it changed the weather patterns.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:18:22'),
(310, 6, 1, 'What was one of the main motivations for the British to colonize Nigeria?', 'To gain resources and markets for their industries back home.', 'To teach Nigerians how to play soccer.', 'To establish new vacation spots for British people.', 'To build big houses for everyone in Nigeria.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:18:22'),
(311, 6, 1, 'What is nationalism mainly about?', 'Feeling sad about your country.', 'Wanting your country to be the biggest.', 'A strong feeling of pride and loyalty to your own country.', 'Only caring about yourself.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:18:22'),
(312, 6, 1, 'Which of these describes Nigeria\'s goal related to independence?', 'To rule itself without control from other countries.', 'To become friends with all other countries.', 'To stop trading with other countries.', 'To change its name.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:18:22'),
