(395, 6, 2, 'Dr. Azikiwe traveled widely across Nigeria to gather support for independence. How did this action help in the nationalist movement?', 'It allowed him to see many new places.', 'It helped him connect with ordinary people and build a broad-based movement for self-rule.', 'It was a way to avoid the British.', 'It only helped people in one specific area.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(396, 6, 2, 'Awolowo introduced free primary education in the Western Region of Nigeria. How did this transform the lives of children there?', 'It made school less fun.', 'It meant only rich children could go to school.', 'It allowed many more children, including those from poor families, to get an education.', 'It stopped children from learning traditional skills.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(397, 6, 2, 'Awolowo\'s vision included building the first television station in Africa (in Nigeria). How does this analyze his contribution to Nigeria\'s development?', 'It showed he liked watching TV.', 'It demonstrated his foresight in using modern technology for information and education.', 'It made radio less popular.', 'It was just for entertainment purposes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(398, 6, 2, 'Imagine a leader with a clear vision for their country, like Awolowo. How would having a clear vision help them achieve big goals?', 'It means they don\'t need help from anyone.', 'It makes everything easy and without challenges.', 'It only works if they are very strong.', 'It provides a clear direction and helps them plan and inspire others to work towards a common future.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(399, 6, 2, 'Awolowo faced political challenges and even imprisonment. How does his reaction to these difficulties analyze the importance of perseverance?', 'It shows he was always lucky.', 'It meant he eventually gave up his vision.', 'It shows that despite setbacks, hard work and dedication can eventually lead to success.', 'It taught him to avoid all challenges.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(400, 6, 2, 'Awolowo believed in regional development, focusing on making each part of Nigeria strong. How did this contribute to Nigeria\'s overall progress?', 'It made the regions fight more.', 'It helped each region use its resources effectively, contributing to the nation\'s overall growth.', 'It meant some regions would be left behind.', 'It only benefited the capital city.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(401, 6, 2, 'Ahmadu Bello focused on \"Northernization,\" which meant having more Northern Nigerians in government and important jobs. How did this affect the region?', 'It meant fewer jobs for local people.', 'It caused more people to move away.', 'It aimed to empower Northern Nigerians to take leadership roles in their own region.', 'It stopped development in the North.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(402, 6, 2, 'Alhaji Ahmadu Bello faced the challenge of uniting many diverse ethnic groups within Northern Nigeria. How did his leadership address this complexity?', 'He ignored the different groups.', 'He only listened to one small group.', 'He forced everyone to be the same.', 'He worked to promote unity and mutual respect among them, despite differences.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(403, 6, 2, 'Bello believed that development in Northern Nigeria should be based on Islamic principles. How might this analyze his approach to leadership?', 'It meant he only cared about religion.', 'It showed he wanted to make sure development honored the traditions and values of the majority of the people in his region.', 'It meant he did not care about progress.', 'It made him dislike other cultures.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(404, 6, 2, 'Ahmadu Bello traveled widely across Northern Nigeria to meet people and understand their needs. How did this apply to his efforts in development?', 'It allowed him to connect directly with communities and plan development that met their specific needs.', 'He was just interested in sightseeing.', 'It helped him avoid his responsibilities.', 'It made him tired.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(405, 6, 2, 'Ahmadu Bello emphasized self-reliance and encouraged Northern Nigerians to take charge of their own destiny. How did this concept contribute to the region\'s progress?', 'It made people wait for others to help them.', 'It inspired local people to work hard and develop their communities without depending solely on outsiders.', 'It made people think they didn\'t need any help at all.', 'It caused conflict with neighboring regions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(406, 6, 2, 'Mallam Aminu Kano often spoke out against injustice and unfair treatment of the poor. How did this influence the political landscape?', 'It made rich people angrier.', 'It caused more people to leave the country.', 'It discouraged people from voting.', 'It raised awareness and put pressure on leaders to address the needs of ordinary citizens.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(407, 6, 2, 'Aminu Kano campaigned for basic education for all, especially for the poor. How does this analyze his contribution to social change?', 'He thought education was not important.', 'He understood that education could empower the poor to improve their lives and demand their rights.', 'He believed only rich people should be educated.', 'He only cared about religious education.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(408, 6, 2, 'Imagine a leader today who, like Aminu Kano, truly fights for the poor. What kind of actions would this leader take to influence the political landscape?', 'They would ignore the problems of the poor.', 'They would only speak to the very powerful.', 'They would champion policies that help create jobs, improve healthcare, and provide education for all.', 'They would focus on making themselves rich.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20');
INSERT INTO `exam_questions` (`question_id`, `subject_id`, `type`, `question`, `option1`, `option2`, `option3`, `option4`, `option5`, `feedback1`, `feedback2`, `feedback3`, `feedback4`, `feedback5`, `answer`, `marks`, `createdate`) VALUES
(409, 6, 2, 'Aminu Kano used methods like grassroots organizing (working directly with ordinary people) to build his political movement. How does this differ from leaders who only focus on appealing to the elite?', 'It meant he only spoke to a few people.', 'It was a slower way to achieve goals.', 'It was a way to avoid talking to anyone.', 'It helped empower the common people and give them a direct voice in politics.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(410, 6, 2, 'Mallam Aminu Kano believed that leaders should be servants of the people, especially the common person. How does this value influence his approach to leadership?', 'It made him focus only on himself.', 'It guided him to prioritize the welfare and needs of the ordinary citizens, rather than personal power.', 'It meant he did not make any decisions.', 'It made him want to be king.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(411, 6, 2, 'Imagine you were a child in Nigeria on October 1, 1960. How might gaining independence change your life and the lives of your family?', 'Life would stay exactly the same as before.', 'You would suddenly become very rich.', 'You would have to move to a new country.', 'Nigerians would now make their own laws and decisions about their country\'s future.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(412, 6, 2, 'The Nigerian national flag was raised for the first time on Independence Day. How did this event symbolize the meaning of independence?', 'It meant a new type of cloth was invented.', 'It showed Nigeria was now a self-governing nation, with its own identity.', 'It was just a colorful decoration.', 'It meant people could fly kites.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(413, 6, 2, 'Nigeria\'s independence was the result of many years of struggle by nationalists. How does this analyze the importance of perseverance in achieving freedom?', 'It shows that freedom is easy to get.', 'It means leaders don\'t need to work hard.', 'It suggests that long and hard work, despite challenges, is often needed to achieve big goals like national freedom.', 'It proved that only one person can make a difference.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(414, 6, 2, 'After independence, Nigeria\'s leaders had the power to make decisions about education, healthcare, and infrastructure. How did this differ from before independence?', 'Foreign rulers made all the major decisions before independence.', 'Education and healthcare were not important before.', 'There were no laws before independence.', 'Nigerians always had control over these things.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(415, 6, 2, 'The emotional impact of independence was huge for many Nigerians. How might people have expressed their feelings on that day?', 'By being very quiet and sad.', 'By celebrating with parades, music, and joyful gatherings.', 'By moving to other countries.', 'By hiding inside their homes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(416, 6, 2, 'Traditional religions often involve storytelling about gods, spirits, and heroes. How does this reflect Nigeria\'s cultural heritage?', 'It shows that Nigerians don\'t like reading books.', 'It means people are scared of spirits.', 'These stories pass down ancient wisdom, history, and values from generation to generation.', 'It helps people remember only recent events.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(417, 6, 2, 'Many traditional festivals are linked to the planting and harvesting of crops. How does this show the importance of these religions to community survival?', 'It means people only celebrated when they had food.', 'It made farming harder.', 'It meant people didn\'t need to work hard.', 'It highlights how traditional beliefs were connected to daily life and ensured success in farming for the community.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(418, 6, 2, 'The masquerade tradition is important in some Nigerian traditional religions. How can you analyze the role of masquerades in cultural preservation?', 'They are just costumes for parties.', 'They represent ancestral spirits and play a role in teaching history and social order.', 'They are used to scare children.', 'They are for tourists only.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(419, 6, 2, 'If a community practices a traditional religion where respecting elders is a core value. How might this influence daily life in that community?', 'People would show great respect and care for their elders.', 'Children would ignore their grandparents.', 'People would often be rude to older people.', 'Only young people would make decisions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(420, 6, 2, 'Traditional religions often have specific sacred places like groves or rivers. How does treating these places as sacred contribute to cultural preservation?', 'It means people cannot visit these places.', 'It helps protect natural spaces and connects people to their historical and spiritual roots.', 'It makes the places dangerous.', 'It means new buildings cannot be built there.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(421, 6, 2, 'Traders from North Africa brought goods and Islamic teachings to Nigeria. How did their travels contribute to the spread of Islam?', 'They only sold goods.', 'They avoided talking about religion.', 'They forced people to become Muslims.', 'They shared their faith and customs with the people they traded with.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(422, 6, 2, 'The establishment of the Sokoto Caliphate by Usman Dan Fodio led to widespread adoption of Islam. How did this influence daily life for many people in Northern Nigeria?', 'People stopped farming.', 'Islamic laws and education became central to their society and governance.', 'Everyone started speaking Arabic.', 'People stopped believing in any religion.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(423, 6, 2, 'Islamic scholars played an important role by teaching and writing. How did their efforts contribute to Islam\'s spread?', 'They only taught in secret.', 'They made people afraid of new ideas.', 'They educated people about Islamic principles and the Arabic language, spreading knowledge of the religion.', 'They focused only on science.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(424, 6, 2, 'Islam emphasizes community and brotherhood among believers. How might this feature have helped its spread in Nigeria?', 'It fostered a sense of belonging and unity among diverse groups who adopted the faith.', 'It made people want to fight each other.', 'It encouraged people to stay separate from others.', 'It made people focus only on their own families.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(425, 6, 2, 'The Alfas and other Islamic teachers lived among the people. How did this approach help in the acceptance of Islam?', 'It made them seem distant and powerful.', 'It allowed them to teach and influence people directly through their daily lives and examples.', 'It meant they only taught a few students.', 'It forced people to listen to them.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(426, 6, 2, 'Missionaries often established schools when they introduced Christianity. How did these schools influence Nigerian society?', 'They only taught about religion.', 'They only taught farming skills.', 'They made people forget their own languages.', 'They provided Western education, which changed how many Nigerians learned and thought.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(427, 6, 2, 'Christianity brought new ideas about healthcare and medicine. How did this affect health practices in Nigeria?', 'People stopped caring about health.', 'Missionaries built hospitals and introduced Western medical care, leading to new health approaches.', 'Everyone became a doctor.', 'People only relied on traditional healing methods.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(428, 6, 2, 'The spread of Christianity sometimes led to conflicts with traditional beliefs. How can you analyze this challenge?', 'Everyone immediately accepted the new religion.', 'It meant that there was no change.', 'It created tension as new religious practices and values sometimes clashed with existing cultural norms.', 'It made all religions become the same.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(429, 6, 2, 'Christian hymns and songs were translated into Nigerian languages. How did this contribute to the growth of Christianity?', 'It helped local people understand and connect with the faith in their own language.', 'It made the songs harder to understand.', 'It made the songs less popular.', 'It stopped people from singing traditional songs.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(430, 6, 2, 'Christian missionaries introduced new forms of art, music, and architecture. How did this influence Nigeria\'s cultural landscape?', 'It made all Nigerian art look the same.', 'It added new styles and expressions to the rich existing cultural traditions.', 'It stopped people from creating any art.', 'It only affected people in big cities.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(431, 6, 2, 'A traditional weaver creates clothes using old methods. How does this occupation contribute to cultural preservation?', 'It helps them learn new languages.', 'It makes the clothes more expensive.', 'It means they don\'t use modern machines.', 'It keeps alive traditional skills, designs, and stories passed down through generations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(432, 6, 2, 'A traditional blacksmith makes tools for farmers. How does this occupation contribute to the community\'s survival?', 'It helps farmers get strong muscles.', 'It provides essential tools that enable farming and other vital community activities.', 'It makes noise in the village.', 'It means fewer tools are needed.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(433, 6, 2, 'Modern factories can produce goods faster and cheaper than traditional artisans. How does this create a challenge for traditional occupations?', 'It makes traditional goods more popular.', 'It encourages more people to learn traditional skills.', 'Traditional artisans might struggle to compete and sell their handmade goods.', 'It means traditional artisans can work less.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(434, 6, 2, 'If a community relies on traditional fishing, but pollution threatens the fish, how does this create an ethical consideration?', 'It raises questions about how to protect both the environment and the livelihoods of the traditional fishermen.', 'It means the fish will become bigger.', 'It makes fishing easier.', 'It means new types of fish will appear.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(435, 6, 2, 'Reflect on how modernization affects traditional trades. If your community\'s traditional potters are losing customers to plastic containers, what might be a way to balance tradition with innovation?', 'Tell the potters to stop making pots.', 'Encourage potters to create new, modern designs or find new uses for their traditional pots, while keeping their skills alive.', 'Ban all plastic containers.', 'Ask people to only use old pots.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(436, 6, 2, 'A Hausa leatherworker makes beautiful dyed leather goods, while a Yoruba farmer grows crops. How do these jobs show differences in occupations based on environment?', 'They are exactly the same job.', 'One needs land, the other needs animals.', 'One is modern, the other is old.', 'The availability of resources in their regions often shaped the types of traditional jobs.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(437, 6, 2, 'The Igbo people are known for blacksmithing, creating tools and art from metal. How does this reflect a specialized skill important to their cultural heritage?', 'It means they don\'t need tools.', 'It shows a unique craft that was passed down and used for practical and ceremonial purposes.', 'It means they always traded for metal.', 'It was just a hobby.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(438, 6, 2, 'A Yoruba market trader sells goods, while a Hausa nomadic pastoralist moves with livestock. How do these occupations contrast in terms of lifestyle?', 'Both involve staying in one place.', 'Both involve farming.', 'One involves travel, the other a settled life focused on trade.', 'One is easy, the other is hard.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(439, 6, 2, 'Traditional occupations often have specific tools or techniques. How does learning about these tools help us understand the occupations better?', 'It shows how people solved problems and used local materials in the past.', 'It helps us know where to buy new tools.', 'It means we have to make the tools ourselves.', 'It helps us know which tools are the oldest.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(440, 6, 2, 'If a modern factory starts making clothes very cheaply, how might this impact a traditional weaver (like a Yoruba adire cloth maker)?', 'It would make traditional clothes more expensive.', 'It could make it harder for the weaver to sell their handmade, often more expensive, products.', 'It would help the weaver get more customers.', 'It would mean the weaver can work faster.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(441, 6, 2, 'Imagine a traditional Nigerian storyteller. How might modern changes like television and smartphones impact their occupation?', 'It would make their stories more popular.', 'It would help them tell stories faster.', 'It might make it harder for them to find an audience as people consume stories differently.', 'It would stop people from talking.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(442, 6, 2, 'A modern baker uses an electric oven, while a traditional baker uses a clay oven heated by firewood. How do these methods contrast in terms of technology?', 'Both use very new technology.', 'Both use the same type of oven.', 'One is better than the other in all ways.', 'One uses electricity, the other uses natural fire and traditional materials.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(443, 6, 2, 'If a traditional occupation (like farming with hand tools) is facing challenges from large-scale mechanized farming, how could the community analyze how to sustain the traditional method?', 'By ignoring the problem.', 'By telling everyone to stop farming.', 'By forcing everyone to farm the old way.', 'By looking for ways to adapt, perhaps focusing on niche markets or combining traditional methods with small modern improvements.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(444, 6, 2, 'Some traditional crafts use natural materials found in the environment. How might environmental changes (like deforestation) impact these occupations?', 'It would make the materials grow faster.', 'It would make the materials more available.', 'It could lead to a shortage of raw materials, threatening the craft.', 'It would make the craft easier.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(445, 6, 2, 'Consider a traditional occupation that uses skills passed down through families, but fewer young people are learning it. How does this pose a challenge for its future?', 'It means the skill will become more popular.', 'It means the job is no longer important.', 'It will make the job easier to learn.', 'It risks the traditional knowledge and skills being lost when the older generation is no longer able to teach.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:29:20'),
(446, 6, 3, 'If you were a Nigerian child living during British colonial rule, what would be the most important ethical issue you might notice or experience?', 'That British food was different from Nigerian food.', 'That British clothing styles were popular.', 'That the British often made decisions that benefited themselves more than the Nigerian people.', 'That the British spoke a different language.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(447, 6, 3, 'Imagine you are asked to create a short play for your class showing the arrival of the British in Nigeria. To highlight a moral dilemma, which scene would be most effective?', 'A scene where everyone happily shares gifts.', 'A scene where British and Nigerian children play games together.', 'A scene where everyone learns a new song.', 'A scene where British soldiers demand land from local leaders, who feel pressured to agree.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(448, 6, 3, 'You are evaluating different perspectives on British rule. One person says it brought \"modern development,\" another says it brought \"exploitation.\" Which perspective best emphasizes the moral and ethical issues involved?', 'The \"exploitation\" perspective, because it highlights unfair treatment and taking of resources.', 'The \"modern development\" perspective, because new things are always good.', 'Both perspectives equally, as they are just different words.', 'Neither, because history is only about facts, not opinions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(449, 6, 3, 'Your class is debating whether nationalism always leads to good outcomes. Which statement best evaluates a moral dilemma often associated with nationalist movements?', '\"Nationalism always brings peace and happiness.\"', '\"Nationalism can sometimes lead to conflict or unfair treatment if one group\'s pride comes at the expense of others.\"', '\"Nationalism means everyone in the country is exactly the same.\"', '\"Nationalism is only about singing national songs.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(450, 6, 3, 'If you were to create a new national symbol for Nigeria that reflects the spirit of nationalism during the independence movement, what would it represent?', 'A symbol of foreign power controlling Nigeria.', 'A symbol of division and disagreement.', 'A symbol of the many different groups of people living in Nigeria, but fighting for independence.', 'A symbol of only one specific leader.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(451, 6, 3, 'Reflect on how nationalism influences contemporary issues in Nigeria. If you were to advise a young Nigerian leader today, what personal safety strategy could be created based on the lessons of nationalism to unite people?', 'Focus on dividing people by their differences.', 'Emphasize common goals and shared identity for the good of the nation, learning from past unity.', 'Ignore the country\'s history of nationalism.', 'Only listen to people from one part of the country.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(452, 6, 3, 'Your class is discussing the moral lessons from Herbert Macaulays life. Which of these is the most important lesson about standing up for what is right?', 'It\'s always easy to fight for justice.', 'You should only fight for your own rights.', 'It often requires courage and perseverance, even when facing difficulties.', 'Others will always fight for you.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(453, 6, 3, 'If you were to create a monument in honor of Herbert Macaulay, what key message about his contribution to Nigeria\'s independence would it convey?', 'That he was good at writing.', 'That he liked to travel.', 'That he was a very old man.', 'That he was the brave pioneer who ignited Nigeria\'s quest for self-rule.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(454, 6, 3, 'Think about how Macaulay\'s actions shaped Nigeria\'s path to independence. If you could design a modern campaign inspired by his life to address a current issue in Nigeria (like education or health), what core value from his life would you emphasize for success?', 'Passionate dedication to the nation\'s welfare and a willingness to challenge injustice.', 'Being quiet and not speaking up.', 'Selfishness and individual gain.', 'Laziness and avoiding work.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(455, 6, 3, 'Your class is reflecting on Dr. Azikiwe\'s life. Which statement best evaluates the importance of his dedication to education for young Nigerians today?', '\"Education was just a hobby for him.\"', '\"Education is only for getting good jobs.\"', '\"His life shows that education is a powerful tool for personal growth and for helping to build a better nation.\"', '\"Only political leaders need a good education.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(456, 6, 3, 'If you were asked to create a mural celebrating Azikiwe\'s fight for independence, what key idea about overcoming challenges would you include?', 'Show him always winning without any struggle.', 'Show him giving up when things get tough.', 'Show him making friends with everyone.', 'Show him facing difficulties, but always rising up and continuing his efforts.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(457, 6, 3, 'Reflect on the value of perseverance from Azikiwe\'s life. If you had to design a school program to teach this value, what activity would be most effective for 9-10 year olds?', 'A fun game that requires trying many times to succeed.', 'A lesson where students only read about perseverance.', 'An activity where giving up early is rewarded.', 'A quiet activity with no challenges.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(458, 6, 3, 'Your class is reflecting on Chief Awolowo\'s principle of \"free education for all.\" Which statement best evaluates why this was a crucial vision for Nigeria\'s long-term development?', '\"It was a good idea, but not really necessary.\"', '\"It only helped children who already liked school.\"', '\"It was crucial because an educated population is essential for a nation\'s progress and future.\"', '\"It only benefited people in his specific region.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(459, 6, 3, 'If you were asked to create a motto inspired by Chief Awolowo\'s life about having a clear vision, what would it emphasize?', '\"Look back, not forward.\"', '\"See the future, then work tirelessly to build it.\"', '\"Only dream, never act.\"', '\"Let others decide your path.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(460, 6, 3, 'Imagine you are a young leader today, inspired by Awolowo\'s hard work. If you were to design a project to improve your community, what is the most important lesson from Awolowo\'s life you would apply to ensure its success?', 'That hard work is only for leaders.', 'That projects don\'t need a clear plan.', 'The importance of having a clear goal and working diligently to achieve it, even when it\'s tough.', 'That success happens overnight.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(461, 6, 3, 'Your class is discussing the complexities of Ahmadu Bellos leadership. Which statement best evaluates a challenge he faced when trying to unite Northern Nigeria?', '\"He only had to deal with friendly neighbors.\"', '\"Everyone in Northern Nigeria agreed with him all the time.\"', '\"He had to manage different ethnic and religious groups with varied interests and traditions.\"', '\"His biggest challenge was building roads.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(462, 6, 3, 'If you were asked to create a short motto for young people inspired by Ahmadu Bellos focus on education and development for his community, what would it emphasize?', '\"Education is only for leaders.\"', '\"Learning is less important than playing.\"', '\"Only look out for yourself.\"', '\"Developing yourself helps your community grow.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(463, 6, 3, 'Reflect on how Ahmadu Bello\'s leadership can inspire contributions to the community. If you were to design a school project based on his principles, which project idea would best reflect his focus on local development and education?', 'A project to only learn about foreign countries.', 'A project to ignore local problems.', 'A project that only benefits one person.', 'A project to clean up the school grounds and teach younger students about recycling.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(464, 6, 3, 'Your class is reflecting on Mallam Aminu Kano\'s dedication to justice. Which statement best evaluates the moral lesson from his life about standing up for the disadvantaged?', '\"It\'s easy to defend the poor if you are famous.\"', '\"Helping the poor is not a leader\'s job.\"', '\"True leadership involves courageously advocating for the rights and dignity of those who are most vulnerable.\"', '\"You should only help people who are like you.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(465, 6, 3, 'If you were asked to create a short motto to inspire young Nigerians to contribute to their community, based on Aminu Kano\'s values, what would it emphasize?', '\"Only the rich matter.\"', '\"Your voice can change things for the poor.\"', '\"Stay quiet, let others lead.\"', '\"Individual wealth is the only goal.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(466, 6, 3, 'Imagine you need to design a small community project that reflects Mallam Aminu Kano\'s fight for the poor. Which project idea would be the most effective and why?', 'A project to build a luxurious house for one rich person.', 'A project to organize a food drive for families in need.', 'A project to start a new fashion brand.', 'A project that only benefits your own family.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(467, 6, 3, 'Your class is reflecting on Nigeria\'s independence. Which statement best evaluates why it was historically significant for the entire continent of Africa?', '\"It was just one small country getting its freedom.\"', '\"It showed that African countries could not rule themselves.\"', '\"It only mattered to people living in Nigeria.\"', '\"Nigeria\'s independence was a major step towards self-governance for many African nations, inspiring others.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(468, 6, 3, 'If you were asked to create a new national slogan for Nigeria, reflecting the spirit of independence and national unity, what would it emphasize?', '\"Divided we stand.\"', '\"My tribe first.\"', '\"One nation, one dream, together we build.\"', '\"Only the past matters.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(469, 6, 3, 'Imagine you are celebrating Independence Day. What personal connection can you make to this historical event in your own life today, and how might you express it?', 'By ignoring the day completely.', 'By only thinking about yourself.', 'By wishing another country still ruled Nigeria.', 'By understanding that you have freedom and opportunities because of it, and perhaps celebrating with pride.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(470, 6, 3, 'Your class is discussing the significance of traditional religions. Which statement best evaluates their contribution to Nigeria\'s rich cultural diversity?', '\"Traditional religions are all the same, so they don\'t add much diversity.\"', '\"They are only important to a few people now.\"', '\"They are a fundamental part of Nigeria\'s varied cultural tapestry, offering unique beliefs, rituals, and worldviews.\"', '\"They make Nigeria less modern.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(471, 6, 3, 'If you were to create a simple storytelling session about a traditional Nigerian festival, what aspect would be most important to highlight to appreciate cultural heritage?', 'How much food was eaten.', 'How long the festival lasted.', 'The clothes people wore only.', 'The historical meaning and the community activities that bring people together.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(472, 6, 3, 'Reflect on the importance of appreciating diverse cultural heritage. If you were to design a school display about Nigerian traditional religions, what would be your goal, and what would be the most effective way to show their beauty?', 'To show that these religions are old and not relevant today.', 'To show only the funny parts.', 'To highlight the unique stories, art, music, and community values, showing their richness.', 'To compare them negatively to other religions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(473, 6, 3, 'Your class is reflecting on the impact of Islam on Nigerian culture and society. Which statement best evaluates a significant cultural change brought by Islam?', '\"Islam only brought new foods.\"', '\"It had no impact on Nigerian culture.\"', '\"It influenced art, architecture, legal systems, and education, adding new layers to Nigerian culture.\"', '\"It made everyone dress the same.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(474, 6, 3, 'If you were to create a short story about the spread of Islam in Nigeria, what key factor would you emphasize as making it successful?', 'Only strong armies.', 'Magical powers.', 'People being forced to convert.', 'The peaceful interactions through trade and the teachings of scholars.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(475, 6, 3, 'Imagine you are teaching about the historical journey of Islam in Nigeria. What visual aid would you design to effectively show how it became a major religion?', 'A map showing only modern cities.', 'A picture of a single mosque.', 'A list of all Islamic holidays.', 'A timeline showing the major events of its spread and key figures.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(476, 6, 3, 'Your class is reflecting on the introduction of Christianity in Nigeria. Which statement best evaluates its overall impact on social development?', '\"It only brought religious change.\"', '\"It had no lasting effect on society.\"', '\"It led to major advancements in education and healthcare, significantly impacting social development.\"', '\"It only benefited foreign people.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(477, 6, 3, 'If you were asked to create a timeline showing the growth of Christianity in Nigeria, what type of event would be most important to include to show its influence?', 'Dates of major sporting events.', 'The invention of new foods.', 'The discovery of gold mines.', 'The establishment of mission schools and hospitals.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(478, 6, 3, 'Reflect on how communities respond to new ideas. If you were to design a project to help people in a community learn about a new idea (like recycling), what lesson from the spread of Christianity would be most useful?', 'That new ideas are always immediately accepted.', 'The importance of dedicated teachers (like missionaries) and adapting the message to local understanding.', 'That only powerful people can introduce new ideas.', 'That people should be forced to accept new ideas.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(479, 6, 3, 'Your class is evaluating the importance of traditional occupations. Which statement best evaluates why they are crucial for a community\'s survival and identity?', '\"They are just old jobs that people did in the past.\"', '\"They are only for making money.\"', '\"They provide essential goods and services, preserve unique cultural skills, and pass down heritage from ancestors.\"', '\"They slow down modern progress.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(480, 6, 3, 'If you were asked to create a \"Living History\" fair in your locality to celebrate traditional occupations, what activity would be the most effective to show their importance?', 'Only showing old photos of the occupations.', 'Having modern factory workers demonstrate their jobs.', 'Giving a long speech about history.', 'Allowing visitors to try out simple tasks with traditional tools, like grinding grain or weaving a small pattern.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(481, 6, 3, 'Think about balancing tradition with innovation. If you had to design a way to help a traditional occupation (like basket weaving) survive today, what new idea would you introduce that respects tradition?', 'Stop making baskets and make something completely new.', 'Use new plastic materials instead of traditional ones.', 'Create new, modern designs for baskets or sell them online, while still using traditional weaving techniques.', 'Only sell baskets to people in your village.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(482, 6, 3, 'Your class is exploring the balance between tradition and modernity. Which statement best evaluates why it\'s important for Nigeria to preserve its traditional occupations while embracing some modern changes?', '\"Traditional jobs are just for museums; modern jobs are all that matter.\"', '\"Only old ways are good, new ways are bad.\"', '\"It helps maintain cultural identity and unique skills while allowing for progress and economic growth.\"', '\"It makes Nigeria seem less developed.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(483, 6, 3, 'If you were asked to create a new project to help a traditional occupation thrive in modern Nigeria (e.g., traditional textile dyeing), what creative approach would you suggest to keep it relevant?', 'Stop making traditional dyes and only use factory-made ones.', 'Only make very old designs that nobody wears anymore.', 'Teach the traditional dyeing techniques in schools to new generations and help artisans sell their unique products globally online.', 'Tell people to only buy imported textiles.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(484, 6, 3, 'You are developing critical thinking skills to balance tradition with innovation. If a traditional occupation relies heavily on an outdated tool, what is the best way to approach \"innovation\" that respects \"tradition\"?', 'Completely abandon the old tool and process for something entirely new.', 'Find a way to slightly improve the old tool or process to make it more efficient, without losing its traditional essence.', 'Force people to only use the outdated tool, no matter how hard it is.', 'Tell people that the old tool is useless.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 08:34:18'),
(485, 9, 1, 'What is personal security mainly about?', 'Knowing how to keep yourself safe and protected.', 'Having many friends to play with.', 'Learning new magic tricks.', 'Only talking to grown-ups you know.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(486, 9, 1, 'Which of these is an important reason why personal security matters?', 'So you can get more toys.', 'It helps you stay healthy and happy.', 'So you don\'t have to go to school.', 'It helps you learn to read faster.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(487, 9, 1, 'Which of these actions helps keep you personally secure?', 'Telling your secrets to anyone who asks.', 'Walking home alone in the dark.', 'Keeping your family informed about where you are.', 'Playing with matches.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(488, 9, 1, 'Why is making safe choices crucial for your personal security?', 'Because it makes you popular.', 'So you can play video games all day.', 'Because adults will give you candy.', 'Because it helps you avoid dangers and stay out of harm\'s way.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(489, 9, 1, 'What does \"personal security\" mean for a child your age?', 'Knowing how to protect your body and privacy.', 'It means having a personal bodyguard.', 'It means keeping all your feelings a secret.', 'It means always having your parents with you.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(490, 9, 1, 'Who is a \"stranger\"?', 'Anyone you have not met before and do not know well.', 'Someone you know from school.', 'Your relatives.', 'Your neighbors.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(491, 9, 1, 'Why is it important to be cautious around strangers?', 'Because they might give you too much candy.', 'Because you don\'t know their intentions and they might not be safe.', 'Because they might ask you for directions.', 'Because they might be lost.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(492, 9, 1, 'What does the safety measure \"Run, Yell, Tell\" mean?', 'Run as fast as you can, yell at your friends, tell a story.', 'Run around the block, yell for your pet, tell them goodbye.', 'Run away, yell loudly for help, and tell a trusted adult what happened.', 'Run to the store, yell for ice cream, tell your parents later.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(493, 9, 1, 'Which of these is a good safety rule about talking to strangers?', 'Never go anywhere with a stranger or take things from them without a trusted adult\'s permission.', 'It\'s okay to talk to a stranger if they smile at you.', 'You can tell a stranger your address if they ask nicely.', 'Always try to make new friends with strangers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(494, 9, 1, 'What should you do if a stranger tries to grab you?', 'Kick, scream, and make a lot of noise to get attention.', 'Stand still and be quiet.', 'Try to reason with them.', 'Close your eyes and hope they go away.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(495, 9, 1, 'Which of these is an example of an unsafe food?', 'Food that has mold growing on it.', 'Fresh fruit and vegetables.', 'Cooked chicken.', 'A sandwich you just made.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(496, 9, 1, 'Why is it important to check the expiry date on food and medicine?', 'To see if it\'s your birthday.', 'To know if it\'s still safe to eat or use.', 'To know who made it.', 'To see how much it cost.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(497, 9, 1, 'What is a fake drug?', 'A type of candy that looks like medicine.', 'Real medicine that helps you feel better.', 'Medicine that doesn\'t work or can harm you because it\'s not made correctly.', 'Vitamins you take every day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(498, 9, 1, 'Where is the best place to buy food and products to ensure they are safe?', 'From a stranger selling things on the street.', 'From a trusted store or shop.', 'From a friend who found it somewhere.', 'From a box left outside a house.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(499, 9, 1, 'What should you look for on a product\'s label to know if it\'s safe?', 'Information about what\'s inside, warnings, and how to use it safely.', 'Only the color of the package.', 'Pictures of animals.', 'How shiny the package is.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(500, 9, 1, 'What is one of a child\'s main duties regarding their personal security?', 'To always play alone.', 'To never talk to anyone.', 'To hide from adults.', 'To understand and follow safety rules.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(501, 9, 1, 'Which of these is an example of a safe behavior?', 'Asking a trusted adult for help when you\'re lost.', 'Running into the street without looking.', 'Riding your bike without a helmet.', 'Climbing on unstable structures.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(502, 9, 1, 'What does it mean to be \"responsible\" for your own safety?', 'It means someone else is always in charge of keeping you safe.', 'It means you don\'t have to listen to adults.', 'It means you help make choices and take actions to keep yourself safe.', 'It means you can do whatever you want.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(503, 9, 1, 'Why is it important to tell a trusted adult if you feel unsafe?', 'Because they can help you and make the situation safe.', 'Because they will get angry at you.', 'Because it\'s fun to tell secrets.', 'Because you want attention.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(504, 9, 1, 'Which of these is a safe behavior when using the internet?', 'Giving out your home address to online friends.', 'Asking a trusted adult before visiting new websites or sharing information.', 'Sharing your full name and school name with strangers online.', 'Clicking on pop-up ads without asking.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(505, 9, 1, 'What is a main responsibility a child has for their own personal security?', 'Making sure their toys are put away.', 'Always winning at games.', 'Learning about dangers and how to avoid them.', 'Keeping their room clean.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(506, 9, 1, 'Which of these describes an unsafe behavior?', 'Using crosswalks to cross the street.', 'Washing your hands before eating.', 'Wearing a seatbelt in a car.', 'Playing with sharp objects without adult supervision.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(507, 9, 1, 'Why is it important to tell a trusted adult about an uncomfortable situation?', 'Because trusted adults can help you solve problems and stay safe.', 'Because they will give you a reward.', 'Because it makes you feel smarter.', 'Because they might tell your friends.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(508, 9, 1, 'What does \"demonstrate responsibility\" mean in terms of safety?', 'Just knowing the rules.', 'Showing through your actions that you understand and follow safety rules.', 'Letting others make all the safety choices.', 'Always being the leader.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(509, 9, 1, 'What is a good way to identify if a situation is potentially unsafe?', 'If it makes you feel uncomfortable, scared, or if a trusted adult has told you it\'s risky.', 'If it looks exciting and fun.', 'If all your friends are doing it.', 'If it\'s a new game you\'ve never played.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(510, 9, 1, 'What is a \"role model\" in the context of personal security?', 'Someone who acts in movies.', 'Someone you look up to and learn good safety habits from.', 'A person who gives you gifts.', 'A friend who plays games with you.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(511, 9, 1, 'Why is it important to learn from role models in personal security?', 'Because they can show you how to be safe and make good choices.', 'Because they are famous.', 'Because they have a lot of money.', 'Because they always tell jokes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(512, 9, 1, 'Which of these describes a personal security tip you might learn from a role model?', 'How to tie your shoelaces.', 'How to build a fort.', 'Always checking in with a trusted adult before going somewhere new.', 'What to eat for breakfast.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(513, 9, 1, 'What does \"cultural influences on safety practices\" mean?', 'How different countries have different types of food.', 'How family traditions or community beliefs can affect how people stay safe.', 'How different languages are spoken.', 'How people dress in different places.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(514, 9, 1, 'What is \"problem-solving\" in personal security?', 'Thinking carefully to find the best way to handle a tricky or unsafe situation.', 'Finding answers to math questions.', 'Finishing a puzzle quickly.', 'Deciding what game to play next.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:09:54'),
(515, 9, 2, 'Imagine you are walking home from school and a car you don\'t know pulls up and offers you a ride. What is the safest thing to do?', 'Politely say \"no, thank you\" and keep walking quickly to a safe place.', 'Jump in quickly because you\'re tired.', 'Ask them if they have candy.', 'Run away as fast as you can without looking back.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(516, 9, 2, 'Your friend wants to explore an old, empty building in your neighborhood. You remember learning about personal security. Which question should you ask yourself before going?', 'Is there ice cream inside?', 'Will my parents find out later.', 'Is this a place where I could get hurt or be unsafe?', 'Is my friend excited to go?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(517, 9, 2, 'You are playing at the park, and a stranger approaches you, offering you a puppy if you come with them. How can you analyze this situation to make a safe choice?', 'Think about how cute the puppy must be.', 'Ask your friend if they also want a puppy.', 'Wonder if your parents would let you have a puppy.', 'Realize that adults who offer gifts and ask you to go with them are usually not safe.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(518, 9, 2, 'Which of these scenarios best shows someone applying good personal security?', 'Always telling a trusted adult where they are going.', 'Sharing their home address with a new online friend.', 'Opening the door to anyone who knocks when they are home alone.', 'Not wearing a helmet when riding a bike.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(519, 9, 2, 'A TV show character you like often takes risks and doesn\'t tell anyone where they are going. Why is this not a good example of personal security to follow in real life?', 'Because it\'s boring.', 'Because not telling someone where you are going makes it harder for trusted adults to help you if needed.', 'Because the character might get lost.', 'Because it\'s just a TV show.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(520, 9, 2, 'You are walking home from school and a car you don\'t recognize pulls up beside you. The driver, a stranger, says, \"Your mom sent me to pick you up. Hop in!\" What should you do?', 'Get in the car because they mentioned your mom.', 'Immediately run to the nearest safe place or trusted adult, because your parents would never send someone you don\'t know.', 'Ask them for your mom\'s phone number.', 'Stand there and wait for your real mom.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(521, 9, 2, 'Your parents have a special password for anyone picking you up. A stranger comes to pick you up and doesn\'t know the password. How does knowing this help you analyze the situation?', 'It means they must be a friend of your parents.', 'It means you should teach them the password.', 'It tells you they are NOT the person your parents sent, and you should not go with them.', 'It means your parents forgot to tell them the password.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(522, 9, 2, 'You are playing alone in your front yard. A stranger asks you for directions to a house far away. What is the safest way to handle this?', 'Walk with them to show them the way.', 'Try to point them in the right direction from where you are.', 'Invite them into your house to look at a map.', 'Tell them you don\'t know and go inside to tell a trusted adult.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(523, 9, 2, 'Which scenario shows a child applying safety measures when encountering a stranger?', 'A child keeps walking away quickly and loudly says \"No!\" when a stranger tries to talk to them.', 'A child accepts a toy from a person they don\'t know at the park.', 'A child shares personal information with a new person they met online.', 'A child goes to look at a lost pet with a stranger.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(524, 9, 2, 'You see a younger child talking to a stranger who is offering them candy. How can you analyze this situation to help the younger child?', 'You should go and ask the stranger for candy too.', 'You should tell the younger child to stop talking to the stranger and find a trusted adult immediately.', 'You should watch from afar to see what happens.', 'You should tell the stranger that candy is bad for teeth.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29');
INSERT INTO `exam_questions` (`question_id`, `subject_id`, `type`, `question`, `option1`, `option2`, `option3`, `option4`, `option5`, `feedback1`, `feedback2`, `feedback3`, `feedback4`, `feedback5`, `answer`, `marks`, `createdate`) VALUES
(525, 9, 2, 'Your younger sibling finds an unlabelled bottle of liquid under the sink and wants to drink it. What should you do based on what you\'ve learned about chemicals?', 'Stop them immediately and tell a trusted adult, because unlabelled liquids can be dangerous chemicals.', 'Let them taste a little to see what it is.', 'Tell them it\'s just water.', 'Smell it to figure out what it is.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(526, 9, 2, 'You\'re at the grocery store with an adult, and you see a box of cookies with a \"Best Before\" date that was last year. How should you apply your knowledge to this situation?', 'Put it in the shopping cart anyway, because it might still be good.', 'Point it out to the adult and suggest choosing a box with a current or future date.', 'Open the box to smell the cookies.', 'Buy it and try to eat it quickly before it gets worse.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(527, 9, 2, 'Your friend has a headache, and their older cousin gives them a pill from a small plastic bag, saying \"It will make you feel better.\" How should your friend analyze this situation to make an informed choice?', 'Take the pill because their cousin said it would help.', 'Just take half of the pill.', 'Realize that taking medicine not given by a parent or doctor, especially from an unmarked bag, is unsafe and should be refused.', 'Ask their cousin what flavor the pill is.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(528, 9, 2, 'Which of these situations shows someone applying critical thinking about product safety?', 'Reading reviews and checking for safety certifications before buying an electronic device.', 'Buying the cheapest toy without checking its quality or safety symbols.', 'Eating a snack even if it smells strange.', 'Using a cleaning product without reading the instructions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(529, 9, 2, 'You see an advertisement online for a new energy drink that claims to make you super strong, but it has a very strange-looking label and no clear ingredients list. How should you analyze this advertisement?', 'Believe the advertisement because it looks cool.', 'Be very suspicious because reliable products have clear labels and ingredients, and this might be an unsafe chemical.', 'Ask your parents to buy it for you.', 'Share the advertisement with all your friends.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(530, 9, 2, 'You see a group of older kids playing with matches in the park. What is your responsibility in this situation?', 'Stay away from them and tell a trusted adult immediately, because playing with matches is unsafe for everyone.', 'Join them because it looks exciting.', 'Tell them to stop, but don\'t tell an adult.', 'Watch them from a distance.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(531, 9, 2, 'Your friend wants to climb over a tall fence to get a ball, even though there\'s a gate nearby. How can you apply your knowledge of safe behavior here?', 'Suggest using the gate, explaining that climbing fences can be dangerous and cause injury.', 'Climb with them to help them.', 'Tell them to be careful while they climb.', 'Ignore them and keep playing.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(532, 9, 2, 'You are home alone and someone knocks on the door whom you don\'t know. How should you analyze this situation based on your personal security duties?', 'Open the door to see who it is.', 'Ask who it is through the door.', 'Pretend you are not home.', 'Do not open the door, and tell a trusted adult who is home that someone is there. If no adult is home, stay quiet and safe inside.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(533, 9, 2, 'Which action best demonstrates responsibility for the safety of others?', 'Helping a younger child cross the street safely by holding their hand and looking both ways.', 'Leaving your toys scattered where people can trip.', 'Pushing your friend on the playground.', 'Not telling anyone when you see something dangerous.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(534, 9, 2, 'Your school has a \"buddy system\" for walking in hallways. How does this apply to your responsibility for personal security and the safety of others?', 'It means you can walk alone if you want.', 'It means you help keep yourself and your buddy safe by staying together and looking out for each other.', 'It\'s just a way for teachers to know where you are.', 'It means you have to share everything with your buddy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(535, 9, 2, 'You are at a friend\'s house, and their older sibling suggests playing a game that involves climbing very high on furniture. What should you do?', 'Join in, because it sounds exciting.', 'Tell them you\'re not good at climbing.', 'Say \"no, thank you\" and suggest a safer game, explaining that climbing on furniture can cause falls and injuries.', 'Wait to see if anyone else falls first.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(536, 9, 2, 'You receive a message on your game console from someone you don\'t know, asking for your real name and school. How should you apply your personal security knowledge?', 'Tell them your name, but not your school.', 'Do not share any personal information and tell a trusted adult about the message.', 'Ask them for their name and school first.', 'Block them immediately without telling anyone.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(537, 9, 2, 'You and your friends are playing near a construction site. You remember learning about identifying unsafe behaviors. How do you analyze this situation?', 'Construction sites are dangerous with heavy machinery and materials, so it\'s an unsafe place to play.', 'It\'s a fun place to play hide-and-seek.', 'As long as you are careful, it\'s fine.', 'You might find cool things to play with.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(538, 9, 2, 'Which scenario best demonstrates a child\'s responsibility for their own safety?', 'A child runs across the street to catch a ball without checking for cars.', 'A child wears a helmet and knee pads every time they ride their scooter.', 'A child ignores a \"Wet Floor\" sign.', 'A child plays with a broken toy that has sharp edges.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(539, 9, 2, 'A younger child is about to pick up a sharp piece of glass from the ground. How can you apply your responsibility for the safety of others?', 'Let them pick it up so they learn.', 'Quickly warn them not to touch it, explain it\'s dangerous, and tell a trusted adult to remove it.', 'Tell them it\'s a pretty piece of glass.', 'Pick it up yourself to be helpful.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(540, 9, 2, 'Your older cousin always wears a helmet when biking, even for short rides. How is your cousin acting as a personal security role model?', 'They are just showing off their new helmet.', 'They are too careful.', 'They want to look cool.', 'They are demonstrating a safe behavior that you can apply to your own biking habits.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(541, 9, 2, 'You are at a family gathering and see a younger child about to touch a hot stove. Your parent quickly but calmly moves the child away and explains the danger. How can you analyze your parent\'s action as a role model?', 'Your parent is being mean to the child.', 'Your parent is modeling quick thinking and explaining danger, which teaches you to protect others from hazards.', 'Your parent is just trying to cook.', 'Your parent is being silly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(542, 9, 2, 'In some cultures, children are taught to always walk in groups, even for short distances. How does this cultural influence apply to personal safety?', 'It means they don\'t like to be alone.', 'It\'s just a way to make friends.', 'It emphasizes that there is safety in numbers, providing more eyes and ears to spot potential dangers.', 'It means they are not allowed to go outside alone.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(543, 9, 2, 'You lost your way in a large store. You remember learning about applying personal security tips. What is the best thing to do?', 'Find a store employee or a mom with kids, explain you\'re lost, and ask them to help you find your parents.', 'Keep walking around until you find your parents.', 'Hide in a clothes rack.', 'Yell your parents\' names loudly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(544, 9, 2, 'You are talking to a friend who is thinking of sharing their game password with an online stranger. How can you engage in critical thinking to help your friend solve this problem?', 'Tell them it\'s their choice.', 'Explain that sharing passwords is risky because the stranger could take over their account or steal personal information, and suggest they never share it.', 'Ask the stranger if they will share their password too.', 'Tell your friend to change their password after sharing it.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:12:29'),
(545, 9, 3, 'Your school is making a \"Personal Security Pledge.\" Which statement would be the most important one to include for kids your age to always remember?', 'I will always try new foods.', 'I will be the fastest runner in my class.', 'I will always tell a trusted adult if something makes me feel unsafe or uncomfortable.', 'I will only play games inside my house.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(546, 9, 3, 'If you were teaching a younger child about personal security, what new, simple rule would you create to help them remember to make safe choices?', 'Always look both ways before crossing the street.', 'Eat all your vegetables.', 'Brush your teeth twice a day.', 'Never talk to anyone you don\'t know very well without a trusted adult nearby.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(547, 9, 3, 'You overhear two friends arguing about whether it\'s okay to accept a candy bar from an unknown delivery person. What is the best advice you can offer them, explaining why?', 'It\'s okay if the candy looks tasty, because free candy is always good.', 'Just take the candy, but don\'t eat it right away.', 'Ask your parents later if it was okay to take it.', 'Don\'t take anything from strangers, even if they seem nice, because it\'s hard to know if they have good intentions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(548, 9, 3, 'Your class is making posters about \"Stranger Safety.\" Which evaluation of a safety rule would be the most important to highlight for young children?', 'Always share your toys with strangers.', 'Strangers are always mean people.', 'Never accept gifts or rides from strangers, because they might be trying to trick you.', 'Only talk to strangers if your best friend is there.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(549, 9, 3, 'If you had to create a new catchy jingle or rhyme to help other kids remember how to stay safe from strangers, what would be the most important message to include?', 'Candy is sweet, a sugary treat!', 'Play outside, don\'t hide!', 'Sharing is caring, always daring!', 'If a stranger calls your name, run and tell, that\'s the game!', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(550, 9, 3, 'Imagine your community is setting up a \"Safe Spot\" program (like a trusted store or library) where kids can go if they feel unsafe. What is the best reason for having such spots, and what kind of training would you recommend for the adults working there?', 'It provides a safe haven for kids in trouble; adults should be trained to listen, protect, and contact parents or police.', 'It\'s a place to buy snacks; adults should know how to make change.', 'It\'s a place for kids to play; adults should be good at games.', 'It\'s a place to do homework; adults should be good at math.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(551, 9, 3, 'Your class is discussing the importance of checking labels and expiry dates. Which statement best evaluates why this step is so critical for your health?', 'It helps us find the cheapest products.', 'It helps us remember where we bought the item.', 'It ensures we are using safe products that will not harm us because they are fresh and correctly made.', 'It\'s just a rule adults like to make.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(552, 9, 3, 'If you were creating a public service announcement (PSA) for kids about avoiding fake drugs, what would be the most important piece of advice to give?', 'Always ask for extra medicine.', 'Medicine tastes like candy.', 'Collect all the colorful pills you can find.', 'Only take medicine that your trusted parent or doctor gives you, and never take pills from friends or strangers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(553, 9, 3, 'Your younger brother wants to buy some brightly colored candy from a vendor he doesn\'t know, but the candy has no packaging or ingredients listed. What is the best advice you can give him, and why should he follow it?', 'Don\'t buy that candy because without a label, you don\'t know what\'s in it, and it could be unsafe or make you sick.', 'It\'s okay to buy it, it looks yummy!', 'Just try one piece to see if it\'s good.', 'Ask the vendor if it\'s safe.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(554, 9, 3, 'Your family is discussing emergency plans. Which statement best evaluates why knowing how to contact emergency services (like calling 911/112/199) is a vital personal security responsibility for a child?', 'It\'s important for memorizing numbers.', 'It\'s crucial because in a real emergency, you might need to get help quickly when an adult isn\'t immediately available.', 'It helps you practice your speaking skills.', 'It\'s only for adults to know.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(555, 9, 3, 'If you were asked to create a new \"Safety Superhero\" character for your school, what would be their most important power or advice related to a child\'s duties in personal security?', 'The power to fly anywhere they want.', 'The power to eat unlimited candy.', 'The power to always know when to \"Stop, Think, and Act Safely\" and to tell a trusted adult.', 'The power to turn invisible.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(556, 9, 3, 'You and your classmates are asked to come up with ideas for a school safety campaign. Which idea shows the most critical thinking and responsibility in helping others stay safe?', 'Making posters that just say \"Be Safe.\"', 'Suggesting everyone wears brightly colored clothes.', 'Creating a presentation that teaches younger students specific \"stop, look, and listen\" rules for crossing the street, including real-life examples.', 'Making a list of all the school\'s rules.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(557, 9, 3, 'Your class is thinking about the most important things a child should do to ensure their safety. Which action best evaluates a child taking charge of their personal security?', 'Actively learning and remembering safety rules, and speaking up if they feel unsafe or see something unsafe.', 'Always being the first one to finish schoolwork.', 'Having the most toys at home.', 'Always being quiet and polite.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(558, 9, 3, 'If you were to create a \"Safety First\" slogan for kids to remember their duties, what message would be the most impactful for a 9-10 year old?', 'Eat healthy, feel great!', 'Your safety, your power! Speak up and take action every hour!', 'Read books, get smart!', 'Play nice, share your space!', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(559, 9, 3, 'Your principal asks your class to design a short presentation for parents about how they can be good safety role models. What is the most important message you would recommend they include?', 'Parents should buy their children lots of safety equipment.', 'Parents should only talk about safety on special days.', 'Parents should let their children learn from their own mistakes.', 'Parents should consistently model safe behaviors, discuss safety rules openly, and listen carefully when their child talks about feeling unsafe.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(560, 9, 3, 'Your family is discussing emergency plans. Which statement best evaluates why knowing how to contact emergency services (like calling 911/112/199) is a vital personal security responsibility for a child?', 'It\'s important for memorizing numbers.', 'It\'s crucial because in a real emergency, you might need to get help quickly when an adult isn\'t immediately available.', 'It helps you practice your speaking skills.', 'It\'s only for adults to know.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(561, 9, 3, 'If you were asked to create a new \"Safety Superhero\" character for your school, what would be their most important power or advice related to a child\'s duties in personal security?', 'The power to fly anywhere they want.', 'The power to eat unlimited candy.', 'The power to always know when to \"Stop, Think, and Act Safely\" and to tell a trusted adult.', 'The power to turn invisible.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(562, 9, 3, 'You and your friends are deciding how to play safely near a busy road. Which solution for safe play demonstrates the most responsibility and problem-solving?', 'Play very close to the road but promise to be careful.', 'Find a safer place to play far from the road, or play in a supervised yard, to prevent accidents.', 'Just play tag and hope no cars come.', 'Only play with slow-moving cars.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:14:15'),
(563, 12, 1, 'What does the term \"environment\" refer to?', 'Only the animals in a place.', 'Only the buildings in a city.', 'Only the plants in a forest.', 'Everything that surrounds us, including living and non-living things.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(564, 12, 1, 'How can your environment influence your daily life?', 'By affecting the weather, the food you eat, or the games you play.', 'By deciding what TV shows you watch.', 'By choosing your friends for you.', 'By telling you when to sleep.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(565, 12, 1, 'Which of these is a way humans can impact (change) the environment?', 'Watching the clouds pass by.', 'Littering or planting trees.', 'Learning a new language.', 'Counting the stars at night.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(566, 12, 1, 'What does it mean to contribute positively to your environment?', 'To ignore all environmental problems.', 'To make more trash.', 'To do things that help keep it clean and healthy, like recycling.', 'To only talk about the environment.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(567, 12, 1, 'What does \"maintaining a clean and healthy environment\" involve?', 'Only cleaning your room.', 'Keeping air, water, and land free from pollution and disease.', 'Always buying new things.', 'Never going outside.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(568, 12, 1, 'What is often considered the basic unit of society?', 'A family.', 'A school.', 'A market.', 'A large city.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(569, 12, 1, 'Which of these is a role a child might have within a family?', 'To pay all the bills.', 'To help with chores and show respect.', 'To decide where everyone lives.', 'To cook all the meals.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(570, 12, 1, 'Why is it important to understand each family members role?', 'So you can boss everyone around.', 'So you know who gets more toys.', 'So everyone knows their responsibilities and how to support each other for harmony.', 'So you know only your own role.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(571, 12, 1, 'What does \"family harmony\" mean?', 'When family members never talk to each other.', 'When family members always argue.', 'When everyone in the family is exactly the same.', 'When family members get along well, cooperate, and support each other.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(572, 12, 1, 'What does it mean to \"identify the different roles within a family\"?', 'To name and describe the specific jobs or responsibilities each person has.', 'To guess what each person does.', 'To draw pictures of family members.', 'To decide who has the most important role.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(573, 12, 1, 'What does culture mainly refer to?', 'Only the food people eat.', 'Only the songs people sing.', 'The different languages people speak.', 'The shared customs, beliefs, art, and way of life of a group of people.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(574, 12, 1, 'What does diversity mean in a community?', 'When there is a variety of people from different backgrounds, with different cultures or beliefs.', 'When everyone is exactly the same.', 'When people live in different houses.', 'When people have different opinions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(575, 12, 1, 'What is unity about?', 'People being exactly alike.', 'People working or living together in harmony, despite differences.', 'People always agreeing on everything.', 'People never talking to each other.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(576, 12, 1, 'Which of these is an example of a cultural tradition?', 'Learning math in school.', 'Playing a new video game.', 'A specific festival, dance, or clothing style passed down through generations.', 'Riding a bicycle.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(577, 12, 1, 'What does it mean to \"appreciate different cultural traditions\"?', 'To value and respect them, understanding their importance to others.', 'To ignore them.', 'To criticize them.', 'To just look at them.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(578, 12, 1, 'What does responsible parenthood involve?', 'Only providing food.', 'Only giving toys.', 'Only telling children what to do.', 'Showing love, care, honesty, patience, and support to children.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(579, 12, 1, 'Which of these is a key aspect of being a responsible parent?', 'Showing patience and understanding.', 'Ignoring children\'s feelings.', 'Always being angry with children.', 'Never spending time with children.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(580, 12, 1, 'What does parental responsibility mean?', 'Parents only focusing on their own needs.', 'The duties and obligations parents have to care for and raise their children well.', 'Children taking care of their parents.', 'Parents letting children do whatever they want.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(581, 12, 1, 'Why is responsible parenting important for a child\'s growth?', 'It makes children independent too quickly.', 'It makes children always listen to parents.', 'It helps children feel safe, loved, and grow into happy, healthy individuals.', 'It only helps parents.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(582, 12, 1, 'What does it mean to \"identify key aspects of being a responsible parent\"?', 'To name and describe the important qualities that make a parent responsible.', 'To guess what parents should do.', 'To only think about what parents get.', 'To ignore parents\' duties.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(583, 12, 1, 'What does personal hygiene mainly refer to?', 'Practices that keep your body clean and healthy.', 'Only washing your clothes.', 'Only brushing your teeth.', 'Only eating healthy food.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(584, 12, 1, 'Which of these is a physical change that occurs during pre-adolescence (around 9-12 years old)?', 'Becoming much shorter.', 'Teeth always falling out.', 'Bones stopping growth.', 'Rapid growth spurts and body changes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(585, 12, 1, 'Why is personal hygiene important for overall health?', 'It helps you make more friends.', 'It helps prevent the spread of germs and diseases.', 'It makes you sleep faster.', 'It helps you learn new things.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(586, 12, 1, 'What is a main purpose of a personal hygiene checklist?', 'To remind you to play games.', 'To help you decide what to eat.', 'To ensure you remember and perform daily hygiene habits consistently.', 'To list your favorite things.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(587, 12, 1, 'What does it mean to \"identify physical changes\" during pre-adolescence?', 'To recognize and describe the new ways your body is growing and changing.', 'To guess what will happen.', 'To remember only one change.', 'To ignore changes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(588, 12, 1, 'What does responsible citizenship mean?', 'Only caring about yourself and your family.', 'Knowing all the laws by heart.', 'Just living in a country.', 'Being a member of a country or community and acting in ways that help it.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(589, 12, 1, 'Why is responsible citizenship important?', 'It helps the community stay strong and work well.', 'It makes everything easier for leaders.', 'It means everyone gets rich.', 'It helps people avoid their duties.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(590, 12, 1, 'What is cultural diversity?', 'When everyone in a community is exactly the same.', 'When a community has people from many different backgrounds, with different customs, languages, and beliefs.', 'When people only celebrate one holiday.', 'When people never share their ideas.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(591, 12, 1, 'What is the role of respect in a diverse community?', 'To make people hide their differences.', 'To cause arguments among people.', 'To help people understand and value each other\'s differences, leading to peace and cooperation.', 'To make some people feel less important.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(592, 12, 1, 'What does it mean to \"identify ways to actively contribute\" to one\'s community?', 'To list actions you can take to make your community better.', 'To only complain about community problems.', 'To wait for others to solve community problems.', 'To ignore community needs.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:18:39'),
(593, 12, 2, 'Imagine you live near a river. If people start throwing trash into it, how does this impact the environment?', 'It makes the river cleaner.', 'It helps the fish grow bigger.', 'It pollutes the water, harming animals and making it unsafe for humans.', 'It makes the river smell nicer.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(594, 12, 2, 'Your family decides to start a small garden to grow vegetables. How does this action positively contribute to your environment?', 'It makes the garden look colorful.', 'It uses up all the water.', 'It helps provide fresh food and can improve the local air quality.', 'It only helps the family.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(595, 12, 2, 'Consider a very hot climate. How might this environment influence the type of houses people build?', 'Houses would have very thick walls and no windows.', 'Houses would have many open windows and light materials to stay cool.', 'Houses would be built underground.', 'Houses would be made of ice.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(596, 12, 2, 'If your community organizes a \"Go Green\" club to plant trees, how does this activity analyze ways to positively contribute to the environment?', 'It shows that trees are not important.', 'It creates more work for everyone.', 'It demonstrates collective effort to improve air quality and provide habitats.', 'It only helps the club members.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(597, 12, 2, 'A factory releases smoke into the air every day. How does this action impact the environment, and why is it a negative impact?', 'It makes the air smell good.', 'It adds pollution to the air, which can harm living things and make people sick.', 'It means the factory is working hard.', 'It makes the sky look interesting.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(598, 12, 2, 'Imagine your younger sibling needs help with their homework. If you help them, how does this demonstrate responsibility toward a family member?', 'It shows you are smarter than them.', 'It means you are doing their homework for them.', 'It shows you don\'t have your own homework.', 'It shows you are caring and willing to support your family member.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(599, 12, 2, 'Your family is deciding where to go for a picnic, and everyone has different ideas. How can tolerance help achieve family harmony in this situation?', 'By insisting on your own idea only.', 'By listening to and respecting everyone\'s preferences, even if you don\'t fully agree.', 'By arguing until someone gives up.', 'By ignoring everyone\'s ideas.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(600, 12, 2, 'When there is a disagreement in your family about sharing toys, how can problem-solving skills contribute to family harmony?', 'By hiding all the toys.', 'By letting only one person decide.', 'By working together to find a fair solution that everyone can agree on.', 'By yelling until someone gets their way.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(601, 12, 2, 'A parent works hard to provide for the family, and a child helps with chores. How does this analyze the importance of each family member\'s role?', 'It demonstrates how different roles contribute essential support for the family\'s well-being and functioning.', 'It shows that only parents work hard.', 'It means children do not need to help.', 'It means everyone does the same job.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(602, 12, 2, 'Your older sibling teaches you how to ride a bike patiently. How does this demonstrate respect and responsibility within the family?', 'It means they don\'t have anything else to do.', 'It shows care, patience, and a willingness to teach and support a younger family member.', 'It proves they are better than you.', 'It means you must teach them something back.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(603, 12, 2, 'Imagine your class has students from different ethnic backgrounds. How can promoting respect help them stay united?', 'By telling them to ignore their differences.', 'By making everyone dress the same way.', 'By encouraging them to value and learn from each other\'s unique cultures, building a friendly environment.', 'By separating them into groups.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(604, 12, 2, 'Two friends from different cultures have a misunderstanding because of different customs. How can empathy help them resolve the conflict?', 'By making them argue more.', 'By making one friend ignore the other.', 'By telling them to only follow one custom.', 'By helping them understand and share each other\'s feelings and perspectives.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(605, 12, 2, 'Your school has a diverse group of students with different talents (e.g., some are good at drawing, others at singing). How can these differences contribute to unity in a school project?', 'It would make the project harder.', 'By encouraging everyone to use their unique talents, they can create a richer and more complete project together.', 'It means some talents are not needed.', 'It would cause arguments.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(606, 12, 2, 'If your community has different cultural groups, how can interactive activities (like a cultural fair) promote inclusivity?', 'By allowing people to share and experience each other\'s traditions in a fun, respectful way.', 'By making everyone feel uncomfortable.', 'By only celebrating one culture.', 'By keeping groups separate.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(607, 12, 2, 'A conflict arises when two students disagree about how to celebrate a cultural event. How can applying problem-solving strategies (like talking it out) contribute to unity?', 'It would make the argument worse.', 'It helps them find a compromise or a solution that respects both cultural traditions.', 'It means one person has to give up entirely.', 'It makes everyone confused.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(608, 12, 2, 'A parent makes sure their child goes to school every day and helps with homework. How does this demonstrate responsible parenting?', 'It shows the parent is strict.', 'It means the parent wants the child to be perfect.', 'It shows commitment to the child\'s education and future.', 'It means the parent has too much time.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(609, 12, 2, 'A child is feeling sad, and their parent listens carefully and offers comforting words. How does this reflect the parent\'s role in providing emotional support?', 'It means the parent is weak.', 'It shows the parent wants to make the child cry more.', 'It means the parent has nothing else to do.', 'It demonstrates empathy and active care for the child\'s feelings, which is part of responsible parenting.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(610, 12, 2, 'Imagine a family where parents always discuss problems calmly and work together to find solutions. How does this contribute to positive family dynamics?', 'It makes the family argue more.', 'It fosters open communication and mutual respect, strengthening family bonds.', 'It shows parents are afraid of problems.', 'It means problems never happen.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(611, 12, 2, 'A child receives love and care from their responsible parents. How does this impact the child\'s individual growth?', 'It can help the child feel secure, confident, and develop a positive outlook on life.', 'It makes the child selfish.', 'It makes the child dependent on parents forever.', 'It stops the child from learning.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(612, 12, 2, 'If parents teach their children the importance of honesty by always telling the truth themselves, how are they modeling responsible parenting?', 'They are just showing off.', 'They are demonstrating the value through their own actions, which children learn from.', 'They are trying to trick their children.', 'They are being too strict.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(613, 12, 2, 'You notice your hair is starting to get oily more quickly than before. How would you apply personal hygiene strategies to manage this change?', 'Stop washing your hair.', 'Use more hairspray.', 'Wash your hair more regularly with shampoo.', 'Wear a hat all the time.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(614, 12, 2, 'A friend complains about body odor after playing outside. How can you discuss a solution to this common hygiene issue?', 'Tell them to just ignore it.', 'Tell them to cover it with perfume.', 'Tell them to stop playing.', 'Suggest they take a shower or bath and use deodorant.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(615, 12, 2, 'Your teeth are growing in, and your dentist advises you to brush twice a day. How does this reflect the importance of hygiene for overall health?', 'It\'s just a suggestion for looking good.', 'Brushing regularly prevents cavities and gum disease, which contributes to good overall health.', 'It means you have to brush for a long time.', 'It stops you from eating candy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(616, 12, 2, 'If a student creates a checklist that includes \"brush teeth, shower, change clothes, wash hands,\" how does this demonstrate developing a personal hygiene strategy?', 'It is a systematic way to remember and practice daily self-care habits.', 'It means they are lazy.', 'It shows they are only trying to make a list.', 'It is a list of things to avoid.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(617, 12, 2, 'During pre-adolescence, some children\'s voices may begin to change slightly. How would you reflect on how to handle this physical change?', 'Try to stop your voice from changing.', 'Understand that it\'s a normal part of growing up and accept the changes patiently.', 'Stop talking altogether.', 'Only whisper.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(618, 12, 2, 'Imagine your local park is dirty. How could you actively contribute to improving it as a responsible citizen?', 'By complaining to your friends about the trash.', 'By waiting for someone else to clean it.', 'By organizing a clean-up day with friends and family, or by picking up litter yourself.', 'By throwing more trash.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(619, 12, 2, 'Your community has people from many different countries, and you learn about their holidays. How does this recognize the value of cultural diversity?', 'It shows that only your culture is important.', 'It helps you ignore other cultures.', 'It means you have to celebrate every holiday.', 'It shows appreciation for different traditions and enriches your understanding of the world.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(620, 12, 2, 'A student sees a new classmate who is struggling to understand a lesson. How can the student practice empathy and help solve this community issue (classroom as community)?', 'Ignore the classmate.', 'Understand the classmate\'s feelings and offer to help explain the lesson.', 'Make fun of the classmate.', 'Tell the teacher it\'s not their problem.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(621, 12, 2, 'If you see someone damaging public property (like drawing on a school wall), how can you actively contribute to improving your community?', 'Speak up against the action or report it to a trusted adult/authority.', 'Join them in damaging property.', 'Ignore it, as it\'s not your job.', 'Take a picture of the damage.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(622, 12, 2, 'A neighborhood experiences frequent power outages. How might a group of responsible citizens develop problem-solving skills to address this issue?', 'They would complain but do nothing else.', 'They might gather information, contact the power company, and collectively propose solutions.', 'They would move to another neighborhood.', 'They would rely only on candles.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:13'),
(623, 12, 3, 'Your class is reflecting on the importance of maintaining a clean and healthy environment. Which statement best evaluates why everyone\'s participation is crucial for this goal?', 'Only governments should worry about the environment.', 'One person\'s actions don\'t matter much.', 'Even small actions by many people add up to a big difference in keeping our environment healthy.', 'It\'s too difficult for everyone to help.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(624, 12, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple rule for your school to help students positively contribute to their environment, what rule would be most effective?', 'Don\'t pick up trash.', 'Always throw your litter on the ground.', 'Place all your waste in the correct recycling bins.', 'Use as much water as you want.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(625, 12, 3, 'Think about how our environment shapes who we are. If you had to design a new playground that helps children connect with and appreciate their local environment, what feature would be most important to include?', 'Only concrete and plastic structures.', 'Elements that incorporate natural materials like wood and rocks, or a small garden area.', 'A very tall fence around it.', 'Only artificial grass.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(626, 12, 3, 'Your class is discussing family harmony. Which statement best evaluates why tolerance is a crucial quality for family members?', 'Tolerance means always agreeing with everything.', 'Tolerance makes family life boring.', 'Tolerance allows family members to accept differences and resolve conflicts peacefully, leading to a happier home.', 'Tolerance is not needed in families.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(627, 12, 3, 'If you were asked to create a family chore chart, what design element would be most important to ensure everyone understands their responsibility and feels respected?', 'Only assign chores to one person.', 'Make the chart very small and hard to read.', 'Only list chores that nobody wants to do.', 'Clearly list each person\'s chores in a fair way, with spaces to check them off.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(628, 12, 3, 'Reflect on how tolerance and problem-solving contribute to family harmony. If you had to design a family game that teaches these values, what would be the most effective rule for the game?', 'A rule that encourages arguing.', 'A rule that says one person always wins.', 'A rule that requires players to listen to each other\'s ideas and compromise to reach a solution.', 'A rule that makes winning impossible.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(629, 12, 3, 'Your class is discussing strategies for resolving conflicts and building empathy. Which statement best evaluates why active listening is a crucial skill for conflict resolution?', 'Active listening means you just wait to talk.', 'Active listening makes conflicts worse.', 'Active listening is only for quiet people.', 'Active listening helps you truly understand the other person\'s point of view, which is the first step to finding a solution.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(630, 12, 3, 'If you were asked to create a school event to promote respect and inclusivity among peers, what would be the most effective type of activity?', 'A competition where only one culture wins.', 'A class where everyone learns the exact same thing.', 'An event where students are divided by their differences.', 'An event where students can share their unique cultural dances, songs, or stories with each other.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(631, 12, 3, 'Reflect on how we can stay united even though we are all different. If you had to design a \"Unity Badge\" for your classmates, what symbols or colors would you use to best promote respect and inclusivity?', 'Symbols that represent diversity (different people) coming together in harmony, like interconnected hands or varied colors blending.', 'Symbols that show only one type of person.', 'Colors that clash and symbols that divide.', 'Symbols that are very hard to understand.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(632, 12, 3, 'Your class is reflecting on the importance of parental responsibilities. Which statement best evaluates why patience is a crucial quality for responsible parents?', 'Patience means parents are slow.', 'Patience means parents let children do anything.', 'Patience allows parents to guide children through mistakes and challenges with understanding, fostering growth.', 'Patience is only needed for very young children.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(633, 12, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple guide for a younger sibling on how to support your parents, what is the most important contribution you would emphasize?', 'Only asking for gifts from parents.', 'Ignoring parents when they talk.', 'Always arguing with parents.', 'Helping with small chores and showing appreciation for their efforts.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(634, 12, 3, 'Think about how children can support their parents and contribute to their family. If you had to design a \"Family Teamwork\" award for your own family, what actions from a child would be most important to recognize?', 'Always getting the best grades at school.', 'Keeping their room perfectly clean all the time.', 'Helping with household chores without being asked, and showing kindness to siblings.', 'Being the quietest child in the house.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(635, 12, 3, 'Your class is discussing managing physical changes during growth. Which statement best evaluates why staying informed about these changes is crucial?', 'It makes changes happen faster.', 'It means you don\'t need to do anything.', 'Being informed helps you understand that changes are normal and how to take care of yourself, reducing worry.', 'Only doctors need to know about body changes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(636, 12, 3, 'If you were asked to create a new hygiene habit for students to adopt in school to promote overall health, what effective habit would you suggest?', 'Not washing hands after playing.', 'Always sharing drinks and food directly.', 'Sneezing into your hands.', 'Washing hands thoroughly before eating and after using the restroom.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(637, 12, 3, 'Think about discussing solutions to common hygiene issues. If you had to design a peer-teaching activity on personal hygiene for younger students, what practical tip would be most impactful to include?', 'Only use cold water for washing.', 'That showering daily helps remove sweat and dirt, making you feel fresh and clean.', 'Only brush teeth once a week.', 'That hygiene is only for looking good.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(638, 12, 3, 'Your class is discussing what it means to be a responsible citizen. Which statement best evaluates why respecting cultural diversity is a key aspect of responsible citizenship?', 'It\'s only for looking good to others.', 'It creates arguments among people.', 'It builds a harmonious society where everyone feels valued, which is essential for a strong community.', 'It makes communities less organized.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(639, 12, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple rule for your classroom to promote active contribution to the community (school), what rule would be most effective?', 'Only the teacher cleans the classroom.', 'Students must complain about problems every day.', 'No one should talk about community issues.', 'Everyone must take turns helping keep our classroom tidy and organized.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(640, 12, 3, 'Reflect on how empathy and problem-solving skills relate to community issues. If you had to design a school project to help improve a local issue (e.g., helping the elderly), what would be the most important element to ensure it reflects responsible citizenship?', 'Focusing only on getting good grades for the project.', 'Designing a clear plan that involves students actively helping elderly residents in a compassionate and organized way.', 'Making the project very difficult to complete.', 'Only talking about the elderly, not helping them.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:20:39'),
(641, 19, 1, 'What is agriculture mainly about?', 'Growing crops and raising animals for human use.', 'Building houses and roads.', 'Learning about history.', 'Only fishing in the ocean.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(642, 19, 1, 'Which of these is a component of agriculture?', 'Space travel.', 'Writing stories.', 'Building tall buildings.', 'Crop cultivation (growing plants).', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(643, 19, 1, 'What does animal rearing mean in agriculture?', 'Only watching animals.', 'Taking care of and breeding animals like cows, chickens, or goats.', 'Learning how animals play.', 'Drawing pictures of animals.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44');
INSERT INTO `exam_questions` (`question_id`, `subject_id`, `type`, `question`, `option1`, `option2`, `option3`, `option4`, `option5`, `feedback1`, `feedback2`, `feedback3`, `feedback4`, `feedback5`, `answer`, `marks`, `createdate`) VALUES
(644, 19, 1, 'Why is agriculture important in our daily lives?', 'It helps us fly.', 'It provides all the water we drink.', 'It provides most of our food and many materials we use.', 'It only helps farmers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(645, 19, 1, 'What does it mean to \"define Agriculture\"?', 'To explain clearly what agriculture is and what it includes.', 'To guess what it is.', 'To only talk about farms.', 'To ignore where food comes from.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(646, 19, 1, 'What is the primary role of agriculture in providing for people?', 'Providing food, medicine, and raw materials.', 'Providing only electricity.', 'Providing only toys.', 'Providing only transportation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(647, 19, 1, 'Which of these is a source of food that comes from agriculture?', 'Plastic bottles.', 'Computers.', 'Rocks.', 'Fruits and vegetables.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(648, 19, 1, 'What does \"raw materials\" from agriculture mean?', 'Finished products like clothes.', 'Basic natural resources from farming that are used to make other things.', 'Only water.', 'Only electricity.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(649, 19, 1, 'What does it mean to \"understand the meaning of agriculture\"?', 'To only plant one seed.', 'To know how to drive a tractor.', 'To define what agriculture is and how it works.', 'To ignore how food grows.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(650, 19, 1, 'Which of these is a source of medicine that can come from agriculture?', 'Certain plants.', 'Metals from mining.', 'Oil from the ground.', 'Electricity.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(651, 19, 1, 'What does agriculture refer to?', 'The study of ancient buildings.', 'Making clothes in factories.', 'Only catching fish from the sea.', 'The practice of farming, including growing crops and raising animals for food and products.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(652, 19, 1, 'Which of these is an example of an innovative agricultural practice?', 'Using modern irrigation to save water.', 'Planting only one type of crop every year.', 'Relying only on traditional hand tools.', 'Letting farm animals wander freely.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(653, 19, 1, 'What is the significance of agriculture in society?', 'It only provides jobs for farmers.', 'It provides essential food, raw materials, and supports livelihoods.', 'It makes the weather change.', 'It teaches people to sing.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(654, 19, 1, 'How does technology improve farming?', 'By making farming slower.', 'By making farmers tired.', 'By providing machines and systems that make tasks more efficient, like planting or harvesting.', 'By hiding problems.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(655, 19, 1, 'What does it mean to \"define agriculture\"?', 'To explain what agriculture is and why it matters.', 'To draw a picture of a farm.', 'To guess where food comes from.', 'To remember only one type of crop.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(656, 19, 1, 'Which of these is one of the three main types of soil?', 'Clay soil.', 'Rock soil.', 'Water soil.', 'Air soil.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(657, 19, 1, 'What is sandy soil known for?', 'Holding a lot of water.', 'Being sticky.', 'Being dark in color.', 'Draining water very quickly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(658, 19, 1, 'What does soil health mean?', 'How old the soil is.', 'The quality of soil that allows plants to grow strong and healthy.', 'The amount of sand in the soil.', 'How cold the soil is.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(659, 19, 1, 'Which of these is a modern technique for soil enrichment?', 'Using only rain water.', 'Ignoring soil needs.', 'Adding compost or fertilizers.', 'Throwing trash in the soil.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(660, 19, 1, 'What is a loamy soil?', 'A type of soil that is a balanced mix of sand, silt, and clay.', 'A soil that is too hard for plants.', 'A soil that is always dry.', 'A soil that is only found in mountains.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(661, 19, 1, 'What is soil fertility?', 'The ability of soil to provide enough nutrients for plants to grow well.', 'The color of the soil.', 'The amount of water in the soil.', 'How hard the soil is.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(662, 19, 1, 'Which of these is a cause of soil fertility reduction?', 'Adding lots of compost.', 'Planting different crops each year.', 'Letting the soil rest.', 'Continual farming without adding nutrients back to the soil.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(663, 19, 1, 'What does it mean to enrich soil fertility?', 'To make the soil disappear.', 'To add valuable substances to the soil to make it better for growing plants.', 'To only add water to the soil.', 'To remove all plants from the soil.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(664, 19, 1, 'Which of these is a benefit of advanced farming techniques?', 'They make farming slower.', 'They use more manual labor.', 'They can increase crop yields and make farming more efficient.', 'They always make farming more difficult.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(665, 19, 1, 'What does it mean to \"define soil\"?', 'To identify its components and purpose.', 'To guess what soil is.', 'To only talk about dirt.', 'To ignore what soil is made of.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(666, 19, 1, 'What is the importance of soil fertility?', 'It ensures crops get enough nutrients to grow strong and healthy.', 'It helps soil disappear.', 'It makes the soil hard.', 'It is only about the color of the soil.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(667, 19, 1, 'Which of these is a method to enrich soil fertility?', 'Removing all organic matter.', 'Pouring oil on the soil.', 'Burning all plants.', 'Adding compost or manure.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(668, 19, 1, 'What is crop rotation?', 'Planting the same crop every year in the same spot.', 'Changing the type of crop grown in a field each season to maintain soil health.', 'Only growing one crop.', 'Growing crops in circles.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(669, 19, 1, 'How does traditional farming practice like leaving land fallow (resting) contribute to soil health?', 'It makes the land unusable.', 'It makes the soil harder.', 'It allows the soil to naturally regain nutrients and health over time.', 'It wastes farm land.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(670, 19, 1, 'What does it mean to \"understand the importance of soil fertility\"?', 'To know how vital healthy, nutrient-rich soil is for successful farming and food production.', 'To guess why soil is important.', 'To only learn about soil from pictures.', 'To ignore soil\'s needs.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(671, 19, 1, 'What is a traditional agricultural tool?', 'A simple tool used by farmers for a long time, like a hoe or cutlass.', 'A very complex robot.', 'A machine that flies.', 'A tool that only works with electricity.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(672, 19, 1, 'What does farming efficiency mean?', 'Farming very slowly.', 'Wasting a lot of resources.', 'Doing farming tasks quickly and effectively with less wasted effort or resources.', 'Making farming harder.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(673, 19, 1, 'What does longevity mean for farm tools?', 'How old the tool is.', 'How long the tool lasts and remains useful.', 'How heavy the tool is.', 'How much the tool costs.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(674, 19, 1, 'Which of these is a way to maintain agricultural tools?', 'Leaving them dirty after use.', 'Throwing them in water.', 'Cleaning them and storing them properly.', 'Breaking them into pieces.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(675, 19, 1, 'What does it mean to \"identify traditional and modern agricultural tools\"?', 'To name and describe old tools and new tools used in farming.', 'To guess what tools exist.', 'To only use one type of tool.', 'To ignore any tools.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(676, 19, 1, 'Which of these is a tool used for digging in agriculture?', 'A hoe.', 'A basket.', 'A rope.', 'A chair.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(677, 19, 1, 'What does \"maintenance\" of agricultural tools mean?', 'Making them look shiny only.', 'Taking care of tools by cleaning, repairing, and storing them to keep them working well.', 'Using tools only for playing.', 'Letting tools rust.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(678, 19, 1, 'Which of these is a traditional tool?', 'A drone.', 'A cutlass.', 'A GPS-guided planter.', 'A smartphone.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(679, 19, 1, 'How have agricultural tools evolved with modern technology?', 'They have become harder to use.', 'They have stayed exactly the same.', 'They have become more complex and efficient, often using machines and electronics.', 'They now only work by hand.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(680, 19, 1, 'What does it mean to \"identify different agricultural tools\"?', 'To name and describe tools for specific jobs like digging or gathering.', 'To guess what tools farmers use.', 'To only draw pictures of tools.', 'To only talk about new tools.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(681, 19, 1, 'What is an animal farm tool?', 'A tool used to help care for, feed, or manage farm animals.', 'A tool for playing with pets.', 'A tool for growing plants.', 'A tool for building houses.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(682, 19, 1, 'Which of these is a traditional animal farm tool?', 'An automatic milking machine.', 'A drone for monitoring animals.', 'An electronic fence.', 'A simple feed trough made of wood.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(683, 19, 1, 'What does technology help improve in animal farming tools?', 'Making animals sick.', 'Making animal care more efficient, safer, or less labor-intensive.', 'Making tools more difficult to use.', 'Making animals disappear.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(684, 19, 1, 'What does it mean to \"appreciate the role of technology in improving farming tools\"?', 'To ignore new tools.', 'To criticize modern inventions.', 'To understand and value how new tools make farming easier and better.', 'To only use old tools.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(685, 19, 1, 'What does \"innovation\" mean for farm tools?', 'New and improved methods or tools that change how tasks are done.', 'Old ways of doing things.', 'Copying existing tools.', 'Tools that are very small.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(686, 19, 1, 'What does \"maintaining farm tools\" mean?', 'Taking care of tools by cleaning, sharpening, and storing them properly.', 'Leaving tools outside in the rain.', 'Only buying new tools.', 'Using tools only once.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
(687, 19, 1, 'Which of these is a basic step in caring for farm tools?', 'Hiding them in a corner.', 'Cleaning them after each use.', 'Using them for wrong purposes.', 'Leaving them dirty.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:43:44'),
