(763, 19, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple guide for maintaining a shovel, what would be the most important instruction?', 'Leave it dirty after digging.', 'Use it for digging only.', 'Lend it to everyone without cleaning.', 'Clean it, dry it, and store it in a dry place after each use.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:51:19'),
(764, 19, 3, 'Think about developing problem-solving skills related to agricultural technology. If you had to design a new farm tool for a small community, what challenge would it most effectively help solve?', 'To make farming impossible.', 'To make tools very heavy.', 'To make crops grow in the dark.', 'To help manage pests without harmful chemicals.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:51:19'),
(765, 19, 3, 'Your class is discussing animal farm tools. Which statement best evaluates why technology is important for improving animal welfare on farms?', 'Technology is only for humans.', 'Technology makes animal farming harder.', 'Technology can provide better living conditions, feeding, and health monitoring for animals, leading to healthier livestock.', 'Animals don\'t need technology.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:51:19'),
(766, 19, 3, 'If you were asked to create a new, innovative animal farm tool for the future, what would be its main benefit?', 'To make animals disappear.', 'To only feed animals by hand.', 'To make animals run away.', 'To automate a difficult task like cleaning animal pens, making farm work easier and safer.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:51:19'),
(767, 19, 3, 'Think about improving these tools. If you had to design an interactive activity for students about improving animal farm tools, what would be the most effective way to engage their critical thinking?', 'Only show them pictures of old tools.', 'Ask them to invent a tool that solves a specific problem, like ensuring all animals get enough water.', 'Tell them that all tools are perfect.', 'Only talk about very big farms.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 09:51:19'),
(768, 19, 3, 'Your class is discussing maintaining farm tools. Which statement best evaluates why proper storage is a crucial basic step?', 'Storing tools doesn\'t matter.', 'Storing tools makes them dirty.', 'Proper storage protects tools from rust, damage, and loss, extending their lifespan.', 'Tools should always be kept outside.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:51:19'),
(769, 19, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple chart for younger children about caring for small garden tools, what key instruction would be most important?', 'Leave your tools in the garden.', 'Always share dirty tools.', 'Never use water on your tools.', 'Clean and dry your tools after using them.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 09:51:19'),
(770, 19, 3, 'Think about applying problem-solving skills to tool maintenance. If you had to design a \"Tool Care Checklist\" for farmers, what main question would be most important to help them ensure longevity?', 'Did I use my tool today?', 'Is my tool very old?', 'Is my tool dirty or broken, and do I need to clean or fix it?', 'How much did my tool cost?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 09:51:19'),
