(1086, 17, 1, 'What does \"cultural practice\" refer to for the Efik people?', 'Their ways of life, traditions, and ceremonies.', 'Their favorite sports.', 'Their weather patterns.', 'Their school subjects.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1087, 17, 1, 'Which of these is a unique cultural feature of the Efik people?', 'Boat making.', 'Ekpe masquerade and traditional dances.', 'Building tall buildings.', 'Ice sculpture.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1088, 17, 1, 'Who are the Gwari people mostly known as?', 'A coastal fishing group.', 'A farming community mostly found in Niger and Abuja areas.', 'A mountain tribe.', 'A desert nomad group.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1089, 17, 1, 'What is a traditional occupation of the Gwari people?', 'Farming and pottery.', 'Deep-sea fishing.', 'Mining for gold.', 'Teaching.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1090, 17, 1, 'What does \"identify the cultural heritage\" of a people mean?', 'To name and describe their traditions, customs, and way of life.', 'To ignore their history.', 'To focus only on their modern buildings.', 'To memorize their population.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1091, 17, 1, 'Who are the Ebira people?', 'An ethnic group mainly found in Kogi State.', 'A group in South Africa.', 'A fishing tribe from Lagos.', 'A community from the Middle East.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1092, 17, 1, 'What is one well-known cultural practice of the Ebira people?', 'Their colorful masquerade festivals.', 'Their desert farming methods.', 'Their ice carving festivals.', 'Their shipbuilding industry.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1093, 17, 1, 'What does it mean to \"identify characteristics of a people\'s history and culture\"?', 'To describe important features of their past and how they live.', 'To guess their language.', 'To ignore their way of life.', 'To only learn their school subjects.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1094, 17, 1, 'Which of these is true about the Nupe people?', 'They are known for beadwork, glass making, and brass work.', 'They are famous for desert exploration.', 'They specialize in ice fishing.', 'They are famous mountain climbers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1095, 17, 1, 'What is the significance of studying different Nigerian peoples like the Nupe?', 'It helps us understand Nigerias rich cultural diversity and history.', 'It only tells us about their weather.', 'It shows us their school curriculum.', 'It makes us forget our own culture.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1096, 17, 1, 'Who are the Idoma people?', 'An ethnic group mainly found in Benue State.', 'A group from Europe.', 'A fishing community from Rivers State.', 'A desert tribe from the Sahara.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1097, 17, 1, 'What cultural feature is the Idoma people known for?', 'Traditional music, colorful festivals, and oral storytelling.', 'Ice sculpture.', 'Mountain climbing.', 'Space exploration.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1098, 17, 1, 'Why is it important to learn about the history and culture of different Nigerian peoples?', 'To understand and respect Nigerias cultural diversity and unity.', 'To forget about the past.', 'To focus only on the present.', 'To avoid learning history.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1099, 17, 1, 'What does \"describe cultural practices\" mean in Social Studies?', 'To explain the ways of life, ceremonies, and traditions of a people.', 'To ignore cultural differences.', 'To only focus on modern technology.', 'To memorize population figures.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:26:18'),
(1100, 17, 2, 'The Northern Region was known for its large empires and Islamic traditions, while the Western Region had strong Yoruba kingdoms. How do these differences contribute to Nigeria\'s diversity?', 'They show that all regions were the same.', 'They made Nigeria less interesting.', 'They highlight the rich variety of governance systems, beliefs, and cultures within Nigeria.', 'They caused all regions to fight.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1101, 17, 2, 'The early regions of Nigeria had distinct climates and resources (e.g., North was drier, South had more forests). How did this influence their history and culture?', 'It made everyone live in the same way.', 'It caused all regions to trade only with each other.', 'It made their cultures identical.', 'It shaped their farming methods, traditional clothing, and types of homes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1102, 17, 2, 'Consider how a common language like Hausa became widespread in the Northern Region. How does this illustrate its historical and cultural significance?', 'It shows that no one spoke other languages.', 'It demonstrates how cultural practices like language can become a unifying part of a region\'s identity over time.', 'It means everyone was forced to speak Hausa.', 'It made the region smaller.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1103, 17, 2, 'If you were to study the history of a traditional festival in one of these regions, what would be the best way to develop critical thinking about its significance?', 'Research its origins, symbols, and how it has changed over time to understand its deeper meaning.', 'Only memorize the date of the festival.', 'Watch the festival without understanding its meaning.', 'Only talk to one person about the festival.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1104, 17, 2, 'The different early regions often traded unique goods with each other (e.g., agricultural products from the South, crafts from the North). How did this contribute to Nigeria\'s diversity?', 'It made them independent.', 'It allowed cultural exchange and the sharing of various products and ideas across regions.', 'It caused them to argue about trade.', 'It made them stop producing goods.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1105, 17, 2, 'Before 1967, Nigeria had a few large regions. How did creating smaller states contribute to unity among different ethnic groups?', 'It made the regions fight more.', 'It caused more problems.', 'It aimed to give different groups more say in their local governance and reduce regional dominance.', 'It made everyone speak the same language.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1106, 17, 2, 'The creation of states was meant to address issues like ethnic rivalry and uneven development. How does this analyze the reasons for state creation?', 'It shows leaders wanted more power.', 'It means the country was already perfect.', 'It was a simple decision.', 'It was a strategy to solve existing national problems and bring governance closer to the people.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1107, 17, 2, 'Imagine a country where one very large region dominates all decisions. How might creating smaller units (like states) solve group problems related to fairness?', 'It makes one region even more powerful.', 'It can give more groups a voice and a share in power, promoting fairness.', 'It makes decision-making slower.', 'It stops anyone from making decisions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1108, 17, 2, 'If you were involved in a project where a large group of friends needed to divide tasks fairly, how would critical thinking skills from learning about state creation help?', 'You would think about dividing the tasks into smaller, manageable parts that everyone agrees on for fairness.', 'You would force everyone to do what you want.', 'You would avoid dividing tasks.', 'You would let one person do all the work.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1109, 17, 2, 'Some states were created to protect minority ethnic groups. How did this contribute to problem-solving in the nation?', 'It made minority groups disappear.', 'It aimed to give them a sense of belonging and protection within their own state.', 'It created new problems for them.', 'It only helped the largest groups.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1110, 17, 2, 'The British set up their headquarters in specific towns like Calabar and Lokoja. How did choosing these locations affect their control over Nigeria?', 'It made it harder for them to control.', 'It helped them easily communicate with local leaders.', 'It allowed them to centrally manage their political, economic, and military activities in the region.', 'It helped them find new types of food.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1111, 17, 2, 'Lokoja is located where the River Niger and River Benue meet. How did its geographical location contribute to its significance as an administrative headquarters?', 'It made it difficult to travel.', 'It had no impact on its importance.', 'It was a good place for farming only.', 'Its central location and access to waterways made it a strategic point for trade and control.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1112, 17, 2, 'Imagine a town becoming an administrative headquarters. How would this impact the daily lives of the local people?', 'Their lives would not change at all.', 'They might experience new laws, increased trade, and different job opportunities.', 'They would become poorer.', 'They would lose all their cultural traditions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1113, 17, 2, 'The British built government buildings and houses for their officials in these headquarters. How does this illustrate their presence and power?', 'It suggests a permanent establishment of authority and control in these locations.', 'It shows they were just visiting.', 'It means they liked the local architecture.', 'It was just for decoration.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1114, 17, 2, 'If you were a British official working in an administrative headquarters in the 1890s, what would be your main task related to managing the protectorate?', 'Playing games all day.', 'Helping to collect taxes and enforce British laws.', 'Only learning local languages.', 'Building new types of houses for everyone.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1115, 17, 2, 'Lagos was a coastal city and a major port. How did this geographical feature analyze its significance as Nigeria\'s first federal capital?', 'It made Lagos a bad choice for a capital.', 'It made Lagos very hot.', 'Its location made it easy for trade and communication with the outside world, especially for colonial powers.', 'It stopped people from traveling.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1116, 17, 2, 'The decision to move the capital to Abuja involved a lot of planning and building in a new area. How does this illustrate the complexities of choosing a federal capital?', 'It shows that any city can be a capital.', 'It means the old capital was perfect.', 'It only affected a few people.', 'It highlights the huge effort and resources needed to create a new, central city from scratch.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1117, 17, 2, 'Imagine your community is asked to move because a new big project is being built. How would this cause ethical considerations related to displacement?', 'Everyone would be happy to move.', 'It raises questions about fairness, compensation, and how the move affects people\'s lives and livelihoods.', 'It means no one has to pay taxes.', 'It is always easy to move.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1118, 17, 2, 'Why did the builders of Abuja plan for it to be centrally located? How does this reasoning analyze the decision-making behind choosing a capital?', 'To ensure easier access and a sense of neutrality for all parts of Nigeria, fostering national unity.', 'It was just a random choice.', 'To make the city very big.', 'To make traveling harder.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1119, 17, 2, 'The move from Lagos to Abuja aimed to create a capital that was accessible to all Nigerians. How did this decision reflect the idea of unity in a diverse country?', 'It ignored diversity.', 'It showed a desire to create a symbol of national unity, equally accessible to all ethnic groups.', 'It made the country smaller.', 'It only helped people from one region.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1120, 17, 2, 'A community leader works tirelessly to build a new school for children, even when it\'s difficult. How does this demonstrate qualities that make them a hero?', 'It shows they are only trying to be famous.', 'It means they don\'t have other things to do.', 'It shows dedication, selflessness, and a commitment to their community\'s well-being.', 'It means the school is very big.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1121, 17, 2, 'A historical figure speaks out against an unfair law, even facing danger. How does this action impact their community?', 'It makes the community afraid.', 'It causes more unfair laws.', 'It makes no difference.', 'It inspires others to stand up for justice and brings about positive change.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1122, 17, 2, 'Imagine a situation where someone has to choose between keeping a promise to a friend and helping a stranger in urgent need. How does this present a moral dilemma?', 'The choice is very easy.', 'It is a conflict between two important values (loyalty vs. helping others).', 'It means one choice is clearly wrong.', 'It is not a real problem.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1123, 17, 2, 'A young person volunteers to clean up the local park every week. How does this discuss the impact of their actions on the community?', 'It inspires others to care for their environment and makes the park a more pleasant place for everyone.', 'It makes the park dirtier.', 'It means no one else helps.', 'It is only for their own benefit.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1124, 17, 2, 'A hero is known for always telling the truth, even when it\'s difficult. How does this analyze the impact of honesty as a heroic quality?', 'It makes people avoid them.', 'It builds trust and sets a positive example for integrity in the community.', 'It causes arguments.', 'It means they don\'t care about others\' feelings.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1125, 17, 2, 'The Nupe people are known for their traditional black-and-white striped clothing. How does this cultural practice shape Nigeria\'s identity?', 'It makes Nigeria look like other countries.', 'It means everyone must wear stripes.', 'It adds a unique visual and artistic element to the overall Nigerian cultural tapestry.', 'It is not important.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1126, 17, 2, 'The Oworo people live along riverine areas and have traditions related to fishing. How does this illustrate how geographical factors influence cultural practices?', 'It means they don\'t like other types of food.', 'It shows that fishing is easy.', 'It means they never leave the river.', 'Their customs are shaped by their environment and access to water resources.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1127, 17, 2, 'Some Nigerian cultures have complex traditional leadership systems. How does understanding these systems contribute to appreciating cultural diversity?', 'It makes governance harder.', 'It helps you appreciate the different ways communities have organized themselves throughout history.', 'It shows that all leadership is the same.', 'It means you only need one leader.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1128, 17, 2, 'If your school organized an activity where students learn a few words from different Nigerian languages (like Yala or Zuru), how would this demonstrate comprehension of cultural diversity?', 'It shows a willingness to engage with and appreciate the linguistic variety of Nigeria.', 'It makes the languages disappear.', 'It only helps you speak one language.', 'It means the languages are easy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1129, 17, 2, 'The diverse histories of the Yakurr and Kanuri peoples highlight different origins and developments. How does this shape Nigeria\'s identity?', 'It makes Nigeria\'s history simple.', 'It shows that Nigeria\'s identity is formed by a tapestry of unique stories and developments from various groups.', 'It means Nigeria has no identity.', 'It focuses only on one part of Nigeria.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1130, 17, 2, 'The Oro people have specific traditional masquerades. How does this cultural practice shape their identity and contribute to Nigeria\'s overall diversity?', 'It makes everyone ignore their culture.', 'It adds a unique artistic and spiritual element to Nigeria\'s rich cultural tapestry.', 'It is only for entertainment.', 'It means they are exactly like other groups.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1131, 17, 2, 'The Isoko people have unique proverbs and folklore. How does this cultural tradition help preserve their heritage?', 'It makes their language disappear.', 'It means no one understands them.', 'It only helps very old people.', 'These stories and sayings pass down wisdom, history, and values from generation to generation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1132, 17, 2, 'Imagine a situation where a younger generation wants to learn about their ancestral Awori traditions, but some old practices are no longer practical. How does this present a challenge for preserving cultural heritage while embracing modernity?', 'It means all old traditions must be forgotten.', 'It requires finding ways to adapt or celebrate traditions in a new, relevant context.', 'It means the culture is dying.', 'It is an easy problem to solve.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1133, 17, 2, 'If your class creates a project where students share songs from their own diverse cultural groups, how does this activity promote understanding of cultural diversity and Nigeria\'s identity?', 'It helps students appreciate the variety of Nigerian music and its role in cultural expression.', 'It only shows differences.', 'It makes music confusing.', 'It means everyone must sing the same song.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1134, 17, 2, 'The Itsekiri people historically lived near the coast and engaged in trade. How did their historical background influence their cultural practices and identity?', 'It made them live in the desert.', 'It shaped their customs, language, and economic activities around maritime trade and interaction with other groups.', 'It had no impact on their culture.', 'It meant they only ate land food.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1135, 17, 2, 'You visit the National Museum in Lagos. How does seeing old artifacts and photographs there help you understand Nigeria\'s past?', 'It shows only modern life.', 'It helps you ignore history.', 'It provides visual evidence and stories from past events and cultures.', 'It tells you about other countries.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1136, 17, 2, 'The Olumo Rock in Abeokuta was a refuge during wars. How does this explain its significance to Nigerian history?', 'It shows it\'s just a big rock.', 'It means people lived on it forever.', 'It is only a tourist attraction.', 'It highlights its historical role as a place of safety and strength during troubled times.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1137, 17, 2, 'If a historical building is falling apart, how does preserving it impact understanding our past?', 'It stops us from learning about the past.', 'By restoring it, we keep a tangible link to our history and can continue to learn from it.', 'It means the building is useless.', 'It makes the building look new.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1138, 17, 2, 'A historical site has old writings and carvings. How does critical thinking help you understand its impact on history and heritage?', 'You try to figure out what the writings mean and what stories they tell about the past.', 'You assume the writings are just drawings.', 'You only look at the building.', 'You ignore the carvings.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1139, 17, 2, 'The ancient city walls of Kano served as protection. How does learning about them shape our understanding of Nigeria\'s past?', 'It means people didn\'t need walls.', 'It shows how communities organized for defense and their ingenuity in building.', 'It makes the city seem small.', 'It only tells you about one city.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1140, 17, 2, 'The ancient city of Benin was known for its bronze artworks. How do these historical features shape our understanding of Nigerias cultural heritage?', 'They show that art is not important.', 'They prove that Benin was a small city.', 'They demonstrate a rich artistic tradition and advanced craftsmanship from the past.', 'They are just old pieces of metal.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1141, 17, 2, 'The walls of Kano City were built centuries ago for defense. How does this historical feature influence modern-day Kano?', 'They are no longer there.', 'They are just a tourist attraction.', 'They make the city unsafe.', 'They still stand as symbols of the city\'s history and planning, influencing its identity.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1142, 17, 2, 'If a historical site is being considered for new construction, how does this present a challenge for the balance between development and preservation?', 'It means the construction should always happen.', 'It requires a decision about whether to protect the historical site or build something new for modern needs.', 'It means the historical site is useless.', 'It helps people forget history.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1143, 17, 2, 'You visit a historical site where old tools are displayed. How does this feature explain the significance of the site to Nigeria\'s cultural heritage?', 'It shows how people lived and worked in the past, reflecting their skills and daily life.', 'It means tools are boring.', 'It is just a display of old items.', 'It tells you about modern tools.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1144, 17, 2, 'The practice of traditional chieftaincy continues in some parts of Nigeria, connected to ancient kingdoms. How does this historical feature influence modern-day Nigeria?', 'It has no impact today.', 'It shows how historical leadership structures continue to play a role in local governance and culture.', 'It means no new leaders are needed.', 'It is only about old traditions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:29:02'),
(1145, 17, 3, 'Your class is discussing how Nigeria\'s early regions shaped its history. Which statement best evaluates why understanding these regional differences is crucial for understanding Nigeria today?', 'The regions are not important anymore.', 'All of Nigeria is the same now.', 'It only matters if you live in one of those regions.', 'Understanding regional histories helps explain Nigeria\'s current diversity and challenges.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1146, 17, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple map of Nigeria showing its early regions, what key information would be most important to include for each region to show its cultural significance?', 'Only its modern cities.', 'The current population numbers.', 'A short description of its major ethnic groups or famous traditions.', 'Only its natural resources.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1147, 17, 3, 'Think about how cultural traditions are passed down. If you had to design an inquiry-based activity for younger students to learn about their own family\'s cultural traditions, what would be the most effective first step?', 'Ask them to read a very long book about history.', 'Tell them to guess their family traditions.', 'Ask them to ignore their family\'s past.', 'Encourage them to interview their grandparents or older family members about old stories, songs, or recipes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1148, 17, 3, 'Your class is discussing the significance of the first 12 states. Which statement best evaluates why their creation was a turning point in Nigeria\'s history?', 'It was just a small change.', 'It made Nigeria smaller.', 'It fundamentally reshaped Nigeria\'s political map and administrative structure, impacting national unity.', 'It solved all of Nigeria\'s problems forever.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1149, 17, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple historical map showing the creation of the first 12 states, what key information would be most important to include for each state?', 'The exact number of people in each state today.', 'The current capital city of each state.', 'The type of food eaten in each state.', 'The names of the 12 states and their original boundaries.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1150, 17, 3, 'Reflect on how the creation of states helped promote unity. If you had to design an inquiry-based activity for younger students about cooperation in a diverse group, what would be the most effective starting question?', 'How can different people with different ideas work together fairly to achieve a goal?', 'Why is it hard to work with others?', 'How can we make everyone exactly the same?', 'How can we make a group fair for only one person?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1151, 17, 3, 'Your class is discussing the significance of colonial administrative headquarters. Which statement best evaluates why towns like Calabar and Lokoja are important to study in Nigerian history?', 'They are just old towns, not important.', 'They show where the British lived in comfort.', 'They represent key points from which British colonial power was exercised and shaped Nigeria\'s early development.', 'They only remind us of bad times.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1152, 17, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple historical timeline about Nigeria\'s colonial headquarters, what key events would you include for Calabar and Lokoja?', 'The dates when people started living there.', 'The dates of local festivals.', 'The dates when modern buildings were built.', 'The years they were established as administrative headquarters and any major changes in their status.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1153, 17, 3, 'Think about critical thinking and historical events. If you had to design an inquiry-based activity for students about these headquarters, what question would be most effective for getting them to think deeply about the topic?', 'What colors were the buildings?', 'How many people lived there in 1900?', 'How did being an administrative headquarters change life for the people living in Calabar or Lokoja?', 'Which headquarters was the biggest?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1154, 17, 3, 'Your class is discussing why Nigeria chose Abuja as its capital. Which statement best evaluates the importance of a central location for a diverse country\'s capital?', 'A central capital is not important.', 'It only makes travel longer.', 'It helps all citizens feel equally represented and reduces the dominance of one region.', 'Only small countries need central capitals.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1155, 17, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple timeline of Nigeria\'s federal capitals, what would be the most important events to include?', 'The dates when new buildings were built in each city.', 'The dates of major festivals in each city.', 'The dates when famous people visited the capitals.', 'The dates when Lagos became capital, and when the capital was officially moved to Abuja.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1156, 17, 3, 'Think about ethical considerations related to displacement of communities. If your school needed to expand and had to move some local stalls, how would you design a plan that shows ethical consideration for the affected vendors?', 'Offer them new, fair locations and help with relocation costs.', 'Tell them to move immediately without help.', 'Ignore them and build anyway.', 'Give them no warning.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1157, 17, 3, 'Your class is discussing what makes someone a hero. Which statement best evaluates why courage is an essential quality for a hero or heroine?', 'Courage means never being afraid.', 'Courage means always winning.', 'Courage means acting bravely despite fear, which is often needed to face challenges and help others.', 'Courage is only for big people.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1158, 17, 3, 'If you were asked to create a \"Hero\'s Code\" for your community, what key action would be most important to include about impacting others positively?', 'Always think only of yourself.', 'Ignore problems around you.', 'Wait for someone else to act.', 'Speak up for fairness and help those in need.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1159, 17, 3, 'Reflect on the impact of heroes on their community. If you had to design a school play about a modern-day hero, what complex situation would you present for them to solve, showing a moral dilemma?', 'A hero who finds a lost toy.', 'A hero who wins a game easily.', 'A hero who always gets praise.', 'A hero who has to choose between personal fun and helping a struggling neighbor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1160, 17, 3, 'Your class is reflecting on the moral dilemmas faced by historical figures. Which statement best evaluates why these dilemmas make heroes more relatable?', 'Heroes should never have dilemmas.', 'Dilemmas show heroes are weak.', 'They show that heroes are real people who faced tough choices, making their actions more inspiring.', 'Dilemmas only make stories complicated.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1161, 17, 3, 'If you were asked to create a new award for a Nigerian hero, what key contribution would it celebrate for shaping Nigeria\'s development?', 'Building the biggest house.', 'Having the most money.', 'Being the fastest runner.', 'Inspiring unity, promoting education, or fighting for justice for all Nigerians.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1162, 17, 3, 'Think about learning from real-life examples. If you had to design an inquiry-based activity for younger students about a local hero, what would be the most effective starting point?', 'Asking them to research how the hero solved a specific community problem.', 'Telling them to only memorize the hero\'s name.', 'Asking them to draw a picture of the hero without learning about them.', 'Telling them that heroes are perfect.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1163, 17, 3, 'Your class is discussing the balance between preserving cultural traditions and embracing modernity. Which statement best evaluates why this balance is important for Nigeria\'s identity?', 'Modernity should replace all traditions.', 'Traditions should never change.', 'Balancing tradition and modernity allows Nigeria to keep its unique heritage while also growing and adapting to the modern world.', 'This balance is not important.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1164, 17, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple presentation about one of the Nigerian peoples discussed, what key cultural practice would you highlight to demonstrate its significance?', 'Only their modern jobs.', 'How many cars they own.', 'How much food they eat every day.', 'A traditional dance, a unique craft, or a special celebration.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1165, 17, 3, 'Think about how diverse cultures shape identity. If you had to design an interactive activity for a school cultural day to promote appreciation for the Jukun people, what would be the most effective way to engage students?', 'Have Jukun students teach a simple traditional game or song.', 'Only tell them to read a book about the Jukun.', 'Show a very long and complicated historical film.', 'Only talk about one historical fact.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1166, 17, 3, 'Your class is discussing the importance of cultural diversity in Nigeria. Which statement best evaluates why it\'s a strength, not a weakness?', 'Diversity causes too many problems.', 'It means everyone is different, which is confusing.', 'Cultural diversity enriches Nigeria with unique customs, arts, and perspectives, making it stronger and more interesting.', 'Unity is impossible with diversity.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1167, 17, 3, 'If you were asked to create a fun activity to demonstrate comprehension of different Nigerian cultures (like the Kanuri or Zuru), what would be the most effective interactive activity?', 'A quiz where students only guess answers.', 'A presentation where only the teacher talks.', 'An activity where students only learn about their own culture.', 'A \"Cultural Dress-Up\" day where students wear clothes from different groups and explain their meaning.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1168, 17, 3, 'Reflect on the balance between modernization and tradition. If you had to design a small community project to preserve a traditional craft (e.g., a specific type of weaving from the Yala people) while also making it relevant today, what would be the most effective approach?', 'Stop the craft entirely.', 'Only make products that are very old-fashioned.', 'Help artisans sell traditional designs with modern uses online.', 'Only teach the craft to adults.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1169, 17, 3, 'Your class is discussing preserving historical landmarks. Which statement best evaluates why preserving them is important for future generations?', 'Future generations don\'t care about the past.', 'Landmarks are only for old people.', 'Preserving landmarks ensures future generations can see, learn from, and connect with their heritage.', 'It\'s too expensive to preserve old sites.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1170, 17, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple visitor guide for a historical site, what key information would you highlight to explain its significance to cultural heritage?', 'Only the building materials.', 'The stories of people who lived there and the traditions they practiced.', 'How much money was spent building it.', 'The current weather at the site.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1171, 17, 3, 'Think about how historical landmarks shape our understanding of the past. If you had to design an activity for younger students to explore a local historical site, what would be the most effective way to help them connect with its history?', 'A guided tour focusing on stories and the daily lives of people who used the site.', 'Just give them a picture of the site.', 'Tell them to guess what happened there.', 'Let them play games that have nothing to do with the site.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1172, 17, 3, 'Your class is discussing how historical features shape cultural heritage. Which statement best evaluates the importance of preserving historical sites for a nation?', 'Historical sites are only for tourists.', 'Preserving sites is too expensive and slows down progress.', 'They are vital links to our past, helping us understand our roots and build a stronger national identity.', 'Modern buildings are always better than old ones.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1173, 17, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple educational tour for a local historical site, what key information would you highlight to explain its significance to cultural heritage?', 'Only the building materials.', 'The stories of people who lived there and the traditions they practiced.', 'How much money was spent building it.', 'The current weather at the site.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
(1174, 17, 3, 'Think about balancing development and preservation. If you had to design a new project near a historical landmark, what is the most important consideration to ensure the project respects the historical significance?', 'To build as fast as possible.', 'To make the new project as different from the landmark as possible.', 'To design the new project so it blends with and protects the historical landmark, perhaps using similar materials or styles.', 'To ignore the landmark and build what is needed.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 10:30:52'),
