(1316, 18, 2, 'You see a person trying to open car doors in a parking lot, even though the cars don\'t belong to them. How would you apply critical thinking to analyze this situation?', 'They are helping clean the cars.', 'They might be looking for their own car.', 'This is suspicious because they are trying to enter cars that are not theirs, which could be a sign of theft.', 'They are just playing a game.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1317, 18, 2, 'A stranger offers you candy and asks you to go with them. How would you analyze this situation to recognize it as suspicious and respond appropriately?', 'Take the candy and go with them.', 'Ask them if they have more candy.', 'Hide from them.', 'Politely refuse and quickly go to a trusted adult, realizing this is a common trick.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1318, 18, 2, 'You are walking alone and notice someone following you very closely. How should you respond appropriately to stay safe?', 'Stop and ask them why they are following you.', 'Run into a busy store or to a trusted adult, making noise if needed.', 'Keep walking slower so they catch up.', 'Hide in a dark place.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1319, 18, 2, 'Your parents have a special password for anyone picking you up from school. An unknown adult comes to pick you up and doesn\'t know the password. How does this help you apply problem-solving skills to analyze the situation?', 'It tells you this person is not safe to go with, and you should immediately go to a teacher.', 'It means your parents forgot to tell them.', 'You should teach them the password.', 'You should go home with them anyway.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1320, 18, 2, 'A child often sees a neighbor\'s dog barking loudly at a certain time each night. One night, the dog barks unusually and continuously. How might they apply critical thinking to consider this as a possible sign of suspicious behavior?', 'The dog is just playing.', 'The dog is just hungry.', 'The dog is mad at them.', 'The dog\'s unusual barking might signal something is wrong or suspicious in the neighborhood.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1321, 18, 2, 'Imagine you see someone trying to break into a neighbor\'s house while they are away. How would you apply critical thinking to decide what to report?', 'Ignore it, it\'s not your house.', 'Go over to see what\'s happening.', 'Realize this is a crime in progress and focus on details like what the person looks like, what they are doing, and if they have a car.', 'Yell at the person.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1322, 18, 2, 'You need to report a suspicious person you saw. How would you use clear communication to describe what they looked like?', 'Say \"They looked normal.\"', 'Say \"I saw someone, but I don\'t remember details.\"', 'Only say they were tall.', 'Describe their height, clothing, hair color, and any unique features clearly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1323, 18, 2, 'In a hypothetical scenario, you see an unfamiliar package left near your school gate. How would you practice problem-solving to report this safely?', 'Kick the package to see what\'s inside.', 'Tell a trusted adult immediately and avoid touching the package.', 'Open the package yourself.', 'Ignore the package and walk away.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1324, 18, 2, 'You see a lost child wandering alone in a busy area. How can you apply critical thinking to decide who to report this to?', 'Report it to a trusted adult, like a store employee, security guard, or police officer.', 'Report it to a child younger than you.', 'Report it to your friend first.', 'Report it to a stranger.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1325, 18, 2, 'You witness someone taking flowers from a public garden that are not theirs. How does reporting this to a trusted adult help ensure neighborhood safety?', 'It gets the person in trouble.', 'It helps maintain order and shows that community rules against petty crime are enforced.', 'It makes the garden look worse.', 'It means you don\'t like flowers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1326, 18, 2, 'You see a house on fire. How would you demonstrate how to use an emergency phone number in this situation?', 'Call your best friend first.', 'Wait for someone else to call.', 'Dial the fire emergency number and clearly state there is a fire and the address.', 'Run into the burning house.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1327, 18, 2, 'A friend has fallen and is hurt, and no adult is immediately nearby. How does staying calm help when you call an emergency number?', 'It makes the problem disappear.', 'It means you don\'t care about your friend.', 'It makes the operator talk faster.', 'It helps you remember what to say and speak clearly to the emergency operator.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1328, 18, 2, 'You are practicing making an emergency call. When the operator asks \"What is your emergency?\" how would you provide clear information?', 'Say \"I need help.\"', 'Say \"There\'s a person hurt at [give specific address].\"', 'Say \"I don\'t know.\"', 'Say \"I\'m just practicing.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1329, 18, 2, 'If you hear someone screaming for help from a neighbor\'s house, how would you recognize the importance of using an emergency phone number?', 'It indicates a possible dangerous situation that requires immediate police or rescue help.', 'It means someone is playing.', 'It means you should go help them alone.', 'It is just a loud noise.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1330, 18, 2, 'A role-play scenario is given: \"You see a dog running into a busy road.\" How would you apply understanding of emergency phone numbers?', 'Call your family.', 'Call the animal control emergency number or a trusted adult who can call them.', 'Try to catch the dog yourself.', 'Ignore the dog.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07');
INSERT INTO `exam_questions` (`question_id`, `subject_id`, `type`, `question`, `option1`, `option2`, `option3`, `option4`, `option5`, `feedback1`, `feedback2`, `feedback3`, `feedback4`, `feedback5`, `answer`, `marks`, `createdate`) VALUES
(1331, 18, 2, 'You feel angry because someone took your toy without asking. How can self-regulation help you act safely in this situation?', 'Yell loudly at the person.', 'Hit the person.', 'Take a deep breath and calmly explain that you don\'t like what happened, instead of reacting angrily.', 'Cry for a long time.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1332, 18, 2, 'A friend is sad because they lost their favorite book. How can empathy help you respond in a way that enhances their security (feeling cared for)?', 'Tell them it\'s their fault.', 'Laugh at them.', 'Ignore them.', 'Understand their sadness and offer comforting words or help them look for the book.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1333, 18, 2, 'Imagine a new student is quiet and looks lonely. How can your social skills contribute to their community safety (feeling welcome)?', 'By avoiding them.', 'By talking to them and inviting them to play, making them feel included and safe.', 'By making fun of them.', 'By ignoring them.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1334, 18, 2, 'A child realizes they feel very anxious before a school presentation. How does self-awareness contribute to their personal safety (managing stress)?', 'It allows them to recognize their feeling and take steps to calm down, like practicing breathing.', 'It makes them feel more anxious.', 'It means they don\'t care about the presentation.', 'It makes them forget their lines.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1335, 18, 2, 'A group of children is working on a team project, and one child is very motivated to finish well. How does this motivation contribute to safety in the group (ensuring good outcome)?', 'It makes others work less.', 'High motivation helps the group stay focused and work efficiently, reducing errors and ensuring a good outcome.', 'It makes the project harder.', 'It means they will always argue.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1336, 18, 2, 'A case study describes how a community worked together to prevent a series of thefts by setting up a neighborhood watch. How does this analyze how the challenge was handled?', 'It shows that only police can prevent theft.', 'It means the thefts continued.', 'It demonstrates that community collaboration and awareness can effectively deter crime.', 'It shows that nobody cared about the thefts.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1337, 18, 2, 'You learn about a case study where clear communication helped resolve a conflict that was threatening community safety. How can you apply problem-solving skills from this?', 'By arguing more loudly.', 'By ignoring misunderstandings.', 'By forcing your opinion on others.', 'By understanding that calm and clear talking can help prevent conflicts from escalating.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1338, 18, 2, 'A real-life example tells about a child who stayed calm and gave clear information during an emergency, which helped emergency services arrive quickly. How does this demonstrate understanding of emotional intelligence?', 'It shows the child was not scared.', 'It highlights how self-regulation (staying calm) and social skills (clear communication) are vital in emergencies.', 'It means the child was a superhero.', 'It shows the child only cared about themselves.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1339, 18, 2, 'Consider a security scenario where a group of friends needs to safely leave a dangerous area. How would applying critical thinking skills help them?', 'They would quickly assess the safest escape route and decide on the best course of action.', 'They would run without a plan.', 'They would panic and stay put.', 'They would wait for someone else to tell them what to do.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1340, 18, 2, 'A case study describes how a community organized a clean-up to prevent accidents caused by litter. How can you apply this problem-solving to a similar scenario in your school?', 'Ignore litter in your school.', 'Organize a similar clean-up or campaign to remove hazards and make your school safer.', 'Blame someone else for the litter.', 'Wait for adults to clean.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1341, 18, 2, 'You notice that there is a broken street light in your neighborhood, making it dark at night. How does this identify a community need related to safety?', 'It\'s just a small problem.', 'It means the street is better for playing hide-and-seek.', 'It creates a dark area where suspicious activities could occur, making the street less safe.', 'It only affects one house.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1342, 18, 2, 'Your friends decide to start a \"Safe Walk\" program where older students walk younger ones to school. How does this apply to making your community safer?', 'It makes walking take longer.', 'It shows that friends can make trouble.', 'It means younger students can\'t walk alone.', 'It provides a protective presence, reducing risks for younger children on their way to school.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1343, 18, 2, 'Imagine your community has a problem with speeding cars. How would you suggest a way to address this need to local leaders?', 'Ignore the speeding cars.', 'Suggest installing speed bumps or having more police presence to slow down traffic.', 'Ask everyone to drive faster.', 'Tell only your friends about the problem.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1344, 18, 2, 'During a simulated community meeting, your group needs to decide on safety rules for a local park. How would developing a basic safety plan with actionable steps help?', 'It helps organize practical rules like \"no littering\" or \"report broken swings\" to keep the park safe.', 'It means the park will never be used.', 'It will confuse everyone.', 'It is only a suggestion.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1345, 18, 2, 'A community organizes a \"Neighborhood Watch\" group. How does this demonstrate working together to make the community safer?', 'It means neighbors won\'t talk to each other.', 'It shows people taking collective action to monitor and protect their area.', 'It is just for show.', 'It makes the neighborhood look worse.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 12:53:07'),
(1346, 18, 3, 'Your class is discussing the importance of a neighborhood watch. Which statement best evaluates why a neighborhood watch is important for community safety?', 'It means police don\'t have to do their job.', 'It creates arguments among neighbors.', 'It encourages neighbors to work together, share information, and create a visible presence that deters crime.', 'It only helps the people who lead it.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1347, 18, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple poster for your neighborhood about reporting suspicious activities, what key message would be most effective?', 'Don\'t worry, accidents happen.', 'See something, say nothing.', 'Only police report suspicious things.', 'If it looks wrong, tell a trusted adult!', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1348, 18, 3, 'Think about community roles in ensuring neighborhood safety. If you had to design a \"Safety Superhero\" for your neighborhood, what would be their main power related to community safety?', 'The power to make all bad people disappear.', 'The power to inspire everyone to look out for each other and report anything unusual.', 'The power to build tall walls around the neighborhood.', 'The power to always know where criminals are hiding.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1349, 18, 3, 'Your class is discussing the importance of reporting suspicious behavior. Which statement best evaluates why it\'s crucial to report, even if you\'re not sure it\'s dangerous?', 'It\'s better to stay quiet and not cause trouble.', 'Only adults should report things.', 'Reporting helps authorities check things out, and it\'s better to be safe than sorry.', 'Reporting will always lead to big problems.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1350, 18, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple checklist for identifying suspicious behavior in your neighborhood, what key behavior would be most important to include?', 'People walking their dogs.', 'People talking loudly on their phones.', 'People sitting on a park bench during the day.', 'People looking into windows repeatedly and trying door handles.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1351, 18, 3, 'Reflect on how to stay safe and respond appropriately. If you had to design a role-play scenario to help younger students learn how to respond to a stranger offering a ride, what would be the most effective action for the child to demonstrate?', 'Running away and telling a trusted adult immediately.', 'Getting into the car quickly.', 'Asking the stranger for their name.', 'Standing still and waving.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1352, 18, 3, 'Your class is discussing hypothetical scenarios for reporting. Which statement best evaluates why staying calm is crucial when making a report?', 'Staying calm makes the situation disappear.', 'Staying calm means you don\'t care.', 'Staying calm helps you remember important details and communicate clearly to get help faster.', 'Staying calm is only for adults.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1353, 18, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple step-by-step guide for younger students on \"How to Report,\" what would be the most important first step?', 'Yell loudly.', 'Write down every single detail first.', 'Wait for the suspicious activity to stop.', 'Go to a trusted adult (parent, teacher, police).', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1354, 18, 3, 'Think about reporting suspicious activities to keep your neighborhood safe. If you had to design a \"Community Alert\" system for your neighborhood, what would be its main purpose?', 'To quickly share important safety information with trusted neighbors.', 'To make noises that scare animals.', 'To make a secret club for only a few people.', 'To only send funny messages.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1355, 18, 3, 'Your class is discussing emergency calls. Which statement best evaluates why providing your exact location (address) is the most important information during an emergency call?', 'It\'s not very important, they can find you.', 'It\'s important so they know who you are.', 'It helps the emergency services know exactly where to send help quickly.', 'It makes the call longer.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1356, 18, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple rule for using emergency phone numbers, what rule would be most effective?', 'Only call if it\'s very exciting.', 'Always call an emergency number, even if it\'s not a real emergency.', 'Never call unless an adult tells you to.', 'Only call 911/112/199 for true emergencies, and be ready to speak clearly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1357, 18, 3, 'Think about practicing making emergency calls through role-playing. If you had to design a role-play scenario for younger students about a small emergency (e.g., a lost pet), what would be the most important skill for them to demonstrate?', 'The ability to tell their name and the problem clearly to the operator.', 'How loudly they can shout.', 'How quickly they can hang up.', 'How well they can act scared.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1358, 18, 3, 'Your class is discussing how emotional intelligence enhances security. Which statement best evaluates why self-awareness is a fundamental component for personal safety?', 'Self-awareness means you are always worried.', 'Self-awareness is only about knowing your strengths.', 'Understanding your own feelings helps you recognize when you\'re in an unsafe situation or need help.', 'Self-awareness has no role in safety.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1359, 18, 3, 'If you were asked to create an example of how emotional intelligence can enhance community safety, what scenario would you provide?', 'A scenario where people ignore each other\'s feelings.', 'A scenario where leaders make decisions without listening to the community.', 'A scenario where everyone argues loudly.', 'A scenario where neighbors communicate calmly to resolve a dispute, preventing conflict.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1360, 18, 3, 'Reflect on personal experiences to understand the impact of emotional intelligence. If you had to design a peer-support activity for students who are feeling angry, what emotionally intelligent strategy would you emphasize for them to practice?', 'To shout their anger out loud.', 'To ignore their anger and pretend it\'s not there.', 'To take a \"cool-down\" break and talk about their feelings calmly with a trusted friend.', 'To start a fight.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1361, 18, 3, 'Your class is discussing how learning from case studies helps handle security challenges. Which statement best evaluates the value of analyzing past events for future safety?', 'Past events are not useful for the future.', 'Case studies are too complicated.', 'Analyzing past events helps us understand what works and what doesn\'t, so we can make better safety plans.', 'Every security challenge is totally new.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1362, 18, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple security plan for your school playground, based on real-life examples, what key step would you include to prevent common challenges?', 'Allow all children to play alone.', 'Encourage children to report bullying and set up clear rules for fair play.', 'Have no rules at all.', 'Let only the strongest children play.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1363, 18, 3, 'Reflect on how emotional intelligence can manage security challenges. If you had to design a school play about a security challenge, what emotionally intelligent action would be most important for the main character to demonstrate to resolve a conflict safely?', 'Shouting and arguing loudly.', 'Ignoring the feelings of others.', 'Staying calm and using empathy to understand others, then finding a peaceful solution.', 'Blaming someone else for the problem.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1364, 18, 3, 'Your class is discussing community safety. Which statement best evaluates why collaboration (working together) is crucial for building a safer community?', 'Only one person can make a community safe.', 'Collaboration makes safety plans too complicated.', 'When everyone works together, they can identify more needs and achieve bigger safety goals than individuals alone.', 'Community safety is not everyone\'s responsibility.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1365, 18, 3, 'If you were asked to create a new community safety initiative for your neighborhood, what would be the most effective actionable step?', 'Tell everyone to stay inside.', 'Ignore all safety concerns.', 'Only talk about safety in meetings.', 'Organize a weekly clean-up and a \"safe walking path\" map for children.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1366, 18, 3, 'Reflect on how you and your friends can work together. If you had to design a \"Community Helper\" award for your school, what quality would be most important to recognize in a student who contributes to a safer community?', 'Being the fastest runner.', 'Always complaining about problems.', 'Taking initiative to help others and actively participate in safety efforts.', 'Hiding from problems.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 12:54:33'),
(1367, 11, 1, 'What does the term \"environment\" refer to?', 'Only the animals in a place.', 'Only the buildings in a city.', 'Only the plants in a forest.', 'Everything that surrounds us, including living and non-living things.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1368, 11, 1, 'How can your environment influence your daily life?', 'By affecting the weather, the food you eat, or the games you play.', 'By deciding what TV shows you watch.', 'By choosing your friends for you.', 'By telling you when to sleep.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1369, 11, 1, 'Which of these is a way humans can impact (change) the environment?', 'Watching the clouds pass by.', 'Littering or planting trees.', 'Learning a new language.', 'Counting the stars at night.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1370, 11, 1, 'What does it mean to contribute positively to your environment?', 'To ignore all environmental problems.', 'To make more trash.', 'To do things that help keep it clean and healthy, like recycling.', 'To only talk about the environment.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1371, 11, 1, 'What does \"maintaining a clean and healthy environment\" involve?', 'Only cleaning your room.', 'Keeping air, water, and land free from pollution and disease.', 'Always buying new things.', 'Never going outside.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1372, 11, 1, 'What is often considered the basic unit of society?', 'A family.', 'A school.', 'A market.', 'A large city.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1373, 11, 1, 'Which of these is a role a child might have within a family?', 'To pay all the bills.', 'To help with chores and show respect.', 'To decide where everyone lives.', 'To cook all the meals.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1374, 11, 1, 'Why is it important to understand each family members role?', 'So you can boss everyone around.', 'So you know who gets more toys.', 'So everyone knows their responsibilities and how to support each other for harmony.', 'So you know only your own role.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1375, 11, 1, 'What does \"family harmony\" mean?', 'When family members never talk to each.', 'When family members always argue.', 'When everyone in the family is exactly the same.', 'When family members get along well, cooperate, and support each other.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1376, 11, 1, 'What does it mean to \"identify the different roles within a family\"?', 'To name and describe the specific jobs or responsibilities each person has.', 'To guess what each person does.', 'To draw pictures of family members.', 'To decide who has the most important role.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1377, 11, 1, 'What does the term \"beliefs\" refer to when talking about different cultures?', 'The ideas and convictions that people hold to be true, often about life, the world, or spirituality.', 'Only things that are proven by science.', 'Just opinions that don\'t matter.', 'Only things that are very old.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1378, 11, 1, 'What does it mean to \"appreciate the diversity of practices\"?', 'To only accept practices that are like your own.', 'To ignore other people\'s ways.', 'To dislike anything different.', 'To value and respect the wide variety of customs and ways of doing things that different cultures have.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1379, 11, 1, 'Why is it important to understand different beliefs and traditions?', 'To argue with people.', 'To help us be more respectful and live peacefully with others.', 'To make everyone believe the same thing.', 'To know who is right or wrong.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1380, 11, 1, 'Which of these is an example of a tradition?', 'A new game you just learned.', 'A rule that just started today.', 'A way of celebrating a holiday that has been done for many years by a group.', 'A piece of modern technology.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1381, 11, 1, 'What does it mean to \"identify various beliefs and traditions\"?', 'To name and describe different customs or ideas from different cultures.', 'To guess what someone believes.', 'To draw pictures of traditions.', 'To ignore different ways of life.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1382, 11, 1, 'What does responsible parenthood involve?', 'Only providing food.', 'Only giving toys.', 'Only telling children what to do.', 'Showing love, care, honesty, patience, and support to children.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1383, 11, 1, 'Which of these is a key aspect of being a responsible parent?', 'Showing patience and understanding.', 'Ignoring children\'s feelings.', 'Always being angry with children.', 'Never spending time with children.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1384, 11, 1, 'What does parental responsibility mean?', 'Parents only focusing on their own needs.', 'The duties and obligations parents have to care for and raise their children well.', 'Children taking care of their parents.', 'Parents letting children do whatever they want.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1385, 11, 1, 'Why is responsible parenting important for a child\'s growth?', 'It makes children independent too quickly.', 'It makes children always listen to parents.', 'It helps children feel safe, loved, and grow into happy, healthy individuals.', 'It only helps parents.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1386, 11, 1, 'What does it mean to \"identify key aspects of being a responsible parent\"?', 'To name and describe the important qualities that make a parent responsible.', 'To guess what parents should do.', 'To only think about what parents get.', 'To ignore parents\' duties.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1387, 11, 1, 'What does personal hygiene mainly refer to?', 'Practices that keep your body clean and healthy.', 'Only washing your clothes.', 'Only brushing your teeth.', 'Only eating healthy food.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1388, 11, 1, 'Which of these is a physical change that occurs during pre-adolescence (around 9-12 years old)?', 'Becoming much shorter.', 'Teeth always falling out.', 'Bones stopping growth.', 'Rapid growth spurts and body changes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1389, 11, 1, 'Why is personal hygiene important for overall health?', 'It helps you make more friends.', 'It helps prevent the spread of germs and diseases.', 'It makes you sleep faster.', 'It helps you learn new things.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1390, 11, 1, 'What is a main purpose of a personal hygiene checklist?', 'To remind you to play games.', 'To help you decide what to eat.', 'To ensure you remember and perform daily hygiene habits consistently.', 'To list your favorite things.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1391, 11, 1, 'What does it mean to \"identify physical changes\" during pre-adolescence?', 'To recognize and describe the new ways your body is growing and changing.', 'To guess what will happen.', 'To remember only one change.', 'To ignore changes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1392, 11, 1, 'What does responsible citizenship mean?', 'Only caring about yourself and your family.', 'Knowing all the laws by heart.', 'Just living in a country.', 'Being a member of a country or community and acting in ways that help it.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1393, 11, 1, 'Why is responsible citizenship important?', 'It helps the community stay strong and work well.', 'It makes everything easier for leaders.', 'It means everyone gets rich.', 'It helps people avoid their duties.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1394, 11, 1, 'What is cultural diversity?', 'When everyone in a community is exactly the same.', 'When a community has people from many different backgrounds, with different customs, languages, and beliefs.', 'When people only celebrate one holiday.', 'When people never share their ideas.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1395, 11, 1, 'What is the role of respect in a diverse community?', 'To make people hide their differences.', 'To cause arguments among people.', 'To help people understand and value each other\'s differences, leading to peace and cooperation.', 'To make some people feel less important.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1396, 11, 1, 'What does it mean to \"identify ways to actively contribute\" to one\'s community?', 'To list actions you can take to make your community better.', 'To only complain about community problems.', 'To wait for others to solve community problems.', 'To ignore community needs.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1397, 11, 1, 'Why is it important to choose good friends?', 'Good friends can influence you positively and help you make healthy choices.', 'So you always get what you want.', 'So you can play more games.', 'So you have someone to do your homework.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1398, 11, 1, 'What does negative influence mean?', 'When someone helps you do something good.', 'When someone is very quiet.', 'When someone is always happy.', 'When someone encourages you to do something harmful or wrong.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1399, 11, 1, 'What is self-discipline?', 'Always doing what others tell you.', 'The ability to control your own behavior and make good choices, even when it\'s hard.', 'Only listening to yourself.', 'Never setting rules for yourself.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1400, 11, 1, 'What does resilience mean in overcoming challenges?', 'Giving up easily.', 'Being afraid of problems.', 'The ability to bounce back and keep trying after difficulties or setbacks.', 'Always needing help from others.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1401, 11, 1, 'What does it mean to \"identify strategies to stay away from drug abuse\"?', 'To find and understand different ways or plans to avoid drug use.', 'To guess what to do.', 'To ignore advice.', 'To only talk about drugs.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1402, 11, 1, 'What is an accident?', 'An unexpected event that can cause injury or damage.', 'Something that always happens on purpose.', 'A planned event.', 'A type of game.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1403, 11, 1, 'Which of these is a common type of accident that can happen at home?', 'A car crash.', 'A plane crash.', 'A boat sinking.', 'A fall or a cut.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1404, 11, 1, 'What does prevention mean in the context of accidents?', 'Reacting to an accident after it happens.', 'Stopping accidents from happening in the first place.', 'Ignoring safety rules.', 'Making accidents worse.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1405, 11, 1, 'What does it mean to demonstrate basic first aid knowledge?', 'To only read about first aid.', 'To know someone who can do first aid.', 'To show you know how to give simple, immediate care for injuries.', 'To call an ambulance for every small scratch.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1406, 11, 1, 'What is the main goal of accident prevention?', 'To reduce injuries and keep people safe.', 'To make sure accidents are fun.', 'To understand how accidents happen.', 'To only prevent very big accidents.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1407, 11, 1, 'What is first aid?', 'The final medical treatment by a doctor.', 'A type of medicine.', 'A game played to help someone.', 'Immediate, temporary care given to an injured or sick person before professional medical help arrives.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1408, 11, 1, 'Why is prompt first aid important?', 'It can reduce the impact of an accident and sometimes save a life.', 'It makes the injury worse.', 'It means you don\'t need a doctor.', 'It makes the person feel tired.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1409, 11, 1, 'Which of these is a basic first aid step for a small cut?', 'Ignoring the cut.', 'Cleaning the wound.', 'Putting dirt on the cut.', 'Wrapping it tightly without cleaning.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1410, 11, 1, 'What does it mean to have a \"positive attitude towards accident victims\"?', 'To laugh at them.', 'To blame them for the accident.', 'To be supportive, empathetic, and helpful towards injured individuals.', 'To ignore them.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1411, 11, 1, 'What is the main goal of giving first aid?', 'To provide immediate care to prevent further harm and help the person until more help arrives.', 'To make someone famous.', 'To make a lot of noise.', 'To play with bandages.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:03:31'),
(1412, 11, 2, 'Imagine you live near a river. If people start throwing trash into it, how does this impact the environment?', 'It makes the river cleaner.', 'It helps the fish grow bigger.', 'It pollutes the water, harming animals and making it unsafe for humans.', 'It makes the river smell nicer.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1413, 11, 2, 'Your family decides to start a small garden to grow vegetables. How does this action positively contribute to your environment?', 'It makes the garden look colorful.', 'It uses up all the water.', 'It helps provide fresh food and can improve the local air quality.', 'It only helps the family.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1414, 11, 2, 'Consider a very hot climate. How might this environment influence the type of houses people build?', 'Houses would have very thick walls and no windows.', 'Houses would have many open windows and light materials to stay cool.', 'Houses would be built underground.', 'Houses would be made of ice.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1415, 11, 2, 'If your community organizes a \"Go Green\" club to plant trees, how does this activity analyze ways to positively contribute to the environment?', 'It shows that trees are not important.', 'It creates more work for everyone.', 'It demonstrates collective effort to improve air quality and provide habitats.', 'It only helps the club members.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1416, 11, 2, 'A factory releases smoke into the air every day. How does this action impact the environment, and why is it a negative impact?', 'It makes the air smell good.', 'It adds pollution to the air, which can harm living things and make people sick.', 'It means the factory is working hard.', 'It makes the sky look interesting.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1417, 11, 2, 'Imagine your younger sibling needs help with their homework. If you help them, how does this demonstrate responsibility toward a family member?', 'It shows you are smarter than them.', 'It means you are doing their homework for them.', 'It shows you don\'t have your own homework.', 'It shows you are caring and willing to support your family member.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1418, 11, 2, 'Your family is deciding where to go for a picnic, and everyone has different ideas. How can tolerance help achieve family harmony in this situation?', 'By insisting on your own idea only.', 'By listening to and respecting everyone\'s preferences, even if you don\'t fully agree.', 'By arguing until someone gives up.', 'By ignoring everyone\'s ideas.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1419, 11, 2, 'When there is a disagreement in your family about sharing toys, how can problem-solving skills contribute to family harmony?', 'By hiding all the toys.', 'By letting only one person decide.', 'By working together to find a fair solution that everyone can agree on.', 'By yelling until someone gets their way.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1420, 11, 2, 'A parent works hard to provide for the family, and a child helps with chores. How does this analyze the importance of each family member\'s role?', 'It demonstrates how different roles contribute essential support for the family\'s well-being and functioning.', 'It shows that only parents work hard.', 'It means children do not need to help.', 'It means everyone does the same job.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1421, 11, 2, 'Your older sibling teaches you how to ride a bike patiently. How does this demonstrate respect and responsibility within the family?', 'It means they don\'t have anything else to do.', 'It shows care, patience, and a willingness to teach and support a younger family member.', 'It proves they are better than you.', 'It means you must teach them something back.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1422, 11, 2, 'Your friend celebrates a different holiday than you do, with unique customs. How can you demonstrate respect for their beliefs?', 'By telling them their holiday is strange.', 'By ignoring their celebration.', 'By learning about their holiday and wishing them well.', 'By trying to make them celebrate your holiday instead.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1423, 11, 2, 'In some cultures, people greet elders by bowing slightly. How does this custom demonstrate how moral values (like respect for elders) shape daily life?', 'It shows that elders are weak.', 'It means people are forced to bow.', 'It is just a random movement.', 'It reflects a value of reverence for older people, influencing how daily interactions happen.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1424, 11, 2, 'A community lives in a mountainous region, and their traditions include unique dances that mimic climbing. How does this illustrate how geographical factors influence customs?', 'It shows they don\'t like flat land.', 'Their customs are influenced by the natural features of their environment.', 'It means their dances are very old.', 'It is just a coincidence.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1425, 11, 2, 'Two students have a disagreement because they have different ideas about fairness based on their family traditions. How can discussing strategies for resolving conflicts help them?', 'It helps them find a way to understand each other and find a solution that respects both traditions.', 'It would make them argue more.', 'It makes one person win.', 'It means they will never talk again.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1426, 11, 2, 'A teacher explains a historical event that led to a change in a cultural custom. How does this show how historical factors influence customs?', 'It means history is boring.', 'It demonstrates how past events can cause traditions to change or develop over time.', 'It shows that customs never change.', 'It means the custom is new.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1427, 11, 2, 'A parent makes sure their child goes to school every day and helps with homework. How does this demonstrate responsible parenting?', 'It shows the parent is strict.', 'It means the parent wants the child to be perfect.', 'It shows commitment to the child\'s education and future.', 'It means the parent has too much time.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1428, 11, 2, 'A child is feeling sad, and their parent listens carefully and offers comforting words. How does this reflect the parent\'s role in providing emotional support?', 'It means the parent is weak.', 'It shows the parent wants to make the child cry more.', 'It means the parent has nothing else to do.', 'It demonstrates empathy and active care for the child\'s feelings, which is part of responsible parenting.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1429, 11, 2, 'Imagine a family where parents always discuss problems calmly and work together to find solutions. How does this contribute to positive family dynamics?', 'It makes the family argue more.', 'It fosters open communication and mutual respect, strengthening family bonds.', 'It shows parents are afraid of problems.', 'It means problems never happen.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1430, 11, 2, 'A child receives love and care from their responsible parents. How does this impact the child\'s individual growth?', 'It can help the child feel secure, confident, and develop a positive outlook on life.', 'It makes the child selfish.', 'It makes the child dependent on parents forever.', 'It stops the child from learning.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1431, 11, 2, 'If parents teach their children the importance of honesty by always telling the truth themselves, how are they modeling responsible parenting?', 'They are just showing off.', 'They are demonstrating the value through their own actions, which children learn from.', 'They are trying to trick their children.', 'They are being too strict.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1432, 11, 2, 'You notice your hair is starting to get oily more quickly than before. How would you apply personal hygiene strategies to manage this change?', 'Stop washing your hair.', 'Use more hairspray.', 'Wash your hair more regularly with shampoo.', 'Wear a hat all the time.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1433, 11, 2, 'A friend complains about body odor after playing outside. How can you discuss a solution to this common hygiene issue?', 'Tell them to just ignore it.', 'Tell them to cover it with perfume.', 'Tell them to stop playing.', 'Suggest they take a shower or bath and use deodorant.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1434, 11, 2, 'Your teeth are growing in, and your dentist advises you to brush twice a day. How does this reflect the importance of hygiene for overall health?', 'It\'s just a suggestion for looking good.', 'Brushing regularly prevents cavities and gum disease, which contributes to good overall health.', 'It means you have to brush for a long time.', 'It stops you from eating candy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1435, 11, 2, 'If a student creates a checklist that includes \"brush teeth, shower, change clothes, wash hands,\" how does this demonstrate developing a personal hygiene strategy?', 'It is a systematic way to remember and practice daily self-care habits.', 'It means they are lazy.', 'It shows they are only trying to make a list.', 'It is a list of things to avoid.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1436, 11, 2, 'During pre-adolescence, some children\'s voices may begin to change slightly. How would you reflect on how to handle this physical change?', 'Try to stop your voice from changing.', 'Understand that it\'s a normal part of growing up and accept the changes patiently.', 'Stop talking altogether.', 'Only whisper.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1437, 11, 2, 'Imagine your local park is dirty. How could you actively contribute to improving it as a responsible citizen?', 'By complaining to your friends about the trash.', 'By waiting for someone else to clean it.', 'By organizing a clean-up day with friends and family, or by picking up litter yourself.', 'By throwing more trash.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1438, 11, 2, 'Your community has people from many different countries, and you learn about their holidays. How does this recognize the value of cultural diversity?', 'It shows that only your culture is important.', 'It helps you ignore other cultures.', 'It means you have to celebrate every holiday.', 'It shows appreciation for different traditions and enriches your understanding of the world.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1439, 11, 2, 'A student sees a new classmate who is struggling to understand a lesson. How can the student practice empathy and help solve this community issue (classroom as community)?', 'Ignore the classmate.', 'Understand the classmate\'s feelings and offer to help explain the lesson.', 'Make fun of the classmate.', 'Tell the teacher it\'s not their problem.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1440, 11, 2, 'If you see someone damaging public property (like drawing on a school wall), how can you actively contribute to improving your community?', 'Speak up against the action or report it to a trusted adult/authority.', 'Join them in damaging property.', 'Ignore it, as it\'s not your job.', 'Take a picture of the damage.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1441, 11, 2, 'A neighborhood experiences frequent power outages. How might a group of responsible citizens develop problem-solving skills to address this issue?', 'They would complain but do nothing else.', 'They might gather information, contact the power company, and collectively propose solutions.', 'They would move to another neighborhood.', 'They would rely only on candles.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1442, 11, 2, 'Imagine your friends always encourage you to study and participate in sports. How do they help you stay healthy and avoid negative influences?', 'They make you lazy.', 'They help you avoid drug abuse.', 'They provide positive peer pressure and encourage healthy activities.', 'They only care about themselves.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1443, 11, 2, 'A student sets a goal to read every day and sticks to it, even when they prefer to play. How does this demonstrate self-discipline?', 'It shows they have no fun.', 'It means they don\'t like reading.', 'It is only because someone is watching.', 'It highlights their ability to control their desire to play and focus on a good habit.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1444, 11, 2, 'You are offered an unknown pill by an older child. How would you apply strategies to stay away from drug abuse?', 'Take the pill to be polite.', 'Say \"No, thank you\" firmly, walk away, and tell a trusted adult.', 'Ask the older child for more pills.', 'Hide the pill.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1445, 11, 2, 'A child faces a challenge, fails, but then tries again with a different approach. How does this show courage and resilience?', 'It demonstrates their bravery to face a setback and determination to keep trying until they succeed.', 'It means they are lucky.', 'It shows they are stubborn.', 'It means they need more help.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1446, 11, 2, 'If you develop a habit of going to bed early every night, how does this significance of good habits contribute to staying healthy?', 'It makes you tired.', 'Good habits like regular sleep are important for your body and mind to function well.', 'It means you miss out on fun.', 'It only helps you to wake up early.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1447, 11, 2, 'A friend falls and gets a small cut on their arm. How would you apply first aid knowledge to help them?', 'Tell them to go home and wait.', 'Blow on the cut to make it better.', 'Clean the cut with water and soap, and cover it with a clean bandage.', 'Give them a sweet.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1448, 11, 2, 'Someone at the playground suddenly looks pale and dizzy. You remember first aid steps. How does calling for an adult\'s help quickly demonstrate prompt care?', 'It means you are scared.', 'It is only for very serious problems.', 'It makes the adult angry.', 'It ensures the person gets proper attention and prevents their condition from getting worse.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1449, 11, 2, 'Why is it important to offer reassurance to an injured individual?', 'It makes them feel weaker.', 'It can calm them down and help them feel safer, which is part of empathetic care.', 'It has no effect on their pain.', 'It makes them talk more.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1450, 11, 2, 'You see a classmate crying after falling down. How can you recognize a positive attitude towards an accident victim here?', 'By asking if they are okay and offering to help them up gently.', 'By laughing at them.', 'By ignoring them.', 'By telling them to stop crying.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1451, 11, 2, 'A small fire starts in the kitchen. Knowing to grab the fire extinguisher and call for adult help is a basic first aid step. How does this apply first aid knowledge for emergencies?', 'It means the child is a doctor.', 'It shows immediate, helpful actions taken to assist someone in need during an emergency.', 'It makes the situation worse.', 'It is too complicated for a child.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1452, 11, 2, 'You always put toys away after playing to prevent tripping hazards. How does this identify a way to prevent accidents through positive actions?', 'It means you don\'t like toys.', 'It shows laziness.', 'It is a proactive step to keep the environment safe and prevent falls.', 'It is only for cleanliness.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1453, 11, 2, 'A friend has a minor injury and is scared. How can you demonstrate victim care skills by offering support?', 'Tell them to run around.', 'Make them cry more.', 'Leave them alone.', 'Offer a kind word, help them to a safe spot, and stay with them until an adult arrives.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1454, 11, 2, 'Why is a positive attitude towards safety important for ensuring well-being for everyone?', 'It makes people ignore dangers.', 'It creates a culture of care and caution that protects everyone in the community.', 'It means safety is only for children.', 'It makes rules harder to follow.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1455, 11, 2, 'If a school implements a \"buddy system\" for walking to class, how does this recognize the role of support in accident prevention?', 'It encourages students to look out for each other, reducing chances of accidents.', 'It means students cannot walk alone.', 'It makes walking slower.', 'It is only for new students.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1456, 11, 2, 'A child helps an injured person by staying calm and calling for help. How does this demonstrate basic first aid and victim care skills?', 'It means the child is a doctor.', 'It shows immediate, helpful actions taken to assist someone in need during an emergency.', 'It makes the situation worse.', 'It is too complicated for a child.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:07:01'),
(1457, 11, 3, 'Your class is reflecting on the importance of maintaining a clean social environment. Which statement best evaluates why everyone\'s participation is crucial for this goal?', 'Only governments should worry about the environment.', 'One person\'s actions don\'t matter much.', 'Even small actions by many people add up to a big difference in keeping our environment healthy.', 'It\'s too difficult for everyone to help.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:09:36'),
(1458, 11, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple rule for your school to help students positively contribute to their environment, what rule would be most effective?', 'Don\'t pick up trash.', 'Always throw your litter on the ground.', 'Place all your waste in the correct recycling bins.', 'Use as much water as you want.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:09:36');
INSERT INTO `exam_questions` (`question_id`, `subject_id`, `type`, `question`, `option1`, `option2`, `option3`, `option4`, `option5`, `feedback1`, `feedback2`, `feedback3`, `feedback4`, `feedback5`, `answer`, `marks`, `createdate`) VALUES
(1459, 11, 3, 'Think about how our environment shapes who we are. If you had to design a new playground that helps children connect with and appreciate their local environment, what feature would be most important to include?', 'Only concrete and plastic structures.', 'Elements that incorporate natural materials like wood and rocks, or a small garden area.', 'A very tall fence around it.', 'Only artificial grass.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:09:36'),
(1460, 11, 3, 'Your class is discussing family harmony. Which statement best evaluates why tolerance is a crucial quality for family members?', 'Tolerance means always agreeing with everything.', 'Tolerance makes family life boring.', 'Tolerance allows family members to accept differences and resolve conflicts peacefully, leading to a happier home.', 'Tolerance is not needed in families.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:09:36'),
(1461, 11, 3, 'If you were asked to create a family chore chart, what design element would be most important to ensure everyone understands their responsibility and feels respected?', 'Only assign chores to one person.', 'Make the chart very small and hard to read.', 'Only list chores that nobody wants to do.', 'Clearly list each person\'s chores in a fair way, with spaces to check them off.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:09:36'),
(1462, 11, 3, 'Reflect on how tolerance and problem-solving contribute to family harmony. If you had to design a family game that teaches these values, what would be the most effective rule for the game?', 'A rule that encourages arguing.', 'A rule that says one person always wins.', 'A rule that requires players to listen to each other\'s ideas and compromise to reach a solution.', 'A rule that makes winning impossible.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:09:36'),
(1463, 11, 3, 'Your class is discussing strategies for resolving conflicts and building empathy. Which statement best evaluates why active listening is a crucial skill for conflict resolution?', 'Active listening means you just wait to talk.', 'Active listening makes conflicts worse.', 'Active listening is only for quiet people.', 'Active listening helps you truly understand the other person\'s point of view, which is the first step to finding a solution.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:09:36'),
