(1551, 20, 2, 'Why is it important to prevent water pollution in rivers and lakes? How does this help maintain environmental balance?', 'It makes the water taste bad.', 'It ensures there is enough clean water for animals, plants, and humans to survive, keeping nature healthy.', 'It means fish will disappear.', 'It only helps people.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1552, 20, 2, 'A problem-solving activity: \"How to reduce waste in your home.\" What solution would you propose to help the environment?', 'Use reusable bags and recycle paper and plastic.', 'Throw everything away quickly.', 'Buy new things every day.', 'Ignore your trash.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1553, 20, 2, 'A child sees a bird struggling in a plastic bag. How does this situation help them develop empathy towards protecting the environment?', 'It makes them laugh.', 'It helps them feel sad for the bird and understand how human actions harm animals.', 'It means the bird is old.', 'It has no effect.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1554, 20, 2, 'You see a used plastic bottle. How would you apply recycling to care for the environment?', 'Throw it in the regular trash.', 'Throw it on the ground.', 'Put it in a recycling bin so it can be made into something new.', 'Break it into small pieces.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1555, 20, 2, 'A group of neighbors organizes a clean-up of their local river. How does this demonstrate community involvement in environmental care?', 'It means they are just playing.', 'It only helps a few people.', 'It means the river will stay dirty.', 'It shows people working together to improve their shared environment.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1556, 20, 2, 'Your school has a problem with a lot of wasted paper. How would you demonstrate problem-solving skills related to this environmental issue?', 'Ignore the wasted paper.', 'Suggest ways to use less paper or set up a paper recycling box.', 'Blame others for wasting paper.', 'Ask for more paper.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1557, 20, 2, 'Why is it important to turn off lights when you leave a room? How does this promote environmental responsibility?', 'It makes the room dark.', 'It is just a rule.', 'It wastes electricity, which uses up energy and can harm the environment.', 'It saves energy and reduces harm to the environment.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1558, 20, 2, 'A child sees a leaking tap. How does fixing it (or telling an adult) identify a way to care for the environment?', 'It means the tap is old.', 'It prevents water waste, which is important for saving natural resources.', 'It is only a small problem.', 'It means the water is clean.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1559, 20, 2, 'You see bees flying from one flower to another. How does this illustrate the process of pollination?', 'It means the bees are playing.', 'It means bees like flowers.', 'It shows how bees carry pollen between flowers, helping them make seeds.', 'It makes the flowers disappear.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1560, 20, 2, 'A garden has many colorful flowering plants. How does this enhance the beauty of the environment?', 'It makes the garden look messy.', 'It makes the garden noisy.', 'It only helps plants grow.', 'It adds bright colors and pleasant smells, making the area more beautiful to see and enjoy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1561, 20, 2, 'Why is it important to water flowering plants regularly? How does this show basic plant care?', 'To make them very wet.', 'Water helps plants grow, stay strong, and produce beautiful flowers.', 'To make them grow faster.', 'To make them disappear.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1562, 20, 2, 'A problem-solving activity: \"How to attract more butterflies to a garden.\" What role of flowering plants would you use to find a solution?', 'Plant a variety of colorful flowers that butterflies like to visit for nectar.', 'Plant only green leaves.', 'Plant only one type of plant.', 'Remove all flowers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1563, 20, 2, 'You notice that a certain type of flowering plant always grows near a river. How does this explain the role of flowering plants in the environment?', 'It means the plant likes water.', 'It shows how plants adapt to and are part of different natural environments.', 'It means the river is very small.', 'It means the plant is lazy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1564, 20, 2, 'You want to draw a bright, sunny flower. How would you use colors to enhance its beauty?', 'Use dark, sad colors.', 'Use dull, grey colors.', 'Use bright, warm colors like yellow and orange to make it look cheerful.', 'Use only black.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1565, 20, 2, 'A problem-solving activity: \"How to make a flat drawing of a flower look round.\" What coloring technique would you apply?', 'Use only a pencil.', 'Draw very straight lines.', 'Use only one color.', 'Use shading techniques to show light and shadow, making it look 3D.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1566, 20, 2, 'You are designing a flower with petals that stand out. How would you apply contrasting colors to achieve this?', 'Make the petals the same color as the center.', 'Use a very light color for the petals and a very dark color for the center.', 'Use colors that blend softly.', 'Only use one color for the whole flower.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1567, 20, 2, 'A child draws a plant with a very rough stem. How would they develop basic coloring techniques to show this texture?', 'Use jagged or uneven lines and colors to suggest a rough surface.', 'Use smooth, even colors.', 'Use only very light colors.', 'Ignore the texture.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1568, 20, 2, 'A student creates a drawing of a fantasy flowering plant with swirling, multicolored petals. How does this express creativity and personal style?', 'It shows they are only copying.', 'It shows their unique imagination and how they like to draw.', 'It means the drawing is messy.', 'It means the plant is real.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1569, 20, 2, 'You are drawing a picture of a very fast car. How would you demonstrate how lines affect the appearance of artwork to show speed?', 'Use only slow, curved lines.', 'Use very thick, bumpy lines.', 'Use zig-zag lines or lines that seem to blur behind the car.', 'Use only straight, thin lines.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1570, 20, 2, 'A drawing of a calm, peaceful lake uses soft, smooth, curved lines. How does this analyze the emotional impact of these lines?', 'It makes the lake look angry.', 'It makes the lake look noisy.', 'It makes the lake disappear.', 'The smooth lines help to show a feeling of calm and quiet.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1571, 20, 2, 'You want to draw a picture of a happy, playful dog. How would you experiment with different types of lines to show its playfulness?', 'Use only straight, stiff lines.', 'Use bouncy, curved, and flowing lines to show movement and joy.', 'Use dark, sharp lines.', 'Use only one very thin line.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1572, 20, 2, 'If an artist draws a house using only straight, strong lines. How does this affect the appearance of the house?', 'It can make the house look stable and strong.', 'It makes the house look soft.', 'It makes the house look weak.', 'It makes the house look like its moving.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1573, 20, 2, 'A problem-solving activity: \"How to make a drawing look exciting.\" What type of lines would you experiment with?', 'Very quiet lines.', 'Wavy, zig-zag, or sharp, broken lines to show energy and drama.', 'Only straight lines.', 'Lines that make people feel sleepy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1574, 20, 2, 'You take a ball of clay and start pressing your thumb into the center, then gently squeezing the sides. How does this demonstrate the pinching method?', 'It shows you are playing.', 'It means the clay is too soft.', 'It is the basic action of shaping clay by creating a hollow with your thumb and fingers.', 'It makes the clay flat.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1575, 20, 2, 'A child wants to make a small cup with a smooth edge. How would developing fine motor skills help them with this?', 'By using their whole arm.', 'By doing it very fast.', 'By making the cup very big.', 'By carefully shaping the rim and smoothing the surface with their fingertips.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1576, 20, 2, 'You are making a clay animal, and its legs keep breaking off because the clay is too dry. How would you identify and solve this common problem?', 'Keep trying to attach the dry legs.', 'The clay is too dry; add a little water to make it more workable and stick better.', 'Make the legs much thicker.', 'Throw away the clay.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1577, 20, 2, 'A problem-solving activity: \"How to make a clay ball into a bowl.\" What pinching method principles would you apply?', 'Start with a ball, then press your thumb into the center and pinch the sides evenly to open it up.', 'Roll it into a long rope.', 'Cut it in half.', 'Just make it flat.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1578, 20, 2, 'A child creates a clay monster with three eyes and bumpy skin. How does this demonstrate creativity through clay modeling?', 'It means the monster is real.', 'It shows their unique imagination in creating a fantastical object.', 'It means the monster is scary.', 'It only uses a basic shape.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1579, 20, 2, 'You are making a tall pot using the coiling method. How do you use the coils to build the height?', 'By throwing them together.', 'By making them very small.', 'By stacking them one on top of another and smoothing the joins.', 'By cutting them into flat pieces.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1580, 20, 2, 'A students coiled pot starts to crack as it dries. How would you identify this challenge and suggest how to overcome it?', 'The clay is too wet.', 'The pot is too big.', 'The pot is too colorful.', 'The coils might not have been joined well; try scoring and slipping them.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1581, 20, 2, 'Why is it important to smooth the joins between the coils as you build a clay object?', 'To make the object look rough.', 'To ensure the coils stick strongly together and the object doesnt break easily.', 'To make the object shiny.', 'To make the object fall apart.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1582, 20, 2, 'A problem-solving activity: \"How to make a coiled pot stand straight.\" What would you apply to overcome this challenge?', 'Keep the walls thick and even, and allow each section to firm up before adding more coils.', 'Make the coils very thin.', 'Make the pot lean to one side.', 'Add water all the time.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1583, 20, 2, 'A child creates a clay sculpture of their favorite animal using the coiling method. How does this demonstrate creativity?', 'It means the animal is real.', 'It shows their unique ability to form a complex shape by building with clay coils.', 'It means the animal is very big.', 'It is only a basic shape.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1584, 20, 2, 'You are turning a folk tale about a clever tortoise into a drama sketch. How would you identify the key elements of the folk tale?', 'Only remember the name of the tortoise.', 'Ignore the storys meaning.', 'Understand the main characters, the setting (where it happens), and the main problem and solution in the story.', 'Only focus on the ending.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1585, 20, 2, 'A group of students are working together to write a script from a folk tale. How does this collaborative work help them create a drama sketch?', 'It makes the work harder.', 'It means only one person does the work.', 'It means they will argue.', 'They share ideas for characters, dialogue, and scenes to build the play together.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1586, 20, 2, 'A character in your drama sketch needs to show they are very scared. How would you express different emotions through acting?', 'By laughing loudly.', 'By using trembling voice, wide eyes, and shaky body movements.', 'By standing still and silent.', 'By singing a happy song.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1587, 20, 2, 'Why is it important to have many rehearsals before staging a drama sketch?', 'To help actors remember their lines and movements, and make the performance smooth and clear.', 'To make the play longer.', 'To make actors tired.', 'To make the audience laugh.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1588, 20, 2, 'A problem-solving activity: \"How to adapt a long folk tale into a short drama sketch.\" How would you apply understanding of components?', 'Add more long parts to the story.', 'Focus on the main characters and the most important events, cutting out less important parts.', 'Make it longer.', 'Add many new characters.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1589, 20, 2, 'A play needs to show a forest. How would the set design team prepare for this?', 'By drawing trees on paper.', 'By singing a song about trees.', 'By building fake trees, painting a forest background, and adding leaves on the stage.', 'By inviting real animals.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1590, 20, 2, 'The actors rehearse their lines many times. How does this demonstrate teamwork in a plays production?', 'It means they are lazy.', 'It makes the play longer.', 'It only helps one actor.', 'It shows that all actors must work together to learn their parts and deliver a smooth performance.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1591, 20, 2, 'Why is it important for the lighting designer to understand the plays mood?', 'To make the lights very bright.', 'To make the stage dark.', 'So they can use lights to create feelings (like scary or happy) for the audience.', 'To hide the actors.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1592, 20, 2, 'A problem-solving activity: \"How to make sure the audience can hear all actors clearly.\" What role or task would you focus on?', 'Sound (making sure microphones work or actors speak loudly).', 'Costumes.', 'Set design.', 'Lighting.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1593, 20, 2, 'A child helps to move props (objects on stage) during a scene change. How does this action contribute to a plays production?', 'It means they are playing.', 'It shows their role in making sure the stage is ready for the next part of the story.', 'It only makes noise.', 'It means they dont like acting.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1594, 20, 2, 'You see a dress made from Adire fabric with special patterns. How does this illustrate the cultural significance of traditional fabrics?', 'It means the fabric is new.', 'It means the fabric is boring.', 'The patterns often tell a story or symbolize something important in the culture.', 'It is only for parties.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1595, 20, 2, 'A modern fashion designer creates clothes using Aso Oke fabric for a new collection. How does this demonstrate how traditional fabrics can be integrated into modern fashion?', 'It means Aso Oke is old-fashioned.', 'It makes the fabric expensive.', 'It ignores the fabrics cultural meaning.', 'It shows how designers can use traditional materials in new, stylish ways for todays clothes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1596, 20, 2, 'Why is the craftsmanship (skill in making things) of traditional fabrics important to appreciate?', 'It means anyone can make them.', 'It shows the great skill and effort put into creating beautiful and complex designs.', 'It makes them cheaper.', 'It means they are made quickly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1597, 20, 2, 'If you see someone wearing a traditional Nigerian dress at a special event, how does this reflect its role in Nigerian heritage?', 'It shows pride in cultural roots and helps keep traditions alive.', 'It means they do not like modern clothes.', 'It is only for old people.', 'It makes the event longer.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1598, 20, 2, 'A problem-solving activity: \"How to make a simple garment using traditional fabric patterns.\" How would you apply knowledge of traditional fabrics?', 'Ignore the patterns.', 'Choose a traditional pattern (like from Adire) and find a way to include it in a simple dress design.', 'Only use plain fabric.', 'Copy a foreign design exactly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1599, 20, 2, 'You want to design a traditional dress for a special celebration. How would you identify elements of Nigerian traditional dress designs to include?', 'By looking at foreign dresses.', 'By choosing a modern fabric.', 'By looking for traditional patterns, specific colors, or flowing shapes from a Nigerian culture.', 'By only drawing a simple circle.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1600, 20, 2, 'A designer sketches a dress with patterns inspired by the Efik peoples traditional clothing. How does this illustrate creating a traditional dress design using cultural inspiration?', 'It means the dress is for everyday wear.', 'It means the dress is very plain.', 'It is only about colors.', 'It shows how cultural elements can be used as ideas for new designs.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56');
INSERT INTO `exam_questions` (`question_id`, `subject_id`, `type`, `question`, `option1`, `option2`, `option3`, `option4`, `option5`, `feedback1`, `feedback2`, `feedback3`, `feedback4`, `feedback5`, `answer`, `marks`, `createdate`) VALUES
(1601, 20, 2, 'Why is it important to learn about the cultural significance of traditional dress?', 'To make fun of old clothes.', 'To appreciate the stories, history, and values woven into the clothing.', 'To know which dress is most expensive.', 'To ignore old traditions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1602, 20, 2, 'A problem-solving activity: \"How to make a traditional dress more comfortable for modern wear.\" What elements of design would you consider?', 'Make it very heavy.', 'Keep it exactly the same as old designs.', 'Think about adapting the fabric or adding practical features like softer linings or different fasteners.', 'Make it look very strange.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1603, 20, 2, 'A child creates a drawing of a dress with patterns inspired by their grandmothers traditional clothes. How does this reflect the importance of cultural heritage in fashion?', 'It shows they only like old things.', 'It highlights how personal and family heritage can inspire modern creative work.', 'It means the drawing is messy.', 'It is only a drawing.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:27:56'),
(1604, 20, 3, 'Your class is discussing nature drawing. Which statement best evaluates why taking time to observe nature carefully is crucial for good drawing?', 'Observing makes drawing boring.', 'You don\'t need to look closely at nature.', 'Good observation helps you see details and shapes, making your drawings more accurate and beautiful.', 'Drawing quickly is always better.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1605, 20, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple drawing that shows the beauty of a garden, what drawing technique would be most effective to make it look colorful and lively?', 'Only use gray colors.', 'Draw only one small flower.', 'Draw only straight lines for all plants.', 'Use bright, varied colors and different types of plants and flowers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1606, 20, 3, 'Think about developing critical thinking and problem-solving skills in art. If you had to design a \"Nature Artist\" award for a student, what quality would be most important to recognize?', 'Being able to think about how to draw tricky parts of nature (like a bird\'s wing) to make them look just right.', 'Drawing very fast.', 'Using only one type of pencil.', 'Only copying other people\'s drawings.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1607, 20, 3, 'Your class is discussing why we should care about our environment. Which statement best evaluates why everyone\'s participation is crucial for environmental protection?', 'Only adults should protect the environment.', 'One person\'s actions don\'t matter.', 'Even small actions by many people add up to big positive changes for a healthier planet.', 'Environmental protection is too hard.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1608, 20, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple rule for your school to protect the environment, what rule would be most effective?', 'Always waste water.', 'Never throw trash in bins.', 'Ignore overflowing bins.', 'Turn off lights and fans when you leave a classroom.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1609, 20, 3, 'Think about analyzing environmental issues and proposing solutions. If you had to design a \"Green Solutions\" project for your community, what would be the most important problem-solving skill to demonstrate?', 'Blaming others for problems.', 'Identifying a local environmental problem (like litter) and proposing practical steps to clean it up.', 'Ignoring the problem.', 'Making problems worse.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1610, 20, 3, 'Your class is discussing environmental care. Which statement best evaluates why everyone\'s actions (big or small) are crucial for the environment?', 'Only big actions matter.', 'One person cannot make a difference.', 'Even small actions by many people, like recycling or saving water, add up to big positive changes.', 'Environmental care is too hard for kids.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1611, 20, 3, 'If you were asked to create a new school activity to promote environmental awareness, what would be the most effective activity?', 'A game about wasting water.', 'A \"Recycle Challenge\" where students collect materials to recycle.', 'An activity where nobody talks about the environment.', 'An activity where students learn to litter.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1612, 20, 3, 'Think about demonstrating responsibility. If you had to design a \"Green Pledge\" for your classroom, what would be the most important promise to make for caring for the environment?', 'To only complain about pollution.', 'To only think about your own trash.', 'To always try to reduce waste and save resources like water and electricity.', 'To ignore environmental problems.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1613, 20, 3, 'Your class is discussing flowering plants. Which statement best evaluates why flowering plants are crucial for our ecosystem (nature\'s balance)?', 'They are only pretty.', 'They are only useful for humans.', 'They provide food for animals and help produce oxygen, which are vital for life on Earth.', 'They make the environment complicated.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1614, 20, 3, 'If you were asked to create a drawing to appreciate the beauty of flowering plants, what key features would you emphasize?', 'Only green leaves.', 'Only the stem.', 'Only the roots.', 'The unique shapes of petals, bright colors, and how they attract insects.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1615, 20, 3, 'Think about basic knowledge of plant care and pollination. If you had to design a \"Plant Care Guide\" for younger children, what would be the most important advice about how to help a plant grow?', 'Give it enough sunlight, water, and good soil, and don\'t pick all its flowers.', 'Never give it water.', 'Only talk to the plant.', 'Keep it in the dark.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1616, 20, 3, 'Your class is discussing how colors and patterns enhance artwork. Which statement best evaluates why experimenting with colors and patterns is crucial for artists?', 'Experimenting makes art look bad.', 'It\'s only for experienced artists.', 'It allows artists to discover new ways to make their artwork more beautiful and expressive.', 'Colors and patterns don\'t matter much.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1617, 20, 3, 'If you were asked to create a beautiful artwork of a flowering plant showing depth, what coloring technique would be most important to apply?', 'Only outlines.', 'Only flat colors.', 'Only drawing very small.', 'Shading to create light and shadow, making parts look closer or further away.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1618, 20, 3, 'Think about artistic challenges. If you had to design a \"Flower Artist\" award for a student, what quality related to applying critical thinking and problem-solving would be most important to recognize?', 'Being able to think about how to draw a tricky flower petal or leaf to make it look just right.', 'Drawing the fastest.', 'Only coloring inside the lines.', 'Never making mistakes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1619, 20, 3, 'Your class is discussing lines in art. Which statement best evaluates why experimenting with lines is crucial for artists?', 'Experimenting with lines wastes time.', 'All lines are the same.', 'Experimenting helps artists discover new ways to show feelings, movement, and shapes in their drawings.', 'Only famous artists use different lines.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1620, 20, 3, 'If you were asked to create an artwork that shows the feeling of anger using only lines, what type of lines would be most effective?', 'Soft, gentle lines.', 'Smooth, flowing lines.', 'Very thin, light lines.', 'Sharp, jagged, or thick, dark lines.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1621, 20, 3, 'Think about how different types of lines affect artwork. If you had to design a \"Line Master\" award for a student, what quality related to using lines would be most important to recognize?', 'Being able to use different kinds of lines to show various emotions and appearances in their drawings.', 'Drawing lines very quickly.', 'Drawing only straight lines perfectly.', 'Making lines disappear.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1622, 20, 3, 'Your class is discussing clay modeling. Which statement best evaluates why the pinching method is a great way for beginners to start?', 'It\'s too messy.', 'It\'s too complicated.', 'It uses a simple, natural hand motion that helps beginners understand basic clay shaping.', 'It only makes small objects.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1623, 20, 3, 'If you were asked to create a simple object using the pinching method, what object would be most effective to demonstrate its basic principles?', 'A very complex vase.', 'A flat slab of clay.', 'A very tall sculpture.', 'A small, hollow pot or a pinch pot.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
(1624, 20, 3, 'Think about solving common problems in clay modeling. If you had to design a \"Clay Doctor\" checklist for fixing dry clay, what would be the most important advice?', 'Add a little water at a time and knead gently to rehydrate.', 'Bake the clay immediately.', 'Throw away dry clay.', 'Leave dry clay alone.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-01 13:36:46'),
