(2333, 41, 2, 'If you find a lost wallet with money, what should you do to show integrity?', 'Keep the money and throw the wallet away.', 'Share the money with friends.', 'Hide it and pretend you never saw it.', 'Return it to the owner or a teacher.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2334, 41, 2, 'Your friend asks you to lie for them. How does integrity guide your response?', 'Refuse and explain why honesty matters.', 'Agree to lie to avoid conflict.', 'Laugh and ignore the request.', 'Tell a different lie to cover for them.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2335, 41, 2, 'How did Nelson Mandela show integrity?', 'By always putting himself first.', 'By avoiding challenges.', 'By fighting for fairness even when it was hard.', 'By ignoring injustice.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2336, 41, 2, 'If your friend gets a new toy you wanted, what would a content person do?', 'Cry and demand the same toy.', 'Be happy for your friend.', 'Steal the toy.', 'Enjoy your own toys.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2337, 41, 2, 'How does contentment help with friendship?', 'It makes you want everything your friends have.', 'It helps you appreciate your friends without jealousy.', 'It encourages you to compete with friends.', 'It makes you ignore your friends.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2338, 41, 2, 'Zara was happy with her old backpack while others had new ones. What does this show?', 'She didn\'t care about school.', 'She wanted to make others feel bad.', 'She was practicing contentment.', 'She was too poor to buy a new one.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2339, 41, 2, 'If a content person sees their neighbor with a new car, what might they think?', '\"I must get a better car immediately.\"', '\"I\'ll damage their car.\"', '\"I\'m happy with my working bicycle.\"', '\"I\'ll stop talking to them.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2340, 41, 2, 'How can contentment reduce corruption?', 'By making people want more money.', 'By helping people be satisfied with honest earnings.', 'By encouraging jealousy.', 'By making people work less.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2341, 41, 2, 'What happens when a leader lacks contentment?', 'They share resources fairly.', 'They might steal public funds.', 'They help everyone equally.', 'They work harder.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2342, 41, 2, 'If you set a goal to read a book every week and stick to it even when you prefer to play, which attribute of discipline are you showing?', 'Respect for Authority.', 'Time Management.', 'Perseverance.', 'Self-Control.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2343, 41, 2, 'Imagine a football team that always arrives late to practice and doesn\'t follow the coach\'s instructions. This lack of discipline could lead to what for the team?', 'Winning more games easily.', 'Becoming very popular.', 'Chaos and poor performance.', 'Achieving their goals quickly.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2344, 41, 2, 'How does good time management, a part of discipline, help you achieve your goals?', 'It makes you waste more time.', 'It helps you put off tasks until later.', 'It ensures you have enough time to do what is important.', 'It makes you forget what your goals are.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2345, 41, 2, 'If a student stands up for a classmate who is being bullied, even when others are afraid to, what type of courage are they showing?', 'Physical Courage.', 'Religious Courage.', 'Moral Courage.', 'Academic Courage.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2346, 41, 2, 'Imagine a firefighter running into a burning building to save people. Which type of courage are they mainly demonstrating?', 'Physical Courage.', 'Religious Courage.', 'Moral Courage.', 'Emotional Courage.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2347, 41, 2, 'How does having compassion (caring for others) help someone be courageous?', 'It makes them more afraid.', 'It helps them ignore other people\'s problems.', 'It helps them understand the pain of others and act to help them.', 'It makes them selfish.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2348, 41, 2, 'The lesson mentions that federalism protects local cultures. How does it do this?', 'By forcing everyone to follow one culture.', 'By allowing states to make decisions that fit their unique local needs and traditions.', 'By stopping cultural celebrations.', 'By making all cultures the same.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2349, 41, 2, 'Which of these is a responsibility of the Federal Government in Nigeria?', 'Defending the country and managing its currency.', 'Providing local sanitation services.', 'Managing local schools.', 'Running state hospitals.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2350, 41, 2, 'Imagine students from different Nigerian states bringing their unique cultural items to celebrate Unity Day. This story shows how federalism helps Nigeria by:', 'Making all cultures disappear.', 'Forcing one culture on everyone.', 'Making different cultures argue more.', 'Respecting and bringing together diverse identities.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2351, 41, 2, 'If a new health center is being built in your town, and the Federal, State, and Local governments all help out, what does this show?', 'How governments share power and work together to meet needs.', 'That governments don\'t need to cooperate.', 'That only one level of government is important.', 'That building projects are easy and need no help.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2352, 41, 2, 'Building roads within a state is usually the main responsibility of which government level?', 'Federal Government.', 'Local Government.', 'State Government.', 'International Government.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2353, 41, 2, 'Which type of power means that both the Federal and State governments can make laws on the same topic, like transportation?', 'Exclusive Powers.', 'Residual Powers.', 'Shared Powers.', 'Concurrent Powers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2354, 41, 2, 'If a judge makes a decision in court without showing any favor to one side, what attribute of the Rule of Law are they showing?', 'Transparency.', 'Justice.', 'Equality Before the Law.', 'Impartial Judges.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2355, 41, 2, 'When laws are clear and known to everyone, so people understand what is right and wrong, which attribute of the Rule of Law is being demonstrated?', 'Justice.', 'Equality.', 'Impartiality.', 'Transparency.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2356, 41, 2, 'Stealing from a shop is an example of what type of action that goes against the Rule of Law?', 'A way to promote trust.', 'A punishable offense.', 'A good way to solve problems.', 'A way to show fairness.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2357, 41, 2, 'If a group of citizens gathers peacefully to protest an unfair decision made by the government, what way to protect human rights are they using?', 'Legal Protection.', 'Community Support.', 'Peaceful Protests and Advocacy.', 'Ignoring the problem.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2358, 41, 2, 'When civil society groups help people whose rights have been violated, what kind of support are they providing?', 'Only financial support.', 'Only legal advice.', 'Community Support.', 'Medical treatment.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2359, 41, 2, 'Imagine you learn about a situation where someone\'s right to speak freely was taken away. If you feel strongly about this and want to help, which emotional intelligence skill would you most likely use?', 'Self-awareness.', 'Self-regulation.', 'Time management.', 'Empathy (understanding their struggle).', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2360, 41, 2, 'If a local organization sets up a free training program to teach people new skills for jobs, which problem-solving strategy are they using?', 'Government Action.', 'Community Efforts.', 'Education and Skills Training.', 'Youth Advocacy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32');
INSERT INTO `exam_questions` (`question_id`, `subject_id`, `type`, `question`, `option1`, `option2`, `option3`, `option4`, `option5`, `feedback1`, `feedback2`, `feedback3`, `feedback4`, `feedback5`, `answer`, `marks`, `createdate`) VALUES
(2361, 41, 2, 'You see a social media post about families in your city who don\'t have enough food. If you feel motivated to help and share the post to make others aware, which emotional intelligence component are you showing?', 'Self-Motivation.', 'Critical Thinking.', 'Self-Management.', 'Empathy and Advocacy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2362, 41, 2, 'Imagine your local community organizes a food drive to collect food for families who are struggling. What kind of problem-solving strategy is this?', 'Government Action.', 'Innovation.', 'Community Efforts.', 'Education and Skills Training.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2363, 41, 2, 'If your school makes sure that students with different learning needs get the special support they require to succeed, which important value is the school promoting?', 'Discrimination.', 'Equality only.', 'Human rights for some.', 'Fairness.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2364, 41, 2, 'You witness a new student being left out of a game because of their background. If you then speak up and invite them to join your group, which action for social justice are you taking?', 'Educating Yourself.', 'Getting Involved.', 'Speaking Up for What\'s Right.', 'Ignoring the situation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2365, 41, 2, 'When students from different backgrounds work together on a project, learning about each other\'s cultures and respecting their differences, which emotional intelligence component are they developing?', 'Self-awareness.', 'Self-regulation.', 'Social skills and conflict resolution.', 'Internal motivation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2366, 41, 2, 'If you use what you learned about \"good citizenship\" in Social Studies to help organize a fundraiser for a local charity, what are you doing?', 'Ignoring the needs of your community.', 'Waiting for others to help instead of acting.', 'Thinking only of your own interests.', 'Actively contributing positively to your community.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2367, 41, 2, 'You learned about different social problems like poverty and unemployment in Social Studies. When you start to think about what you personally could do to help, what are you demonstrating?', 'Taking active responsibility for change.', 'Indifference towards others\' struggles.', 'Lack of interest in social issues.', 'Blaming others for the problems.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2368, 41, 2, 'Imagine you see someone being treated unfairly, and you remember what you learned about social justice and human rights. If you then decide to speak up calmly and politely, which Social Studies concept are you applying?', 'Only history facts.', 'Only geography skills.', 'Social justice and human rights.', 'Economic theories.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:14:32'),
(2369, 41, 3, 'How would you design a school campaign to promote integrity?', 'Reward students for cheating.', 'Ignore bad behavior.', 'Encourage breaking small rules.', 'Create posters about honesty and host role-playing activities.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-09 09:36:07'),
(2370, 41, 3, 'How could you help a classmate who is always jealous of others?', 'Tell them to steal what they want.', 'Ignore their feelings.', 'Teach them games to make them forget.', 'Talk about being grateful for what they have.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-09 09:36:07'),
(2371, 41, 3, 'How would you teach younger students about contentment?', 'Create a \"gratitude jar\" to appreciate what they have.', 'Show them expensive toys they can\'t have.', 'Tell them to never share.', 'Complain about things you don\'t have.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-09 09:36:07'),
(2372, 41, 3, 'Your class wants to raise money for a charity, but students are struggling to stay organized and meet deadlines. What is one effective way to use discipline to help your class achieve this goal?', 'Create a clear plan with deadlines and assign specific roles to keep everyone accountable.', 'Give up because it\'s too hard.', 'Tell everyone to just do whatever they want.', 'Only let one person do all the work.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-09 09:36:07'),
(2373, 41, 3, 'Think about a small act of courage you could show in your daily life, like speaking up about something unfair. What is one specific plan you could make to show this courage, and how might it make a positive difference?', 'Practice what you will say and then politely speak to the right person about the issue.', 'Complain about the unfairness without doing anything.', 'Ignore the unfair situation and hope it changes.', 'Expect someone else to fix the problem for you.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-09 09:36:07'),
(2374, 41, 3, 'If you were designing a new way to help your state government work better with the Federal Government on something like improving education, what would be one important idea you would suggest?', 'Make the state government ignore federal education rules.', 'Stop all communication between the state and federal levels.', 'Encourage more meetings and joint planning sessions between state and federal education leaders.', 'Let only the federal government decide everything about education.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:36:07'),
(2375, 41, 3, 'Imagine your community needs a new primary school. How could the three levels of government (Federal, State, Local) work together to make sure this school gets built effectively and benefits the students?', 'Only the Federal Government should decide and pay for everything.', 'The Local Government should ignore the State and Federal Governments.', 'The levels should cooperate, with each contributing based on their responsibilities (e.g., Federal funds, State oversight, Local land/needs).', 'Each level should build its own separate school without talking to others.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:36:07'),
(2376, 41, 3, 'Think about a time when someone broke a rule or law in your school. How could applying the Rule of Law (like fairness and consequences) help solve the problem and make the school community better?', 'By ignoring the rule-breaker completely.', 'By punishing only certain students for the same offense.', 'By having clear rules and fair consequences that apply to everyone equally.', 'By letting students make up their own rules as they go.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-09 09:36:07'),
(2377, 41, 3, 'Think about a human rights issue that you care about, like the right to education for all children. What is one practical step you and your classmates could take in your community to raise awareness or help protect this right?', 'Make fun of children who can\'t go to school.', 'Organize a \"school supplies drive\" to help less fortunate children get materials for learning.', 'Tell people that education is not important.', 'Ignore the problem completely.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-09 09:36:07'),
(2378, 41, 3, 'Your school wants to help address the problem of unemployment in your area. What is one new and creative idea or project your school could start to help young people gain skills or find job opportunities?', 'Stop teaching subjects that lead to jobs.', 'Create a \"student business fair\" where students can show and sell things they make.', 'Tell students not to worry about jobs after school.', 'Reduce career counseling services for students.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-09 09:36:07'),
(2379, 41, 3, 'Imagine your community has a problem where people are sometimes treated unfairly because of their background. What is one creative way your class could organize an event or activity to promote unity and help fight discrimination in your community?', 'Organize a \"Diversity Day\" where everyone shares their culture and learns from each other respectfully.', 'Tell people to stay away from each other to avoid problems.', 'Make everyone dress exactly the same to hide differences.', 'Only allow people from one background to participate in community events.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-09 09:36:07'),
(2380, 41, 3, 'Based on all the Social Studies lessons, what is one new and impactful way you could use your knowledge to make a positive change in your school or local community, and why do you think it would work?', 'Do nothing and just hope things get better on their own.', 'Start a campaign to raise awareness about a social issue you care about and propose solutions to your school leaders.', 'Complain about problems to your friends without suggesting any ideas.', 'Focus only on your own academic achievements and ignore community issues.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-09 09:36:07'),
