(3080, 36, 3, 'Why is the \"folding technique\" particularly useful for making paper crafts like a kite or a greeting card, as opposed to other craft methods?', 'It requires no materials at all.', 'It produces crafts that are impossible to decorate.', 'It is the only way to add color to paper.', 'It allows for the creation of 3D shapes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-14 12:54:59'),
(3081, 36, 3, 'Imagine you are creating a collage to convey the feeling of a busy city. Which approach to using your materials would be most effective in achieving this, and why?', 'Using only plain, solid colored paper to keep it simple.', 'Carefully cutting out and layering various images and textures from magazines to create a sense of chaos and detail.', 'Gluing down only a single large image to represent the entire city.', 'Avoiding the use of any glue to make the city appear unstable.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-14 12:54:59'),
(3082, 36, 3, 'You are tasked with creating a lightweight but sturdy three-dimensional object for a school project. Why would Paper Mache\' be a good choice for this project compared to other materials?', 'It allows for creative shaping and becomes firm when dry.', 'It is heavy and easily breaks.', 'It is very expensive and hard to find.', 'It can only be used for flat, two-dimensional artworks.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-14 12:54:59'),
(3083, 36, 3, 'You want to design a unique piece of jewelry using various materials. How could you combine different materials listed (like seeds, straw, and bottle tops) with beads to create an original and culturally inspired design?', 'By only using beads and nothing else.', 'By randomly gluing all materials together without a plan.', 'By strategically arranging and stringing these diverse materials with beads to create a rich texture and pattern that reflects cultural motifs.', 'By melting all the materials into a single, uniform mass.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-14 12:54:59'),
(3084, 36, 3, 'You want to create a mosaic that captures a vibrant sunset. How would you choose and arrange your materials to best convey the changing colors and light of a sunset?', 'By using only black and white pieces to create a stark contrast.', 'By selecting a wide range of warm-toned pieces (reds, oranges, yellows) and arranging them to blend gradually, mimicking the sky.', 'By using only very large, irregularly shaped pieces.', 'By throwing pieces onto the surface randomly without a specific color scheme.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-14 12:54:59'),
(3085, 36, 3, 'You are asked to compose a short, simple tune that is easy to remember. Which two fundamentals of music would be most critical to focus on to achieve this goal effectively?', 'Timbre and Texture, as they are the most complex.', 'Pitch and Melody, as a clear tune relies on distinct notes in a memorable sequence.', 'Form and Harmony, as they are too advanced for a simple tune.', 'Quality and Rhythm, as they are not relevant to memorability.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-14 12:54:59'),
