(3088, 36, 3, 'Imagine you are teaching someone to play the recorder. What would be the most effective way to help them understand the connection between covering holes and producing different notes?', 'Just tell them to blow randomly.', 'Demonstrate how covering different combinations of holes changes the pitch and let them experiment.', 'Give them a very complex piece to play immediately.', 'Tell them to only listen to others play without trying themselves.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-14 12:54:59'),
(3089, 36, 3, 'Consider a situation where a community is facing a challenge. How could music be effectively used to bring people together and address the challenge?', 'By playing very quiet music that no one notices.', 'By creating songs that highlight divisions within the community.', 'By playing music that only one person enjoys.', 'By composing and sharing music with themes of unity and overcoming adversity', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', 0, '2025-07-14 12:54:59'),
(3090, 36, 3, 'Why is the audience considered an important \"person involved\" in drama and theatre, even though they don\'t perform?', 'They are only there to criticize.', 'Their reactions and presence contribute to the live experience and energy of the performance.', 'They have no impact on the performance at all.', 'They are only there to sell tickets.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', 0, '2025-07-14 12:54:59'),
(3091, 36, 3, 'Consider a drama that addresses a serious social issue, like poverty. How might this drama effectively combine its functions to achieve a significant impact on the audience?', 'By providing information about poverty, educating the audience on its causes', 'By only entertaining the audience and ignoring the issue.', 'By simply presenting facts without any emotional content.', 'By making the audience feel uncomfortable without offering any insights.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 0, '2025-07-14 12:54:59'),
(3092, 36, 3, 'You are creating a short drama scene about a peaceful forest. How would you effectively use the elements of \"Stage\" and \"Sound\" to convey this atmosphere to the audience?', 'Use bright, chaotic lights and loud, jarring noises.', 'Use a cluttered stage with no specific lighting, and only silence.', 'Design a simple, naturalistic stage setting with soft, green lighting and incorporate sounds of birds chirping and gentle breezes.', 'Have the actors describe the forest verbally without any visual or auditory support.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-14 12:54:59'),
(3093, 36, 3, 'You are asked to write a short play that makes the audience feel uplifted and joyful. Which form of drama would you choose, and what kind of plot elements would you include?', 'Tragedy, with a sad ending and serious themes.', 'A documentary, focusing solely on historical facts.', 'Comedy, with a humorous plot, and lighthearted characters.', 'A serious drama, with no element of humor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', 0, '2025-07-14 12:54:59'),
