(117, 19, 4, 'Lesson 1', '', 'Big Question: What does agriculture mean, and how does it shape our world?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n- Define Agriculture.\n\r\n- Identify the different components of agriculture, including crop cultivation, animal rearing, and the processing and selling of agricultural products.\n\r\n- Understand the importance of agriculture in their community and everyday life.\n\r\n- Develop critical thinking and problem-solving skills related to agricultural practice.', '<b>Agriculture</b>: The practice of farming, including growing crops and rearing animals\n<b>Crop</b>: Farm animals raised for food or other products\n<b>Fertilizer</b>: A substance added to soil to help plants grow\n<b>Sustainability</b>: Practices that maintain resources without depleting them', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K1pTmoP4t40', '2025-05-25 22:02:04'),
(118, 19, 4, 'Lesson 2', '', 'Big Question: How does agriculture impact every part of our lives?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n- Understand the meaning of agriculture and its role in providing food, medicine, and raw materials.\n\r\n- Identify various sources of food, medicine, and materials that come from agriculture.\n\r\n- Explore how technology and sustainable practices are transforming agriculture.\n\r\n- Appreciate the cultural and economic significance of agriculture.', '<b>Agriculture</b>: The practice of growing crops and raising animals for food, materials, and other products\n<b>Precision Farming</b>: Using technology to improve crop production and efficiency\n<b>Biotechnology</b>: The use of technology to enhance plant properties for better health and productivity\n<b>Sustainable</b>: Using resources in a way that maintains their availability for future generations', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dX3teqbSK5Q', '2025-05-25 22:02:04'),
(119, 19, 4, 'Lesson 3', '', 'Big Question: What does agriculture mean, and how does it shape our world?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Define agriculture and its significance.\n\r\n2. Identify innovative agricultural practices in Nigeria.\n\r\n3. Describe how technology improves farming and animal rearing.\n\r\n4. Develop critical thinking about modern agricultural challenges and solutions.', '<b>Agriculture</b>: The practice of growing crops and raising animals for food and other products\n<b>Innovation</b>: A new idea or method that improves something\n<b>Technology</b>: The use of scientific knowledge for practical purposes\n<b>Sustainability</b>: Using resources in a way that ensures they are available for future generations\n<b>Data Analytics</b>: Using data to make informed decisions', '', '', '', '2025-05-25 22:02:04'),
(120, 19, 4, 'Lesson 4', '', 'Big Question: What secrets lie beneath the soil, and how does understanding them help farmers grow better crops?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Identify and describe the three main types of soil: clay, sandy, and loamy.\n\r\n2. Understand the importance of soil health and how it affects crop growth.\n\r\n3. Explain modern techniques for soil enrichment and their benefits.\n\r\n4. Use a soil sensor to measure soil moisture and nutrient levels.', '<b>Soil</b>: The top layer of the earth where plants grow\n<b>Clay Soil</b>: A type of soil that is sticky and holds water well\n<b>Sandy Soil</b>: A type of soil that is loose and drains quickly\n<b>Loamy Soil</b>: A fertile soil that holds water, drains well, and is rich in nutrients\n<b>Fertility</b>: The ability of soil to support plant growth\n<b>Compost</b>: Decayed organic material used as a plant fertilizer', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9A86zPS0S0Y', '2025-05-25 22:02:04'),
(121, 19, 4, 'Lesson 5', '', '', '<b>Soil</b>: The top layer of the earth where plants grow\n<b>Fertility</b>: The ability of soil to provide nutrients to plants\n<b>Nutrients</b>: Substances that provide nourishment essential for growth\n<b>Erosion</b>: The process of soil being worn away by wind or water\n<b>Compost</b>: Decayed organic material used as a plant fertilizer', '', '', '', '2025-05-25 22:02:04'),
(122, 19, 4, 'Lesson 6', '', '', '<b>Fertility</b>: The ability of soil to support plant growth\n<b>Compost</b>: A mixture of organic materials used to enrich soil\n<b>Mulch</b>: Material spread over soil to retain moisture and improve fertility\n<b>Crop Rotation</b>: Growing different crops in succession on the same land\n<b>Biochar</b>: Charcoal used as a soil amendment', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FuYSWC8ufss', '2025-05-25 22:02:04'),
(123, 19, 4, 'Lesson 7', '', '', '<b>Tool</b>: A device used to perform a task (e.g., cutlass)\n<b>Innovation</b>: A new idea or method that improves something (e.g., modern tractor)\n<b>Efficient</b>: Performing tasks in the best possible way with the least waste\n<b>Technology</b>: The use of scientific knowledge for practical purposes (e.g., drones in farming)\n<b>Maintenance</b>: The process of keeping something in good condition through regular care', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FvStqIBiRaE', '2025-05-25 22:02:04'),
(124, 19, 4, 'Lesson 8', '', '', '<b>Tool</b>: An instrument used to do a job\n<b>Innovation</b>: A new idea or method\n<b>Maintenance</b>: The act of keeping something in good condition\n<b>Ergonomic</b>: Designed to be comfortable and easy to use\n<b>Durable</b>: Able to withstand wear or damage', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vXa86nFnDCw', '2025-05-25 22:02:04'),
(125, 19, 4, 'Lesson 9', '', '', '<b>Soil Fertility</b>: The ability of soil to provide nutrients to plants\n<b>Compost</b>: Decayed organic material used as a plant fertilizer\n<b>Erosion</b>: Process of soil being worn away by wind or water\n<b>Nutrients</b>: Substances that provide nourishment essential for growth\n<b>Modern</b>: Relating to the present or recent times as opposed to the remote past', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CuYz-wUytSM', '2025-05-25 22:02:04'),
(126, 19, 4, 'Lesson 10', '', '', '<b>Maintain</b>: Keep something in good condition\n<b>Rust</b>: A reddish-brown substance that forms on metal when it gets wet and is left outside\n<b>Sharpen</b>: Make the edge of a tool or blade sharp\n<b>Oil</b>: A liquid used to prevent rust and keep metal parts smooth\n<b>Modern</b>: Relating to the present or recent times, especially as opposed to the past', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2hejwOKDYHg', '2025-05-25 22:02:04'),
(127, 7, 4, 'Lesson 2', '', 'Big Question: How can we keep our homes safe and clean?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Identify the importance of keeping the home clean and safe.\n\r\n2. List common household cleaning tools and their uses.\n\r\n3. Demonstrate simple cleaning routines and safety practices.\n\r\n4. Practice responsibility and teamwork in maintaining home hygiene.', '<b>Cleanliness</b>: Being clean and keeping things clean\n<b>Hygiene</b>: Practices that keep you and your surroundings healthy\n<b>Disinfect</b>: To clean something to remove germs\n<b>Waste</b>: Unwanted or leftover materials\n<b>Sanitation</b>: Keeping places free from dirt, germs, and waste', '', '', '', '2025-05-25 22:29:39'),
(128, 7, 4, 'Lesson 3', '', 'Big Question: How do we take care of our bodies through cleanliness?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Explain the meaning of personal hygiene.\n\r\n2. Identify parts of the body that need regular care.\n\r\n3. Demonstrate personal hygiene practices like bathing, tooth brushing, and hand washing.\n\r\n4. Reflect on the benefits of good hygiene for personal health and social relationships.', '<b>Hygiene</b>: Keeping your body clean to stay healthy\n<b>Bathing</b>: Washing your body\n<b>Tooth brushing</b>: Cleaning your teeth\n<b>Grooming</b>: Keeping your body and clothes neat and clean\n<b>Health</b>: Being free from illness or injury', '', '', '', '2025-05-25 22:29:39'),
