(134, 2, 4, 'Lesson 3', '', 'Big Question: How do colours and textures enhance the beauty of our art?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Identify primary and secondary colours and explain how they are created.\n\r\n2. Explore warm and cool colours and their emotional impact.\n\r\n3. Create colour wheels and use them in artwork.\n\r\n4. Understand texture and how to create it in art using different materials.', '<b>Primary Colours</b>: Red, yellow, and blue\n<b>Secondary Colours</b>: Colours made by mixing two primary colours\n<b>Warm Colours</b>: Colours like red, orange, and yellow that feel hot\n<b>Cool Colours</b>: Colours like blue, green, and purple that feel cold\n<b>Texture</b>: The surface quality of an object or artwork', '', '', '', '2025-05-25 22:29:29'),
