(145, 17, 4, 'Lesson 2', '', 'Big Question: Who are our ancestors and what can we learn from them?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Define ancestors and heritage.\n\r\n2. Identify examples of Nigerian ancestral stories or figures.\n\r\n3. Appreciate ancestral wisdom and values.\n\r\n4. Create a family heritage tree or presentation.', '<b>Ancestors</b>: People in your family who lived long ago\n<b>Heritage</b>: Important traditions passed down from the past\n<b>Culture</b>: The beliefs, art, and way of life of a group\n<b>Custom</b>: A usual way of behaving or doing something\n<b>Genealogy</b>: The study of family history', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v5KL9sMzh8s', '2025-05-25 22:29:59'),
(146, 17, 4, 'Lesson 3', '', 'Big Question: How did early humans live and survive?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Describe the life of early humans (hunter-gatherers).\n\r\n2. Identify early tools and survival techniques.\n\r\n3. Explore the shift from hunting to farming.\n\r\n4. Compare past and present ways of life.', '<b>Hunter-Gatherer</b>: A person who finds food by hunting and collecting plants\n<b>Tools</b>: Items used to do work or make life easier\n<b>Fire</b>: A source of heat and light\n<b>Cave</b>: A natural space in a mountain or hill used for shelter\n<b>Migration</b>: Moving from one place to another to live', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vFnTXUdaM5M', '2025-05-25 22:29:59'),
