(155, 18, 4, 'Lesson 1', '', 'Big Question: What is security and why is it important for children?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Define security.\n\r\n2. Identify types of security (personal, environmental).\n\r\n3. Understand why children need protection.\n\r\n4. List safe practices at home, school, and on the road.', '<b>Security</b>: Being safe and protected from danger\n<b>Safety</b>: Avoiding harm or injury\n<b>Danger</b>: Something that can cause harm\n<b>Rules</b>: Guidelines we follow to stay safe\n<b>Emergency</b>: A serious and sudden situation needing quick action', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BYnssJUfaSQ', '2025-05-25 22:30:13'),
(156, 18, 4, 'Lesson 2', '', 'Big Question: How can we keep ourselves and our school environment safe?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Identify safety hazards in the school.\n\r\n2. Understand how to prevent accidents.\n\r\n3. Demonstrate safe behavior.\n\r\n4. Create school safety posters or routines.', '<b>Hazard</b>: Something that can cause harm or danger\n<b>Prevention</b>: Steps taken to avoid harm or accidents\n<b>Alert</b>: Watching out for danger or warning signs\n<b>First Aid</b>: Help given before medical experts arrive\n<b>Safety Signs</b>: Symbols or messages that show what to do to stay safe', '', '', '', '2025-05-25 22:30:13'),
(157, 18, 4, 'Lesson 3', '', 'Big Question: What should you do when you feel unsafe?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Recognize situations that can be dangerous.\n\r\n2. Identify trusted adults they can talk to.\n\r\n3. Practice basic safety drills (fire, stranger danger).\n\r\n4. Reflect on how they feel and respond during unsafe situations.', '<b>Unsafe</b>: Not safe; likely to cause harm\n<b>Trusted Adult</b>: A grown-up you can count on for help\n<b>Stranger</b>: Someone you dont know\n<b>Warning</b>: A sign or signal of danger\n<b>Escape</b>: Getting away from danger quickly', '', '', '', '2025-05-25 22:30:14'),
