(162, 5, 4, 'Lesson 1', '', 'Big Question: What is good governance and why is it important?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Define good governance and understand its importance.\n\r\n2. Identify and describe the three levels of government in Nigeria.\n\r\n3. Explain the roles and responsibilities of local, state, and federal governments.\n\r\n4. Demonstrate empathy and problem-solving in governance through interactive activities.', '<b>Government</b>: A group of people who have the power to make and enforce laws for a country\n<b>Governor</b>: The leader of a state government\n<b>President</b>: The head of the federal government in Nigeria\n<b>Obedience</b>: Doing what is expected or required\n<b>Leadership</b>: The ability to guide or direct others', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q8-8bg_8gi4', '2025-05-25 22:29:00'),
(163, 5, 4, 'Lesson 2', '', 'Big Question: What are the different types of government, and how do they differ?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Identify and describe different types of government: monarchy, traditional governance, oligarchy, and constitutional government.\n\r\n2. Compare and contrast the characteristics of each government type.\n\r\n3. Understand how different governments handle crises and manage citizen relationships.\n\r\n4. Apply their knowledge of government types to solve problems in a classroom scenario.', '<b>Monarchy</b>: A government ruled by a king or queen\n<b>Traditional Government</b>: Leadership based on customs and traditions\n<b>Oligarchy</b>: A government controlled by a small group of people\n<b>Constitutional Government</b>: A government based on laws and a constitution\n<b>Authority</b>: The right to make decisions and enforce rules', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EUHPYMiyr2c&pp=0gcJCYQJAYcqIYzv', '2025-05-25 22:29:00'),
(164, 5, 4, 'Lesson 3', '', 'Big Question: What values are important for our nation and why?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Define national values and understand their importance in society.\n\r\n2. Identify key national values such as obedience, loyalty, dedication, honesty, and contentment.\n\r\n3. Explain how these values can address societal issues like corruption and environmental pollution.\n\r\n4. Demonstrate understanding through role-play and discussion.\n\r\n5. Develop critical thinking by discussing real-life applications of national values.', '<b>Values</b>: Important ideas or beliefs people live by\n<b>Obedience</b>: Following rules or instructions\n<b>Loyalty</b>: Being faithful to a person, group, or country\n<b>Dedication</b>: Committing to a task or purpose\n<b>Contentment</b>: Being satisfied with what you have\n<b>Corruption</b>: Dishonest or unfair behavior, often for personal gain', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5H2-B44L0Is', '2025-05-25 22:29:00'),
(165, 5, 4, 'Lesson 4', '', 'Big Question: What defines a nation and what are its characteristics?\n\n\r\nLearning Objectives:\n\r\n1. Understand the concept of a nation and its defining characteristics.\n\r\n2. Identify the characteristics of Nigeria as a nation.\n\r\n3. Recognize how these characteristics foster unity and identity.', '<b>Nation</b>: A group of people living in the same country under one government\n<b>Unity</b>: Working together as one\n<b>Diversity</b>: Differences in culture, religion, language, and more\n<b>National Identity</b>: A sense of belonging to a country\n<b>Symbol</b>: A mark or object that represents something else', '', '', '', '2025-05-25 22:29:00'),
